1661 
1662 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1663 /// Create one branch for each element in the collection.
1664 ///
1665 /// Each entry in the collection becomes a top level branch if the
1666 /// corresponding class is not a collection. If it is a collection, the entry
1667 /// in the collection becomes in turn top level branches, etc.
1668 /// The splitlevel is decreased by 1 every time a new collection is found.
1669 /// For example if list is a TObjArray*
1670 /// - if splitlevel = 1, one top level branch is created for each element
1671 /// of the TObjArray.
1672 /// - if splitlevel = 2, one top level branch is created for each array element.
1673 /// if, in turn, one of the array elements is a TCollection, one top level
1674 /// branch will be created for each element of this collection.
1675 ///
1676 /// In case a collection element is a TClonesArray, the special Tree constructor
1677 /// for TClonesArray is called.
1678 /// The collection itself cannot be a TClonesArray.
1679 ///
1680 /// The function returns the total number of branches created.
1681 ///
1682 /// If name is given, all branch names will be prefixed with name_.
1683 ///
1684 /// IMPORTANT NOTE1: This function should not be called with splitlevel < 1.
1685 ///
1686 /// IMPORTANT NOTE2: The branches created by this function will have names
1687 /// corresponding to the collection or object names. It is important
1688 /// to give names to collections to avoid misleading branch names or
1689 /// identical branch names. By default collections have a name equal to
1690 /// the corresponding class name, e.g. the default name for a TList is "TList".
1691 ///
1692 /// And in general, in case two or more master branches contain subbranches
1693 /// with identical names, one must add a "." (dot) character at the end
1694 /// of the master branch name. This will force the name of the subbranches
1695 /// to be of the form `master.subbranch` instead of simply `subbranch`.
1696 /// This situation happens when the top level object
1697 /// has two or more members referencing the same class.
1698 /// For example, if a Tree has two branches B1 and B2 corresponding
1699 /// to objects of the same class MyClass, one can do:
1700 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
1701 /// tree.Branch("B1.","MyClass",&b1,8000,1);
1702 /// tree.Branch("B2.","MyClass",&b2,8000,1);
1703 /// ~~~
1704 /// if MyClass has 3 members a,b,c, the two instructions above will generate
1705 /// subbranches called B1.a, B1.b ,B1.c, B2.a, B2.b, B2.c
1706 ///
1707 /// Example:
1708 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
1709 /// {
1710 /// TTree T("T","test list");
1711 /// TList *list = new TList();
1712 ///
1713 /// TObjArray *a1 = new TObjArray();
1714 /// a1->SetName("a1");
1715 /// list->Add(a1);
1716 /// TH1F *ha1a = new TH1F("ha1a","ha1",100,0,1);
1717 /// TH1F *ha1b = new TH1F("ha1b","ha1",100,0,1);
1718 /// a1->Add(ha1a);
1719 /// a1->Add(ha1b);
1720 /// TObjArray *b1 = new TObjArray();
1721 /// b1->SetName("b1");
1722 /// list->Add(b1);
1723 /// TH1F *hb1a = new TH1F("hb1a","hb1",100,0,1);
1724 /// TH1F *hb1b = new TH1F("hb1b","hb1",100,0,1);
1725 /// b1->Add(hb1a);
1726 /// b1->Add(hb1b);
1727 ///
1728 /// TObjArray *a2 = new TObjArray();
1729 /// a2->SetName("a2");
1730 /// list->Add(a2);
1731 /// TH1S *ha2a = new TH1S("ha2a","ha2",100,0,1);
1732 /// TH1S *ha2b = new TH1S("ha2b","ha2",100,0,1);
1733 /// a2->Add(ha2a);
1734 /// a2->Add(ha2b);
1735 ///
1736 /// T.Branch(list,16000,2);
1737 /// T.Print();
1738 /// }
1739 /// ~~~
1740 
1741 Int_t TTree::Branch(TCollection* li, Int_t bufsize /* = 32000 */, Int_t splitlevel /* = 99 */, const char* name /* = "" */)
1742 {
1743 
1744  if (!li) {
1745  return 0;
1746  }
1747  TObject* obj = 0;
1748  Int_t nbranches = GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries();
1749  if (li->InheritsFrom(TClonesArray::Class())) {
1750  Error("Branch", "Cannot call this constructor for a TClonesArray");
1751  return 0;
1752  }
1753  Int_t nch = strlen(name);
1754  TString branchname;
1755  TIter next(li);
1756  while ((obj = next())) {
1757  if ((splitlevel > 1) && obj->InheritsFrom(TCollection::Class()) && !obj->InheritsFrom(TClonesArray::Class())) {
1758  TCollection* col = (TCollection*) obj;
1759  if (nch) {
1760  branchname.Form("%s_%s_", name, col->GetName());
1761  } else {
1762  branchname.Form("%s_", col->GetName());
1763  }
1764  Branch(col, bufsize, splitlevel - 1, branchname);
1765  } else {
1766  if (nch && (name[nch-1] == '_')) {
1767  branchname.Form("%s%s", name, obj->GetName());
1768  } else {
1769  if (nch) {
1770  branchname.Form("%s_%s", name, obj->GetName());
1771  } else {
1772  branchname.Form("%s", obj->GetName());
1773  }
1774  }
1775  if (splitlevel > 99) {
1776  branchname += ".";
1777  }
1778  Bronch(branchname, obj->ClassName(), li->GetObjectRef(obj), bufsize, splitlevel - 1);
1779  }
1780  }
1781  return GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries() - nbranches;
1782 }
1783 
1784 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1785 /// Create one branch for each element in the folder.
1786 /// Returns the total number of branches created.
1787 
1788 Int_t TTree::Branch(const char* foldername, Int_t bufsize /* = 32000 */, Int_t splitlevel /* = 99 */)
1789 {
1790  TObject* ob = gROOT->FindObjectAny(foldername);
1791  if (!ob) {
1792  return 0;
1793  }
1794  if (ob->IsA() != TFolder::Class()) {
1795  return 0;
1796  }
1797  Int_t nbranches = GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries();
1798  TFolder* folder = (TFolder*) ob;
1799  TIter next(folder->GetListOfFolders());
1800  TObject* obj = 0;
1801  char* curname = new char[1000];
1802  char occur[20];
1803  while ((obj = next())) {
1804  snprintf(curname,1000, "%s/%s", foldername, obj->GetName());
1805  if (obj->IsA() == TFolder::Class()) {
1806  Branch(curname, bufsize, splitlevel - 1);
1807  } else {
1808  void* add = (void*) folder->GetListOfFolders()->GetObjectRef(obj);
1809  for (Int_t i = 0; i < 1000; ++i) {
1810  if (curname[i] == 0) {
1811  break;
1812  }
1813  if (curname[i] == '/') {
1814  curname[i] = '.';
1815  }
1816  }
1817  Int_t noccur = folder->Occurence(obj);
1818  if (noccur > 0) {
1819  snprintf(occur,20, "_%d", noccur);
1820  strlcat(curname, occur,1000);
1821  }
1822  TBranchElement* br = (TBranchElement*) Bronch(curname, obj->ClassName(), add, bufsize, splitlevel - 1);
1823  if (br) br->SetBranchFolder();
1824  }
1825  }
1826  delete[] curname;
1827  return GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries() - nbranches;
1828 }
1829 
1830 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1831 /// Create a new TTree Branch.
1832 ///
1833 /// This Branch constructor is provided to support non-objects in
1834 /// a Tree. The variables described in leaflist may be simple
1835 /// variables or structures. // See the two following
1836 /// constructors for writing objects in a Tree.
1837 ///
1838 /// By default the branch buffers are stored in the same file as the Tree.
1839 /// use TBranch::SetFile to specify a different file
1840 ///
1841 /// * address is the address of the first item of a structure.
1842 /// * leaflist is the concatenation of all the variable names and types
1843 /// separated by a colon character :
1844 /// The variable name and the variable type are separated by a slash (/).
1845 /// The variable type may be 0,1 or 2 characters. If no type is given,
1846 /// the type of the variable is assumed to be the same as the previous
1847 /// variable. If the first variable does not have a type, it is assumed
1848 /// of type F by default. The list of currently supported types is given below:
1849 /// - `C` : a character string terminated by the 0 character
1850 /// - `B` : an 8 bit signed integer (`Char_t`)
1851 /// - `b` : an 8 bit unsigned integer (`UChar_t`)
1852 /// - `S` : a 16 bit signed integer (`Short_t`)
1853 /// - `s` : a 16 bit unsigned integer (`UShort_t`)
1854 /// - `I` : a 32 bit signed integer (`Int_t`)
1855 /// - `i` : a 32 bit unsigned integer (`UInt_t`)
1856 /// - `F` : a 32 bit floating point (`Float_t`)
1857 /// - `f` : a 24 bit floating point with truncated mantissa (`Float16_t`)
1858 /// - `D` : a 64 bit floating point (`Double_t`)
1859 /// - `d` : a 24 bit truncated floating point (`Double32_t`)
1860 /// - `L` : a 64 bit signed integer (`Long64_t`)
1861 /// - `l` : a 64 bit unsigned integer (`ULong64_t`)
1862 /// - `O` : [the letter `o`, not a zero] a boolean (`Bool_t`)
1863 ///
1864 /// Arrays of values are supported with the following syntax:
1865 /// - If leaf name has the form var[nelem], where nelem is alphanumeric, then
1866 /// if nelem is a leaf name, it is used as the variable size of the array,
1867 /// otherwise return 0.
1868 /// - If leaf name has the form var[nelem], where nelem is a non-negative integer, then
1869 /// it is used as the fixed size of the array.
1870 /// - If leaf name has the form of a multi-dimensional array (e.g. var[nelem][nelem2])
1871 /// where nelem and nelem2 are non-negative integer) then
1872 /// it is used as a 2 dimensional array of fixed size.
1873 /// - In case of the truncated floating point types (Float16_t and Double32_t) you can
1874 /// furthermore specify the range in the style [xmin,xmax] or [xmin,xmax,nbits] after
1875 /// the type character. See `TStreamerElement::GetRange()` for further information.
1876 ///
1877 /// Any of other form is not supported.
1878 ///
1879 /// Note that the TTree will assume that all the item are contiguous in memory.
1880 /// On some platform, this is not always true of the member of a struct or a class,
1881 /// due to padding and alignment. Sorting your data member in order of decreasing
1882 /// sizeof usually leads to their being contiguous in memory.
1883 ///
1884 /// * bufsize is the buffer size in bytes for this branch
1885 /// The default value is 32000 bytes and should be ok for most cases.
1886 /// You can specify a larger value (e.g. 256000) if your Tree is not split
1887 /// and each entry is large (Megabytes)
1888 /// A small value for bufsize is optimum if you intend to access
1889 /// the entries in the Tree randomly and your Tree is in split mode.
1890 
1891 TBranch* TTree::Branch(const char* name, void* address, const char* leaflist, Int_t bufsize /* = 32000 */)
1892 {
1893  TBranch* branch = new TBranch(this, name, address, leaflist, bufsize);
1894  if (branch->IsZombie()) {
1895  delete branch;
1896  branch = 0;
1897  return 0;
1898  }
1899  fBranches.Add(branch);
1900  return branch;
1901 }
1902 
1903 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1904 /// Create a new branch with the object of class classname at address addobj.
1905 ///
1906 /// WARNING:
1907 ///
1908 /// Starting with Root version 3.01, the Branch function uses the new style
1909 /// branches (TBranchElement). To get the old behaviour, you can:
1910 /// - call BranchOld or
1911 /// - call TTree::SetBranchStyle(0)
1912 ///
1913 /// Note that with the new style, classname does not need to derive from TObject.
1914 /// It must derived from TObject if the branch style has been set to 0 (old)
1915 ///
1916 /// Note: See the comments in TBranchElement::SetAddress() for a more
1917 /// detailed discussion of the meaning of the addobj parameter in
1918 /// the case of new-style branches.
1919 ///
1920 /// Use splitlevel < 0 instead of splitlevel=0 when the class
1921 /// has a custom Streamer
1922 ///
1923 /// Note: if the split level is set to the default (99), TTree::Branch will
1924 /// not issue a warning if the class can not be split.
1925 
1926 TBranch* TTree::Branch(const char* name, const char* classname, void* addobj, Int_t bufsize /* = 32000 */, Int_t splitlevel /* = 99 */)
1927 {
1928  if (fgBranchStyle == 1) {
1929  return Bronch(name, classname, addobj, bufsize, splitlevel);
1930  } else {
1931  if (splitlevel < 0) {
1932  splitlevel = 0;
1933  }
1934  return BranchOld(name, classname, addobj, bufsize, splitlevel);
1935  }
1936 }
1937 
1938 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
1939 /// Create a new TTree BranchObject.
1940 ///
1941 /// Build a TBranchObject for an object of class classname.
1942 /// addobj is the address of a pointer to an object of class classname.
1943 /// IMPORTANT: classname must derive from TObject.
1944 /// The class dictionary must be available (ClassDef in class header).
1945 ///
1946 /// This option requires access to the library where the corresponding class
1947 /// is defined. Accessing one single data member in the object implies
1948 /// reading the full object.
1949 /// See the next Branch constructor for a more efficient storage
1950 /// in case the entry consists of arrays of identical objects.
1951 ///
1952 /// By default the branch buffers are stored in the same file as the Tree.
1953 /// use TBranch::SetFile to specify a different file
1954 ///
1955 /// IMPORTANT NOTE about branch names:
1956 ///
1957 /// And in general, in case two or more master branches contain subbranches
1958 /// with identical names, one must add a "." (dot) character at the end
1959 /// of the master branch name. This will force the name of the subbranches
1960 /// to be of the form `master.subbranch` instead of simply `subbranch`.
1961 /// This situation happens when the top level object
1962 /// has two or more members referencing the same class.
1963 /// For example, if a Tree has two branches B1 and B2 corresponding
1964 /// to objects of the same class MyClass, one can do:
1965 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
1966 /// tree.Branch("B1.","MyClass",&b1,8000,1);
1967 /// tree.Branch("B2.","MyClass",&b2,8000,1);
1968 /// ~~~
1969 /// if MyClass has 3 members a,b,c, the two instructions above will generate
1970 /// subbranches called B1.a, B1.b ,B1.c, B2.a, B2.b, B2.c
1971 ///
1972 /// bufsize is the buffer size in bytes for this branch
1973 /// The default value is 32000 bytes and should be ok for most cases.
1974 /// You can specify a larger value (e.g. 256000) if your Tree is not split
1975 /// and each entry is large (Megabytes)
1976 /// A small value for bufsize is optimum if you intend to access
1977 /// the entries in the Tree randomly and your Tree is in split mode.
1978 
1979 TBranch* TTree::BranchOld(const char* name, const char* classname, void* addobj, Int_t bufsize /* = 32000 */, Int_t splitlevel /* = 1 */)
1980 {
1981  TClass* cl = TClass::GetClass(classname);
1982  if (!cl) {
1983  Error("BranchOld", "Cannot find class: '%s'", classname);
1984  return 0;
1985  }
1986  if (!cl->IsTObject()) {
1987  if (fgBranchStyle == 0) {
1988  Fatal("BranchOld", "The requested class ('%s') does not inherit from TObject.\n"
1989  "\tfgBranchStyle is set to zero requesting by default to use BranchOld.\n"
1990  "\tIf this is intentional use Bronch instead of Branch or BranchOld.", classname);
1991  } else {
1992  Fatal("BranchOld", "The requested class ('%s') does not inherit from TObject.\n"
1993  "\tYou can not use BranchOld to store objects of this type.",classname);
1994  }
1995  return 0;
1996  }
1997  TBranch* branch = new TBranchObject(this, name, classname, addobj, bufsize, splitlevel);
1998  fBranches.Add(branch);
1999  if (!splitlevel) {
2000  return branch;
2001  }
2002  // We are going to fully split the class now.
2003  TObjArray* blist = branch->GetListOfBranches();
2004  const char* rdname = 0;
2005  const char* dname = 0;
2006  TString branchname;
2007  char** apointer = (char**) addobj;
2008  TObject* obj = (TObject*) *apointer;
2009  Bool_t delobj = kFALSE;
2010  if (!obj) {
2011  obj = (TObject*) cl->New();
2012  delobj = kTRUE;
2013  }
2014  // Build the StreamerInfo if first time for the class.
2015  BuildStreamerInfo(cl, obj);
2016  // Loop on all public data members of the class and its base classes.
2017  Int_t lenName = strlen(name);
2018  Int_t isDot = 0;
2019  if (name[lenName-1] == '.') {
2020  isDot = 1;
2021  }
2022  TBranch* branch1 = 0;
2023  TRealData* rd = 0;
2024  TRealData* rdi = 0;
2025  TIter nexti(cl->GetListOfRealData());
2026  TIter next(cl->GetListOfRealData());
2027  // Note: This loop results in a full split because the
2028  // real data list includes all data members of
2029  // data members.
2030  while ((rd = (TRealData*) next())) {
2031  if (rd->TestBit(TRealData::kTransient)) continue;
2032 
2033  // Loop over all data members creating branches for each one.
2034  TDataMember* dm = rd->GetDataMember();
2035  if (!dm->IsPersistent()) {
2036  // Do not process members with an "!" as the first character in the comment field.
2037  continue;
2038  }
2039  if (rd->IsObject()) {
2040  // We skip data members of class type.
2041  // But we do build their real data, their
2042  // streamer info, and write their streamer
2043  // info to the current directory's file.
2044  // Oh yes, and we also do this for all of
2045  // their base classes.
2046  TClass* clm = TClass::GetClass(dm->GetFullTypeName());
2047  if (clm) {
2048  BuildStreamerInfo(clm, (char*) obj + rd->GetThisOffset());
2049  }
2050  continue;
2051  }
2052  rdname = rd->GetName();
2053  dname = dm->GetName();
2054  if (cl->CanIgnoreTObjectStreamer()) {
2055  // Skip the TObject base class data members.
2056  // FIXME: This prevents a user from ever
2057  // using these names themself!
2058  if (!strcmp(dname, "fBits")) {
2059  continue;
2060  }
2061  if (!strcmp(dname, "fUniqueID")) {
2062  continue;
2063  }
2064  }
2065  TDataType* dtype = dm->GetDataType();
2066  Int_t code = 0;
2067  if (dtype) {
2068  code = dm->GetDataType()->GetType();
2069  }
2070  // Encode branch name. Use real data member name
2071  branchname = rdname;
2072  if (isDot) {
2073  if (dm->IsaPointer()) {
2074  // FIXME: This is wrong! The asterisk is not usually in the front!
2075  branchname.Form("%s%s", name, &rdname[1]);
2076  } else {
2077  branchname.Form("%s%s", name, &rdname[0]);
2078  }
2079  }
2080  // FIXME: Change this to a string stream.
2081  TString leaflist;
2082  Int_t offset = rd->GetThisOffset();
2083  char* pointer = ((char*) obj) + offset;
2084  if (dm->IsaPointer()) {
2085  // We have a pointer to an object or a pointer to an array of basic types.
2086  TClass* clobj = 0;
2087  if (!dm->IsBasic()) {
2088  clobj = TClass::GetClass(dm->GetTypeName());
2089  }
2090  if (clobj && clobj->InheritsFrom(TClonesArray::Class())) {
2091  // We have a pointer to a clones array.
2092  char* cpointer = (char*) pointer;
2093  char** ppointer = (char**) cpointer;
2094  TClonesArray* li = (TClonesArray*) *ppointer;
2095  if (splitlevel != 2) {
2096  if (isDot) {
2097  branch1 = new TBranchClones(branch,branchname, pointer, bufsize);
2098  } else {
2099  // FIXME: This is wrong! The asterisk is not usually in the front!
2100  branch1 = new TBranchClones(branch,&branchname.Data()[1], pointer, bufsize);
2101  }
2102  blist->Add(branch1);
2103  } else {
2104  if (isDot) {
2105  branch1 = new TBranchObject(branch, branchname, li->ClassName(), pointer, bufsize);
2106  } else {
2107  // FIXME: This is wrong! The asterisk is not usually in the front!
2108  branch1 = new TBranchObject(branch, &branchname.Data()[1], li->ClassName(), pointer, bufsize);
2109  }
2110  blist->Add(branch1);
2111  }
2112  } else if (clobj) {
2113  // We have a pointer to an object.
2114  //
2115  // It must be a TObject object.
2116  if (!clobj->IsTObject()) {
2117  continue;
2118  }
2119  branch1 = new TBranchObject(branch, dname, clobj->GetName(), pointer, bufsize, 0);
2120  if (isDot) {
2121  branch1->SetName(branchname);
2122  } else {
2123  // FIXME: This is wrong! The asterisk is not usually in the front!
2124  // Do not use the first character (*).
2125  branch1->SetName(&branchname.Data()[1]);
2126  }
2127  blist->Add(branch1);
2128  } else {
2129  // We have a pointer to an array of basic types.
2130  //
2131  // Check the comments in the text of the code for an index specification.
2132  const char* index = dm->GetArrayIndex();
2133  if (index[0]) {
2134  // We are a pointer to a varying length array of basic types.
2135  //check that index is a valid data member name
2136  //if member is part of an object (e.g. fA and index=fN)
2137  //index must be changed from fN to fA.fN
2138  TString aindex (rd->GetName());
2139  Ssiz_t rdot = aindex.Last('.');
2140  if (rdot>=0) {
2141  aindex.Remove(rdot+1);
2142  aindex.Append(index);
2143  }
2144  nexti.Reset();
2145  while ((rdi = (TRealData*) nexti())) {
2146  if (rdi->TestBit(TRealData::kTransient)) continue;
2147 
2148  if (!strcmp(rdi->GetName(), index)) {
2149  break;
2150  }
2151  if (!strcmp(rdi->GetName(), aindex)) {
2152  index = rdi->GetName();
2153  break;
2154  }
2155  }
2156 
2157  char vcode = DataTypeToChar((EDataType)code);
2158  // Note that we differentiate between strings and
2159  // char array by the fact that there is NO specified
2160  // size for a string (see next if (code == 1)
2161 
2162  if (vcode) {
2163  leaflist.Form("%s[%s]/%c", &rdname[0], index, vcode);
2164  } else {
2165  Error("BranchOld", "Cannot create branch for rdname: %s code: %d", branchname.Data(), code);
2166  leaflist = "";
2167  }
2168  } else {
2169  // We are possibly a character string.
2170  if (code == 1) {
2171  // We are a character string.
2172  leaflist.Form("%s/%s", dname, "C");
2173  } else {
2174  // Invalid array specification.
2175  // FIXME: We need an error message here.
2176  continue;
2177  }
2178  }
2179  // There are '*' in both the branchname and leaflist, remove them.
2180  TString bname( branchname );
2181  bname.ReplaceAll("*","");
2182  leaflist.ReplaceAll("*","");
2183  // Add the branch to the tree and indicate that the address
2184  // is that of a pointer to be dereferenced before using.
2185  branch1 = new TBranch(branch, bname, *((void**) pointer), leaflist, bufsize);
2186  TLeaf* leaf = (TLeaf*) branch1->GetListOfLeaves()->At(0);
2187  leaf->SetBit(TLeaf::kIndirectAddress);
2188  leaf->SetAddress((void**) pointer);
2189  blist->Add(branch1);
2190  }
2191  } else if (dm->IsBasic()) {
2192  // We have a basic type.
2193 
2194  char vcode = DataTypeToChar((EDataType)code);
2195  if (vcode) {
2196  leaflist.Form("%s/%c", rdname, vcode);
2197  } else {
2198  Error("BranchOld", "Cannot create branch for rdname: %s code: %d", branchname.Data(), code);
2199  leaflist = "";
2200  }
2201  branch1 = new TBranch(branch, branchname, pointer, leaflist, bufsize);
2202  branch1->SetTitle(rdname);
2203  blist->Add(branch1);
2204  } else {
2205  // We have a class type.
2206  // Note: This cannot happen due to the rd->IsObject() test above.
2207  // FIXME: Put an error message here just in case.
2208  }
2209  if (branch1) {
2210  branch1->SetOffset(offset);
2211  } else {
2212  Warning("BranchOld", "Cannot process member: '%s'", rdname);
2213  }
2214  }
2215  if (delobj) {
2216  delete obj;
2217  obj = 0;
2218  }
2219  return branch;
2220 }
2221 
2222 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2223 /// Build the optional branch supporting the TRefTable.
2224 /// This branch will keep all the information to find the branches
2225 /// containing referenced objects.
2226 ///
2227 /// At each Tree::Fill, the branch numbers containing the
2228 /// referenced objects are saved to the TBranchRef basket.
2229 /// When the Tree header is saved (via TTree::Write), the branch
2230 /// is saved keeping the information with the pointers to the branches
2231 /// having referenced objects.
2232 
2233 TBranch* TTree::BranchRef()
2234 {
2235  if (!fBranchRef) {
2236  fBranchRef = new TBranchRef(this);
2237  }
2238  return fBranchRef;
2239 }
2240 
2241 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2242 /// Create a new TTree BranchElement.
2243 ///
2244 /// ## WARNING about this new function
2245 ///
2246 /// This function is designed to replace the internal
2247 /// implementation of the old TTree::Branch (whose implementation
2248 /// has been moved to BranchOld).
2249 ///
2250 /// NOTE: The 'Bronch' method supports only one possible calls
2251 /// signature (where the object type has to be specified
2252 /// explicitly and the address must be the address of a pointer).
2253 /// For more flexibility use 'Branch'. Use Bronch only in (rare)
2254 /// cases (likely to be legacy cases) where both the new and old
2255 /// implementation of Branch needs to be used at the same time.
2256 ///
2257 /// This function is far more powerful than the old Branch
2258 /// function. It supports the full C++, including STL and has
2259 /// the same behaviour in split or non-split mode. classname does
2260 /// not have to derive from TObject. The function is based on
2261 /// the new TStreamerInfo.
2262 ///
2263 /// Build a TBranchElement for an object of class classname.
2264 ///
2265 /// addr is the address of a pointer to an object of class
2266 /// classname. The class dictionary must be available (ClassDef
2267 /// in class header).
2268 ///
2269 /// Note: See the comments in TBranchElement::SetAddress() for a more
2270 /// detailed discussion of the meaning of the addr parameter.
2271 ///
2272 /// This option requires access to the library where the
2273 /// corresponding class is defined. Accessing one single data
2274 /// member in the object implies reading the full object.
2275 ///
2276 /// By default the branch buffers are stored in the same file as the Tree.
2277 /// use TBranch::SetFile to specify a different file
2278 ///
2279 /// IMPORTANT NOTE about branch names:
2280 ///
2281 /// And in general, in case two or more master branches contain subbranches
2282 /// with identical names, one must add a "." (dot) character at the end
2283 /// of the master branch name. This will force the name of the subbranches
2284 /// to be of the form `master.subbranch` instead of simply `subbranch`.
2285 /// This situation happens when the top level object
2286 /// has two or more members referencing the same class.
2287 /// For example, if a Tree has two branches B1 and B2 corresponding
2288 /// to objects of the same class MyClass, one can do:
2289 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
2290 /// tree.Branch("B1.","MyClass",&b1,8000,1);
2291 /// tree.Branch("B2.","MyClass",&b2,8000,1);
2292 /// ~~~
2293 /// if MyClass has 3 members a,b,c, the two instructions above will generate
2294 /// subbranches called B1.a, B1.b ,B1.c, B2.a, B2.b, B2.c
2295 ///
2296 /// bufsize is the buffer size in bytes for this branch
2297 /// The default value is 32000 bytes and should be ok for most cases.
2298 /// You can specify a larger value (e.g. 256000) if your Tree is not split
2299 /// and each entry is large (Megabytes)
2300 /// A small value for bufsize is optimum if you intend to access
2301 /// the entries in the Tree randomly and your Tree is in split mode.
2302 ///
2303 /// Use splitlevel < 0 instead of splitlevel=0 when the class
2304 /// has a custom Streamer
2305 ///
2306 /// Note: if the split level is set to the default (99), TTree::Branch will
2307 /// not issue a warning if the class can not be split.
2308 
2309 TBranch* TTree::Bronch(const char* name, const char* classname, void* addr, Int_t bufsize /* = 32000 */, Int_t splitlevel /* = 99 */)
2310 {
2311  return BronchExec(name, classname, addr, kTRUE, bufsize, splitlevel);
2312 }
2313 
2314 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2315 /// Helper function implementing TTree::Bronch and TTree::Branch(const char *name, T &obj);
2316 
2317 TBranch* TTree::BronchExec(const char* name, const char* classname, void* addr, Bool_t isptrptr, Int_t bufsize /* = 32000 */, Int_t splitlevel /* = 99 */)
2318 {
2319  TClass* cl = TClass::GetClass(classname);
2320  if (!cl) {
2321  Error("Bronch", "Cannot find class:%s", classname);
2322  return 0;
2323  }
2324 
2325  //if splitlevel <= 0 and class has a custom Streamer, we must create
2326  //a TBranchObject. We cannot assume that TClass::ReadBuffer is consistent
2327  //with the custom Streamer. The penalty is that one cannot process
2328  //this Tree without the class library containing the class.
2329 
2330  char* objptr = 0;
2331  if (!isptrptr) {
2332  objptr = (char*)addr;
2333  } else if (addr) {
2334  objptr = *((char**) addr);
2335  }
2336 
2337  if (cl == TClonesArray::Class()) {
2338  TClonesArray* clones = (TClonesArray*) objptr;
2339  if (!clones) {
2340  Error("Bronch", "Pointer to TClonesArray is null");
2341  return 0;
2342  }
2343  if (!clones->GetClass()) {
2344  Error("Bronch", "TClonesArray with no class defined in branch: %s", name);
2345  return 0;
2346  }
2347  if (!clones->GetClass()->HasDataMemberInfo()) {
2348  Error("Bronch", "TClonesArray with no dictionary defined in branch: %s", name);
2349  return 0;
2350  }
2351  bool hasCustomStreamer = clones->GetClass()->TestBit(TClass::kHasCustomStreamerMember);
2352  if (splitlevel > 0) {
2353  if (hasCustomStreamer)
2354  Warning("Bronch", "Using split mode on a class: %s with a custom Streamer", clones->GetClass()->GetName());
2355  } else {
2356  if (hasCustomStreamer) clones->BypassStreamer(kFALSE);
2357  TBranchObject *branch = new TBranchObject(this,name,classname,addr,bufsize,0,/*compress=*/ -1,isptrptr);
2358  fBranches.Add(branch);
2359  return branch;
2360  }
2361  }
2362 
2363  if (cl->GetCollectionProxy()) {
2364  TVirtualCollectionProxy* collProxy = cl->GetCollectionProxy();
2365  //if (!collProxy) {
2366  // Error("Bronch", "%s is missing its CollectionProxy (for branch %s)", classname, name);
2367  //}
2368  TClass* inklass = collProxy->GetValueClass();
2369  if (!inklass && (collProxy->GetType() == 0)) {
2370  Error("Bronch", "%s with no class defined in branch: %s", classname, name);
2371  return 0;
2372  }
2373  if ((splitlevel > 0) && inklass && (inklass->GetCollectionProxy() == 0)) {
2374  ROOT::ESTLType stl = cl->GetCollectionType();
2375  if ((stl != ROOT::kSTLmap) && (stl != ROOT::kSTLmultimap)) {
2376  if (!inklass->HasDataMemberInfo()) {
2377  Error("Bronch", "Container with no dictionary defined in branch: %s", name);
2378  return 0;
2379  }
2380  if (inklass->TestBit(TClass::kHasCustomStreamerMember)) {
2381  Warning("Bronch", "Using split mode on a class: %s with a custom Streamer", inklass->GetName());
2382  }
2383  }
2384  }
2385  //-------------------------------------------------------------------------
2386  // If the splitting switch is enabled, the split level is big enough and
2387  // the collection contains pointers we can split it
2388  //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2389 
2390  TBranch *branch;
2391  if( splitlevel > kSplitCollectionOfPointers && collProxy->HasPointers() )
2392  branch = new TBranchSTL( this, name, collProxy, bufsize, splitlevel );
2393  else
2394  branch = new TBranchElement(this, name, collProxy, bufsize, splitlevel);
2395  fBranches.Add(branch);
2396  if (isptrptr) {
2397  branch->SetAddress(addr);
2398  } else {
2399  branch->SetObject(addr);
2400  }
2401  return branch;
2402  }
2403 
2404  Bool_t hasCustomStreamer = kFALSE;
2405  if (!cl->HasDataMemberInfo() && !cl->GetCollectionProxy()) {
2406  Error("Bronch", "Cannot find dictionary for class: %s", classname);
2407  return 0;
2408  }
2409 
2410  if (!cl->GetCollectionProxy() && cl->TestBit(TClass::kHasCustomStreamerMember)) {
2411  // Not an STL container and the linkdef file had a "-" after the class name.
2412  hasCustomStreamer = kTRUE;
2413  }
2414 
2415  if (splitlevel < 0 || ((splitlevel == 0) && hasCustomStreamer && cl->IsTObject())) {
2416  TBranchObject* branch = new TBranchObject(this, name, classname, addr, bufsize, 0, /*compress=*/ ROOT::RCompressionSetting::EAlgorithm::kInherit, isptrptr);
2417  fBranches.Add(branch);
2418  return branch;
2419  }
2420 
2421  if (cl == TClonesArray::Class()) {
2422  // Special case of TClonesArray.
2423  // No dummy object is created.
2424  // The streamer info is not rebuilt unoptimized.
2425  // No dummy top-level branch is created.
2426  // No splitting is attempted.
2427  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, name, (TClonesArray*) objptr, bufsize, splitlevel%kSplitCollectionOfPointers);
2428  fBranches.Add(branch);
2429  if (isptrptr) {
2430  branch->SetAddress(addr);
2431  } else {
2432  branch->SetObject(addr);
2433  }
2434  return branch;
2435  }
2436 
2437  //
2438  // If we are not given an object to use as an i/o buffer
2439  // then create a temporary one which we will delete just
2440  // before returning.
2441  //
2442 
2443  Bool_t delobj = kFALSE;
2444 
2445  if (!objptr) {
2446  objptr = (char*) cl->New();
2447  delobj = kTRUE;
2448  }
2449 
2450  //
2451  // Avoid splitting unsplittable classes.
2452  //
2453 
2454  if ((splitlevel > 0) && !cl->CanSplit()) {
2455  if (splitlevel != 99) {
2456  Warning("Bronch", "%s cannot be split, resetting splitlevel to 0", cl->GetName());
2457  }
2458  splitlevel = 0;
2459  }
2460 
2461  //
2462  // Make sure the streamer info is built and fetch it.
2463  //
2464  // If we are splitting, then make sure the streamer info
2465  // is built unoptimized (data members are not combined).
2466  //
2467 
2468  TStreamerInfo* sinfo = BuildStreamerInfo(cl, objptr, splitlevel==0);
2469  if (!sinfo) {
2470  Error("Bronch", "Cannot build the StreamerInfo for class: %s", cl->GetName());
2471  return 0;
2472  }
2473 
2474  //
2475  // Create a dummy top level branch object.
2476  //
2477 
2478  Int_t id = -1;
2479  if (splitlevel > 0) {
2480  id = -2;
2481  }
2482  TBranchElement* branch = new TBranchElement(this, name, sinfo, id, objptr, bufsize, splitlevel);
2483  fBranches.Add(branch);
2484 
2485  //
2486  // Do splitting, if requested.
2487  //
2488 
2489  if (splitlevel%kSplitCollectionOfPointers > 0) {
2490  branch->Unroll(name, cl, sinfo, objptr, bufsize, splitlevel);
2491  }
2492 
2493  //
2494  // Setup our offsets into the user's i/o buffer.
2495  //
2496 
2497  if (isptrptr) {
2498  branch->SetAddress(addr);
2499  } else {
2500  branch->SetObject(addr);
2501  }
2502 
2503  if (delobj) {
2504  cl->Destructor(objptr);
2505  objptr = 0;
2506  }
2507 
2508  return branch;
2509 }
2510 
2511 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2512 /// Browse content of the TTree.
2513 
2514 void TTree::Browse(TBrowser* b)
2515 {
2516  fBranches.Browse(b);
2517  if (fUserInfo) {
2518  if (strcmp("TList",fUserInfo->GetName())==0) {
2519  fUserInfo->SetName("UserInfo");
2520  b->Add(fUserInfo);
2521  fUserInfo->SetName("TList");
2522  } else {
2523  b->Add(fUserInfo);
2524  }
2525  }
2526 }
2527 
2528 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2529 /// Build a Tree Index (default is TTreeIndex).
2530 /// See a description of the parameters and functionality in
2531 /// TTreeIndex::TTreeIndex().
2532 ///
2533 /// The return value is the number of entries in the Index (< 0 indicates failure).
2534 ///
2535 /// A TTreeIndex object pointed by fTreeIndex is created.
2536 /// This object will be automatically deleted by the TTree destructor.
2537 /// If an index is already existing, this is replaced by the new one without being
2538 /// deleted. This behaviour prevents the deletion of a previously external index
2539 /// assigned to the TTree via the TTree::SetTreeIndex() method.
2540 /// See also comments in TTree::SetTreeIndex().
2541 
2542 Int_t TTree::BuildIndex(const char* majorname, const char* minorname /* = "0" */)
2543 {
2544  fTreeIndex = GetPlayer()->BuildIndex(this, majorname, minorname);
2545  if (fTreeIndex->IsZombie()) {
2546  delete fTreeIndex;
2547  fTreeIndex = 0;
2548  return 0;
2549  }
2550  return fTreeIndex->GetN();
2551 }
2552 
2553 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2554 /// Build StreamerInfo for class cl.
2555 /// pointer is an optional argument that may contain a pointer to an object of cl.
2556 
2557 TStreamerInfo* TTree::BuildStreamerInfo(TClass* cl, void* pointer /* = 0 */, Bool_t canOptimize /* = kTRUE */ )
2558 {
2559  if (!cl) {
2560  return 0;
2561  }
2562  cl->BuildRealData(pointer);
2563  TStreamerInfo* sinfo = (TStreamerInfo*)cl->GetStreamerInfo(cl->GetClassVersion());
2564 
2565  // Create StreamerInfo for all base classes.
2566  TBaseClass* base = 0;
2567  TIter nextb(cl->GetListOfBases());
2568  while((base = (TBaseClass*) nextb())) {
2569  if (base->IsSTLContainer()) {
2570  continue;
2571  }
2572  TClass* clm = TClass::GetClass(base->GetName());
2573  BuildStreamerInfo(clm, pointer, canOptimize);
2574  }
2575  if (sinfo && fDirectory) {
2576  sinfo->ForceWriteInfo(fDirectory->GetFile());
2577  }
2578  return sinfo;
2579 }
2580 
2581 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2582 /// Called by TTree::Fill() when file has reached its maximum fgMaxTreeSize.
2583 /// Create a new file. If the original file is named "myfile.root",
2584 /// subsequent files are named "myfile_1.root", "myfile_2.root", etc.
2585 ///
2586 /// Returns a pointer to the new file.
2587 ///
2588 /// Currently, the automatic change of file is restricted
2589 /// to the case where the tree is in the top level directory.
2590 /// The file should not contain sub-directories.
2591 ///
2592 /// Before switching to a new file, the tree header is written
2593 /// to the current file, then the current file is closed.
2594 ///
2595 /// To process the multiple files created by ChangeFile, one must use
2596 /// a TChain.
2597 ///
2598 /// The new file name has a suffix "_N" where N is equal to fFileNumber+1.
2599 /// By default a Root session starts with fFileNumber=0. One can set
2600 /// fFileNumber to a different value via TTree::SetFileNumber.
2601 /// In case a file named "_N" already exists, the function will try
2602 /// a file named "__N", then "___N", etc.
2603 ///
2604 /// fgMaxTreeSize can be set via the static function TTree::SetMaxTreeSize.
2605 /// The default value of fgMaxTreeSize is 100 Gigabytes.
2606 ///
2607 /// If the current file contains other objects like TH1 and TTree,
2608 /// these objects are automatically moved to the new file.
2609 ///
2610 /// IMPORTANT NOTE:
2611 ///
2612 /// Be careful when writing the final Tree header to the file!
2613 ///
2614 /// Don't do:
2615 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
2616 /// TFile *file = new TFile("myfile.root","recreate");
2617 /// TTree *T = new TTree("T","title");
2618 /// T->Fill(); //loop
2619 /// file->Write();
2620 /// file->Close();
2621 /// ~~~
2622 /// but do the following:
2623 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
2624 /// TFile *file = new TFile("myfile.root","recreate");
2625 /// TTree *T = new TTree("T","title");
2626 /// T->Fill(); //loop
2627 /// file = T->GetCurrentFile(); //to get the pointer to the current file
2628 /// file->Write();
2629 /// file->Close();
2630 /// ~~~
2631 
2632 TFile* TTree::ChangeFile(TFile* file)
2633 {
2634  file->cd();
2635  Write();
2636  Reset();
2637  constexpr auto kBufSize = 2000;
2638  char* fname = new char[kBufSize];
2639  ++fFileNumber;
2640  char uscore[10];
2641  for (Int_t i = 0; i < 10; ++i) {
2642  uscore[i] = 0;
2643  }
2644  Int_t nus = 0;
2645  // Try to find a suitable file name that does not already exist.
2646  while (nus < 10) {
2647  uscore[nus] = '_';
2648  fname[0] = 0;
2649  strlcpy(fname, file->GetName(), kBufSize);
2650 
2651  if (fFileNumber > 1) {
2652  char* cunder = strrchr(fname, '_');
2653  if (cunder) {
2654  snprintf(cunder, kBufSize - Int_t(cunder - fname), "%s%d", uscore, fFileNumber);
2655  const char* cdot = strrchr(file->GetName(), '.');
2656  if (cdot) {
2657  strlcat(fname, cdot, kBufSize);
2658  }
2659  } else {
2660  char fcount[21];
2661  snprintf(fcount,21, "%s%d", uscore, fFileNumber);
2662  strlcat(fname, fcount, kBufSize);
2663  }
2664  } else {
2665  char* cdot = strrchr(fname, '.');
2666  if (cdot) {
2667  snprintf(cdot, kBufSize - Int_t(fname-cdot), "%s%d", uscore, fFileNumber);
2668  strlcat(fname, strrchr(file->GetName(), '.'), kBufSize);
2669  } else {
2670  char fcount[21];
2671  snprintf(fcount,21, "%s%d", uscore, fFileNumber);
2672  strlcat(fname, fcount, kBufSize);
2673  }
2674  }
2675  if (gSystem->AccessPathName(fname)) {
2676  break;
2677  }
2678  ++nus;
2679  Warning("ChangeFile", "file %s already exist, trying with %d underscores", fname, nus+1);
2680  }
2681  Int_t compress = file->GetCompressionSettings();
2682  TFile* newfile = TFile::Open(fname, "recreate", "chain files", compress);
2683  if (newfile == 0) {
2684  Error("Fill","Failed to open new file %s, continuing as a memory tree.",fname);
2685  } else {
2686  Printf("Fill: Switching to new file: %s", fname);
2687  }
2688  // The current directory may contain histograms and trees.
2689  // These objects must be moved to the new file.
2690  TBranch* branch = 0;
2691  TObject* obj = 0;
2692  while ((obj = file->GetList()->First())) {
2693  file->Remove(obj);
2694  // Histogram: just change the directory.
2695  if (obj->InheritsFrom("TH1")) {
2696  gROOT->ProcessLine(TString::Format("((%s*)0x%lx)->SetDirectory((TDirectory*)0x%lx);", obj->ClassName(), (Long_t) obj, (Long_t) newfile));
2697  continue;
2698  }
2699  // Tree: must save all trees in the old file, reset them.
2700  if (obj->InheritsFrom(TTree::Class())) {
2701  TTree* t = (TTree*) obj;
2702  if (t != this) {
2703  t->AutoSave();
2704  t->Reset();
2705  t->fFileNumber = fFileNumber;
2706  }
2707  t->SetDirectory(newfile);
2708  TIter nextb(t->GetListOfBranches());
2709  while ((branch = (TBranch*)nextb())) {
2710  branch->SetFile(newfile);
2711  }
2712  if (t->GetBranchRef()) {
2713  t->GetBranchRef()->SetFile(newfile);
2714  }
2715  continue;
2716  }
2717  // Not a TH1 or a TTree, move object to new file.
2718  if (newfile) newfile->Append(obj);
2719  file->Remove(obj);
2720  }
2721  delete file;
2722  file = 0;
2723  delete[] fname;
2724  fname = 0;
2725  return newfile;
2726 }
2727 
2728 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2729 /// Check whether or not the address described by the last 3 parameters
2730 /// matches the content of the branch. If a Data Model Evolution conversion
2731 /// is involved, reset the fInfo of the branch.
2732 /// The return values are:
2733 //
2734 /// - kMissingBranch (-5) : Missing branch
2735 /// - kInternalError (-4) : Internal error (could not find the type corresponding to a data type number)
2736 /// - kMissingCompiledCollectionProxy (-3) : Missing compiled collection proxy for a compiled collection
2737 /// - kMismatch (-2) : Non-Class Pointer type given does not match the type expected by the branch
2738 /// - kClassMismatch (-1) : Class Pointer type given does not match the type expected by the branch
2739 /// - kMatch (0) : perfect match
2740 /// - kMatchConversion (1) : match with (I/O) conversion
2741 /// - kMatchConversionCollection (2) : match with (I/O) conversion of the content of a collection
2742 /// - kMakeClass (3) : MakeClass mode so we can not check.
2743 /// - kVoidPtr (4) : void* passed so no check was made.
2744 /// - kNoCheck (5) : Underlying TBranch not yet available so no check was made.
2745 
2746 Int_t TTree::CheckBranchAddressType(TBranch* branch, TClass* ptrClass, EDataType datatype, Bool_t isptr)
2747 {
2748  if (GetMakeClass()) {
2749  // If we are in MakeClass mode so we do not really use classes.
2750  return kMakeClass;
2751  }
2752 
2753  // Let's determine what we need!
2754  TClass* expectedClass = 0;
2755  EDataType expectedType = kOther_t;
2756  if (0 != branch->GetExpectedType(expectedClass,expectedType) ) {
2757  // Something went wrong, the warning message has already be issued.
2758  return kInternalError;
2759  }
2760  if (expectedClass && datatype == kOther_t && ptrClass == 0) {
2761  if (branch->InheritsFrom( TBranchElement::Class() )) {
2762  TBranchElement* bEl = (TBranchElement*)branch;
2763  bEl->SetTargetClass( expectedClass->GetName() );
2764  }
2765  if (expectedClass && expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy() && dynamic_cast<TEmulatedCollectionProxy*>(expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy())) {
2766  Error("SetBranchAddress", "Unable to determine the type given for the address for \"%s\". "
2767  "The class expected (%s) refers to an stl collection and do not have a compiled CollectionProxy. "
2768  "Please generate the dictionary for this class (%s)",
2769  branch->GetName(), expectedClass->GetName(), expectedClass->GetName());
2770  return kMissingCompiledCollectionProxy;
2771  }
2772  if (!expectedClass->IsLoaded()) {
2773  // The originally expected class does not have a dictionary, it is then plausible that the pointer being passed is the right type
2774  // (we really don't know). So let's express that.
2775  Error("SetBranchAddress", "Unable to determine the type given for the address for \"%s\". "
2776  "The class expected (%s) does not have a dictionary and needs to be emulated for I/O purposes but is being passed a compiled object."
2777  "Please generate the dictionary for this class (%s)",
2778  branch->GetName(), expectedClass->GetName(), expectedClass->GetName());
2779  } else {
2780  Error("SetBranchAddress", "Unable to determine the type given for the address for \"%s\". "
2781  "This is probably due to a missing dictionary, the original data class for this branch is %s.", branch->GetName(), expectedClass->GetName());
2782  }
2783  return kClassMismatch;
2784  }
2785  if (expectedClass && ptrClass && (branch->GetMother() == branch)) {
2786  // Top Level branch
2787  if (!isptr) {
2788  Error("SetBranchAddress", "The address for \"%s\" should be the address of a pointer!", branch->GetName());
2789  }
2790  }
2791  if (expectedType == kFloat16_t) {
2792  expectedType = kFloat_t;
2793  }
2794  if (expectedType == kDouble32_t) {
2795  expectedType = kDouble_t;
2796  }
2797  if (datatype == kFloat16_t) {
2798  datatype = kFloat_t;
2799  }
2800  if (datatype == kDouble32_t) {
2801  datatype = kDouble_t;
2802  }
2803 
2804  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2805  // Deal with the class renaming
2806  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2807 
2808  if( expectedClass && ptrClass &&
2809  expectedClass != ptrClass &&
2810  branch->InheritsFrom( TBranchElement::Class() ) &&
2811  ptrClass->GetSchemaRules() &&
2812  ptrClass->GetSchemaRules()->HasRuleWithSourceClass( expectedClass->GetName() ) ) {
2813  TBranchElement* bEl = (TBranchElement*)branch;
2814 
2815  if ( ptrClass->GetCollectionProxy() && expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy() ) {
2816  if (gDebug > 7)
2817  Info("SetBranchAddress", "Matching STL collection (at least according to the SchemaRuleSet when "
2818  "reading a %s into a %s",expectedClass->GetName(),ptrClass->GetName());
2819 
2820  bEl->SetTargetClass( ptrClass->GetName() );
2821  return kMatchConversion;
2822 
2823  } else if ( !ptrClass->GetConversionStreamerInfo( expectedClass, bEl->GetClassVersion() ) &&
2824  !ptrClass->FindConversionStreamerInfo( expectedClass, bEl->GetCheckSum() ) ) {
2825  Error("SetBranchAddress", "The pointer type given \"%s\" does not correspond to the type needed \"%s\" by the branch: %s", ptrClass->GetName(), bEl->GetClassName(), branch->GetName());
2826 
2827  bEl->SetTargetClass( expectedClass->GetName() );
2828  return kClassMismatch;
2829  }
2830  else {
2831 
2832  bEl->SetTargetClass( ptrClass->GetName() );
2833  return kMatchConversion;
2834  }
2835 
2836  } else if (expectedClass && ptrClass && !expectedClass->InheritsFrom(ptrClass)) {
2837 
2838  if (expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy() && ptrClass->GetCollectionProxy() &&
2839  branch->InheritsFrom( TBranchElement::Class() ) &&
2840  expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass() &&
2841  ptrClass->GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass() )
2842  {
2843  // In case of collection, we know how to convert them, if we know how to convert their content.
2844  // NOTE: we need to extend this to std::pair ...
2845 
2846  TClass *onfileValueClass = expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass();
2847  TClass *inmemValueClass = ptrClass->GetCollectionProxy()->GetValueClass();
2848 
2849  if (inmemValueClass->GetSchemaRules() &&
2850  inmemValueClass->GetSchemaRules()->HasRuleWithSourceClass(onfileValueClass->GetName() ) )
2851  {
2852  TBranchElement* bEl = (TBranchElement*)branch;
2853  bEl->SetTargetClass( ptrClass->GetName() );
2854  return kMatchConversionCollection;
2855  }
2856  }
2857 
2858  Error("SetBranchAddress", "The pointer type given (%s) does not correspond to the class needed (%s) by the branch: %s", ptrClass->GetName(), expectedClass->GetName(), branch->GetName());
2859  if (branch->InheritsFrom( TBranchElement::Class() )) {
2860  TBranchElement* bEl = (TBranchElement*)branch;
2861  bEl->SetTargetClass( expectedClass->GetName() );
2862  }
2863  return kClassMismatch;
2864 
2865  } else if ((expectedType != kOther_t) && (datatype != kOther_t) && (expectedType != kNoType_t) && (datatype != kNoType_t) && (expectedType != datatype)) {
2866  if (datatype != kChar_t) {
2867  // For backward compatibility we assume that (char*) was just a cast and/or a generic address
2868  Error("SetBranchAddress", "The pointer type given \"%s\" (%d) does not correspond to the type needed \"%s\" (%d) by the branch: %s",
2869  TDataType::GetTypeName(datatype), datatype, TDataType::GetTypeName(expectedType), expectedType, branch->GetName());
2870  return kMismatch;
2871  }
2872  } else if ((expectedClass && (datatype != kOther_t && datatype != kNoType_t && datatype != kInt_t)) ||
2873  (ptrClass && (expectedType != kOther_t && expectedType != kNoType_t && datatype != kInt_t)) ) {
2874  // Sometime a null pointer can look an int, avoid complaining in that case.
2875  if (expectedClass) {
2876  Error("SetBranchAddress", "The pointer type given \"%s\" (%d) does not correspond to the type needed \"%s\" by the branch: %s",
2877  TDataType::GetTypeName(datatype), datatype, expectedClass->GetName(), branch->GetName());
2878  if (branch->InheritsFrom( TBranchElement::Class() )) {
2879  TBranchElement* bEl = (TBranchElement*)branch;
2880  bEl->SetTargetClass( expectedClass->GetName() );
2881  }
2882  } else {
2883  // In this case, it is okay if the first data member is of the right type (to support the case where we are being passed
2884  // a struct).
2885  bool found = false;
2886  if (ptrClass->IsLoaded()) {
2887  TIter next(ptrClass->GetListOfRealData());
2888  TRealData *rdm;
2889  while ((rdm = (TRealData*)next())) {
2890  if (rdm->GetThisOffset() == 0) {
2891  TDataType *dmtype = rdm->GetDataMember()->GetDataType();
2892  if (dmtype) {
2893  EDataType etype = (EDataType)dmtype->GetType();
2894  if (etype == expectedType) {
2895  found = true;
2896  }
2897  }
2898  break;
2899  }
2900  }
2901  } else {
2902  TIter next(ptrClass->GetListOfDataMembers());
2903  TDataMember *dm;
2904  while ((dm = (TDataMember*)next())) {
2905  if (dm->GetOffset() == 0) {
2906  TDataType *dmtype = dm->GetDataType();
2907  if (dmtype) {
2908  EDataType etype = (EDataType)dmtype->GetType();
2909  if (etype == expectedType) {
2910  found = true;
2911  }
2912  }
2913  break;
2914  }
2915  }
2916  }
2917  if (found) {
2918  // let's check the size.
2919  TLeaf *last = (TLeaf*)branch->GetListOfLeaves()->Last();
2920  long len = last->GetOffset() + last->GetLenType() * last->GetLen();
2921  if (len <= ptrClass->Size()) {
2922  return kMatch;
2923  }
2924  }
2925  Error("SetBranchAddress", "The pointer type given \"%s\" does not correspond to the type needed \"%s\" (%d) by the branch: %s",
2926  ptrClass->GetName(), TDataType::GetTypeName(expectedType), expectedType, branch->GetName());
2927  }
2928  return kMismatch;
2929  }
2930  if (expectedClass && expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy() && dynamic_cast<TEmulatedCollectionProxy*>(expectedClass->GetCollectionProxy())) {
2931  Error("SetBranchAddress", writeStlWithoutProxyMsg,
2932  expectedClass->GetName(), branch->GetName(), expectedClass->GetName());
2933  if (branch->InheritsFrom( TBranchElement::Class() )) {
2934  TBranchElement* bEl = (TBranchElement*)branch;
2935  bEl->SetTargetClass( expectedClass->GetName() );
2936  }
2937  return kMissingCompiledCollectionProxy;
2938  }
2939  if (expectedClass && branch->InheritsFrom( TBranchElement::Class() )) {
2940  TBranchElement* bEl = (TBranchElement*)branch;
2941  bEl->SetTargetClass( expectedClass->GetName() );
2942  }
2943  return kMatch;
2944 }
2945 
2946 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2947 /// Create a clone of this tree and copy nentries.
2948 ///
2949 /// By default copy all entries.
2950 /// The compression level of the cloned tree is set to the destination
2951 /// file's compression level.
2952 ///
2953 /// NOTE: Only active branches are copied.
2954 /// NOTE: If the TTree is a TChain, the structure of the first TTree
2955 /// is used for the copy.
2956 ///
2957 /// IMPORTANT: The cloned tree stays connected with this tree until
2958 /// this tree is deleted. In particular, any changes in
2959 /// branch addresses in this tree are forwarded to the
2960 /// clone trees, unless a branch in a clone tree has had
2961 /// its address changed, in which case that change stays in
2962 /// effect. When this tree is deleted, all the addresses of
2963 /// the cloned tree are reset to their default values.
2964 ///
2965 /// If 'option' contains the word 'fast' and nentries is -1, the
2966 /// cloning will be done without unzipping or unstreaming the baskets
2967 /// (i.e., a direct copy of the raw bytes on disk).
2968 ///
2969 /// When 'fast' is specified, 'option' can also contain a sorting
2970 /// order for the baskets in the output file.
2971 ///
2972 /// There are currently 3 supported sorting order:
2973 ///
2974 /// - SortBasketsByOffset (the default)
2975 /// - SortBasketsByBranch
2976 /// - SortBasketsByEntry
2977 ///
2978 /// When using SortBasketsByOffset the baskets are written in the
2979 /// output file in the same order as in the original file (i.e. the
2980 /// baskets are sorted by their offset in the original file; Usually
2981 /// this also means that the baskets are sorted by the index/number of
2982 /// the _last_ entry they contain)
2983 ///
2984 /// When using SortBasketsByBranch all the baskets of each individual
2985 /// branches are stored contiguously. This tends to optimize reading
2986 /// speed when reading a small number (1->5) of branches, since all
2987 /// their baskets will be clustered together instead of being spread
2988 /// across the file. However it might decrease the performance when
2989 /// reading more branches (or the full entry).
2990 ///
2991 /// When using SortBasketsByEntry the baskets with the lowest starting
2992 /// entry are written first. (i.e. the baskets are sorted by the
2993 /// index/number of the first entry they contain). This means that on
2994 /// the file the baskets will be in the order in which they will be
2995 /// needed when reading the whole tree sequentially.
2996 ///
2997 /// For examples of CloneTree, see tutorials:
2998 ///
2999 /// - copytree.C:
3000 /// A macro to copy a subset of a TTree to a new TTree.
3001 /// The input file has been generated by the program in
3002 /// $ROOTSYS/test/Event with: Event 1000 1 1 1
3003 ///
3004 /// - copytree2.C:
3005 /// A macro to copy a subset of a TTree to a new TTree.
3006 /// One branch of the new Tree is written to a separate file.
3007 /// The input file has been generated by the program in
3008 /// $ROOTSYS/test/Event with: Event 1000 1 1 1
3009 
3010 TTree* TTree::CloneTree(Long64_t nentries /* = -1 */, Option_t* option /* = "" */)
3011 {
3012  // Options
3013  Bool_t fastClone = kFALSE;
3014 
3015  TString opt = option;
3016  opt.ToLower();
3017  if (opt.Contains("fast")) {
3018  fastClone = kTRUE;
3019  }
3020 
3021  // If we are a chain, switch to the first tree.
3022  if ((fEntries > 0) && (LoadTree(0) < 0)) {
3023  // FIXME: We need an error message here.
3024  return 0;
3025  }
3026 
3027  // Note: For a tree we get the this pointer, for
3028  // a chain we get the chain's current tree.
3029  TTree* thistree = GetTree();
3030 
3031  // We will use this to override the IO features on the cloned branches.
3032  ROOT::TIOFeatures features = this->GetIOFeatures();
3033  ;
3034 
3035  // Note: For a chain, the returned clone will be
3036  // a clone of the chain's first tree.
3037  TTree* newtree = (TTree*) thistree->Clone();
3038  if (!newtree) {
3039  return 0;
3040  }
3041 
3042  // The clone should not delete any objects allocated by SetAddress().
3043  TObjArray* branches = newtree->GetListOfBranches();
3044  Int_t nb = branches->GetEntriesFast();
3045  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nb; ++i) {
3046  TBranch* br = (TBranch*) branches->UncheckedAt(i);
3047  if (br->InheritsFrom(TBranchElement::Class())) {
3048  ((TBranchElement*) br)->ResetDeleteObject();
3049  }
3050  }
3051 
3052  // Add the new tree to the list of clones so that
3053  // we can later inform it of changes to branch addresses.
3054  thistree->AddClone(newtree);
3055  if (thistree != this) {
3056  // In case this object is a TChain, add the clone
3057  // also to the TChain's list of clones.
3058  AddClone(newtree);
3059  }
3060 
3061  newtree->Reset();
3062 
3063  TDirectory* ndir = newtree->GetDirectory();
3064  TFile* nfile = 0;
3065  if (ndir) {
3066  nfile = ndir->GetFile();
3067  }
3068  Int_t newcomp = -1;
3069  if (nfile) {
3070  newcomp = nfile->GetCompressionSettings();
3071  }
3072 
3073  //
3074  // Delete non-active branches from the clone.
3075  //
3076  // Note: If we are a chain, this does nothing
3077  // since chains have no leaves.
3078  TObjArray* leaves = newtree->GetListOfLeaves();
3079  Int_t nleaves = leaves->GetEntriesFast();
3080  for (Int_t lndx = 0; lndx < nleaves; ++lndx) {
3081  TLeaf* leaf = (TLeaf*) leaves->UncheckedAt(lndx);
3082  if (!leaf) {
3083  continue;
3084  }
3085  TBranch* branch = leaf->GetBranch();
3086  if (branch && (newcomp > -1)) {
3087  branch->SetCompressionSettings(newcomp);
3088  }
3089  if (branch) branch->SetIOFeatures(features);
3090  if (!branch || !branch->TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
3091  continue;
3092  }
3093  // size might change at each iteration of the loop over the leaves.
3094  nb = branches->GetEntriesFast();
3095  for (Long64_t i = 0; i < nb; ++i) {
3096  TBranch* br = (TBranch*) branches->UncheckedAt(i);
3097  if (br == branch) {
3098  branches->RemoveAt(i);
3099  delete br;
3100  br = 0;
3101  branches->Compress();
3102  break;
3103  }
3104  TObjArray* lb = br->GetListOfBranches();
3105  Int_t nb1 = lb->GetEntriesFast();
3106  for (Int_t j = 0; j < nb1; ++j) {
3107  TBranch* b1 = (TBranch*) lb->UncheckedAt(j);
3108  if (!b1) {
3109  continue;
3110  }
3111  if (b1 == branch) {
3112  lb->RemoveAt(j);
3113  delete b1;
3114  b1 = 0;
3115  lb->Compress();
3116  break;
3117  }
3118  TObjArray* lb1 = b1->GetListOfBranches();
3119  Int_t nb2 = lb1->GetEntriesFast();
3120  for (Int_t k = 0; k < nb2; ++k) {
3121  TBranch* b2 = (TBranch*) lb1->UncheckedAt(k);
3122  if (!b2) {
3123  continue;
3124  }
3125  if (b2 == branch) {
3126  lb1->RemoveAt(k);
3127  delete b2;
3128  b2 = 0;
3129  lb1->Compress();
3130  break;
3131  }
3132  }
3133  }
3134  }
3135  }
3136  leaves->Compress();
3137 
3138  // Copy MakeClass status.
3139  newtree->SetMakeClass(fMakeClass);
3140 
3141  // Copy branch addresses.
3142  CopyAddresses(newtree);
3143 
3144  //
3145  // Copy entries if requested.
3146  //
3147 
3148  if (nentries != 0) {
3149  if (fastClone && (nentries < 0)) {
3150  if ( newtree->CopyEntries( this, -1, option ) < 0 ) {
3151  // There was a problem!
3152  Error("CloneTTree", "TTree has not been cloned\n");
3153  delete newtree;
3154  newtree = 0;
3155  return 0;
3156  }
3157  } else {
3158  newtree->CopyEntries( this, nentries, option );
3159  }
3160  }
3161 
3162  return newtree;
3163 }
3164 
3165 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3166 /// Set branch addresses of passed tree equal to ours.
3167 /// If undo is true, reset the branch address instead of copying them.
3168 /// This insures 'separation' of a cloned tree from its original
3169 
3170 void TTree::CopyAddresses(TTree* tree, Bool_t undo)
3171 {
3172  // Copy branch addresses starting from branches.
3173  TObjArray* branches = GetListOfBranches();
3174  Int_t nbranches = branches->GetEntriesFast();
3175  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
3176  TBranch* branch = (TBranch*) branches->UncheckedAt(i);
3177  if (branch->TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
3178  continue;
3179  }
3180  if (undo) {
3181  TBranch* br = tree->GetBranch(branch->GetName());
3182  tree->ResetBranchAddress(br);
3183  } else {
3184  char* addr = branch->GetAddress();
3185  if (!addr) {
3186  if (branch->IsA() == TBranch::Class()) {
3187  // If the branch was created using a leaflist, the branch itself may not have
3188  // an address but the leaf might already.
3189  TLeaf *firstleaf = (TLeaf*)branch->GetListOfLeaves()->At(0);
3190  if (!firstleaf || firstleaf->GetValuePointer()) {
3191  // Either there is no leaf (and thus no point in copying the address)
3192  // or the leaf has an address but we can not copy it via the branche
3193  // this will be copied via the next loop (over the leaf).
3194  continue;
3195  }
3196  }
3197  // Note: This may cause an object to be allocated.
3198  branch->SetAddress(0);
3199  addr = branch->GetAddress();
3200  }
3201  // FIXME: The GetBranch() function is braindead and may
3202  // not find the branch!
3203  TBranch* br = tree->GetBranch(branch->GetName());
3204  if (br) {
3205  br->SetAddress(addr);
3206  // The copy does not own any object allocated by SetAddress().
3207  if (br->InheritsFrom(TBranchElement::Class())) {
3208  ((TBranchElement*) br)->ResetDeleteObject();
3209  }
3210  } else {
3211  Warning("CopyAddresses", "Could not find branch named '%s' in tree named '%s'", branch->GetName(), tree->GetName());
3212  }
3213  }
3214  }
3215 
3216  // Copy branch addresses starting from leaves.
3217  TObjArray* tleaves = tree->GetListOfLeaves();
3218  Int_t ntleaves = tleaves->GetEntriesFast();
3219  for (Int_t i = 0; i < ntleaves; ++i) {
3220  TLeaf* tleaf = (TLeaf*) tleaves->UncheckedAt(i);
3221  TBranch* tbranch = tleaf->GetBranch();
3222  TBranch* branch = GetBranch(tbranch->GetName());
3223  if (!branch) {
3224  continue;
3225  }
3226  TLeaf* leaf = branch->GetLeaf(tleaf->GetName());
3227  if (!leaf) {
3228  continue;
3229  }
3230  if (branch->TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
3231  continue;
3232  }
3233  if (undo) {
3234  // Now we know whether the address has been transfered
3235  tree->ResetBranchAddress(tbranch);
3236  } else {
3237  TBranchElement *mother = dynamic_cast<TBranchElement*>(leaf->GetBranch()->GetMother());
3238  if (leaf->GetLeafCount() && (leaf->TestBit(TLeaf::kNewValue) || !leaf->GetValuePointer() || (mother && mother->IsObjectOwner())) && tleaf->GetLeafCount())
3239  {
3240  // If it is an array and it was allocated by the leaf itself,
3241  // let's make sure it is large enough for the incoming data.
3242  if (leaf->GetLeafCount()->GetMaximum() < tleaf->GetLeafCount()->GetMaximum()) {
3243  leaf->GetLeafCount()->IncludeRange( tleaf->GetLeafCount() );
3244  if (leaf->GetValuePointer()) {
3245  if (leaf->IsA() == TLeafElement::Class() && mother)
3246  mother->ResetAddress();
3247  else
3248  leaf->SetAddress(nullptr);
3249  }
3250  }
3251  }
3252  if (!branch->GetAddress() && !leaf->GetValuePointer()) {
3253  // We should attempts to set the address of the branch.
3254  // something like:
3255  //(TBranchElement*)branch->GetMother()->SetAddress(0)
3256  //plus a few more subtilities (see TBranchElement::GetEntry).
3257  //but for now we go the simplest route:
3258  //
3259  // Note: This may result in the allocation of an object.
3260  branch->SetupAddresses();
3261  }
3262  if (branch->GetAddress()) {
3263  tree->SetBranchAddress(branch->GetName(), (void*) branch->GetAddress());
3264  TBranch* br = tree->GetBranch(branch->GetName());
3265  if (br) {
3266  // The copy does not own any object allocated by SetAddress().
3267  // FIXME: We do too much here, br may not be a top-level branch.
3268  if (br->InheritsFrom(TBranchElement::Class())) {
3269  ((TBranchElement*) br)->ResetDeleteObject();
3270  }
3271  } else {
3272  Warning("CopyAddresses", "Could not find branch named '%s' in tree named '%s'", branch->GetName(), tree->GetName());
3273  }
3274  } else {
3275  tleaf->SetAddress(leaf->GetValuePointer());
3276  }
3277  }
3278  }
3279 
3280  if (undo &&
3281  ( tree->IsA()->InheritsFrom("TNtuple") || tree->IsA()->InheritsFrom("TNtupleD") )
3282  ) {
3283  tree->ResetBranchAddresses();
3284  }
3285 }
3286 
3287 namespace {
3288 
3289  enum EOnIndexError { kDrop, kKeep, kBuild };
3290 
3291  static Bool_t R__HandleIndex(EOnIndexError onIndexError, TTree *newtree, TTree *oldtree)
3292  {
3293  // Return true if we should continue to handle indices, false otherwise.
3294 
3295  Bool_t withIndex = kTRUE;
3296 
3297  if ( newtree->GetTreeIndex() ) {
3298  if ( oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex() == 0 ) {
3299  switch (onIndexError) {
3300  case kDrop:
3301  delete newtree->GetTreeIndex();
3302  newtree->SetTreeIndex(0);
3303  withIndex = kFALSE;
3304  break;
3305  case kKeep:
3306  // Nothing to do really.
3307  break;
3308  case kBuild:
3309  // Build the index then copy it
3310  if (oldtree->GetTree()->BuildIndex(newtree->GetTreeIndex()->GetMajorName(), newtree->GetTreeIndex()->GetMinorName())) {
3311  newtree->GetTreeIndex()->Append(oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex(), kTRUE);
3312  // Clean up
3313  delete oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex();
3314  oldtree->GetTree()->SetTreeIndex(0);
3315  }
3316  break;
3317  }
3318  } else {
3319  newtree->GetTreeIndex()->Append(oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex(), kTRUE);
3320  }
3321  } else if ( oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex() != 0 ) {
3322  // We discover the first index in the middle of the chain.
3323  switch (onIndexError) {
3324  case kDrop:
3325  // Nothing to do really.
3326  break;
3327  case kKeep: {
3328  TVirtualIndex *index = (TVirtualIndex*) oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex()->Clone();
3329  index->SetTree(newtree);
3330  newtree->SetTreeIndex(index);
3331  break;
3332  }
3333  case kBuild:
3334  if (newtree->GetEntries() == 0) {
3335  // Start an index.
3336  TVirtualIndex *index = (TVirtualIndex*) oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex()->Clone();
3337  index->SetTree(newtree);
3338  newtree->SetTreeIndex(index);
3339  } else {
3340  // Build the index so far.
3341  if (newtree->BuildIndex(oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex()->GetMajorName(), oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex()->GetMinorName())) {
3342  newtree->GetTreeIndex()->Append(oldtree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex(), kTRUE);
3343  }
3344  }
3345  break;
3346  }
3347  } else if ( onIndexError == kDrop ) {
3348  // There is no index on this or on tree->GetTree(), we know we have to ignore any further
3349  // index
3350  withIndex = kFALSE;
3351  }
3352  return withIndex;
3353  }
3354 }
3355 
3356 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3357 /// Copy nentries from given tree to this tree.
3358 /// This routines assumes that the branches that intended to be copied are
3359 /// already connected. The typical case is that this tree was created using
3360 /// tree->CloneTree(0).
3361 ///
3362 /// By default copy all entries.
3363 ///
3364 /// Returns number of bytes copied to this tree.
3365 ///
3366 /// If 'option' contains the word 'fast' and nentries is -1, the cloning will be
3367 /// done without unzipping or unstreaming the baskets (i.e., a direct copy of the
3368 /// raw bytes on disk).
3369 ///
3370 /// When 'fast' is specified, 'option' can also contains a sorting order for the
3371 /// baskets in the output file.
3372 ///
3373 /// There are currently 3 supported sorting order:
3374 ///
3375 /// - SortBasketsByOffset (the default)
3376 /// - SortBasketsByBranch
3377 /// - SortBasketsByEntry
3378 ///
3379 /// See TTree::CloneTree for a detailed explanation of the semantics of these 3 options.
3380 ///
3381 /// If the tree or any of the underlying tree of the chain has an index, that index and any
3382 /// index in the subsequent underlying TTree objects will be merged.
3383 ///
3384 /// There are currently three 'options' to control this merging:
3385 /// - NoIndex : all the TTreeIndex object are dropped.
3386 /// - DropIndexOnError : if any of the underlying TTree object do no have a TTreeIndex,
3387 /// they are all dropped.
3388 /// - AsIsIndexOnError [default]: In case of missing TTreeIndex, the resulting TTree index has gaps.
3389 /// - BuildIndexOnError : If any of the underlying TTree objects do not have a TTreeIndex,
3390 /// all TTreeIndex are 'ignored' and the missing piece are rebuilt.
3391 
3392 Long64_t TTree::CopyEntries(TTree* tree, Long64_t nentries /* = -1 */, Option_t* option /* = "" */)
3393 {
3394  if (!tree) {
3395  return 0;
3396  }
3397  // Options
3398  TString opt = option;
3399  opt.ToLower();
3400  Bool_t fastClone = opt.Contains("fast");
3401  Bool_t withIndex = !opt.Contains("noindex");
3402  EOnIndexError onIndexError;
3403  if (opt.Contains("asisindex")) {
3404  onIndexError = kKeep;
3405  } else if (opt.Contains("buildindex")) {
3406  onIndexError = kBuild;
3407  } else if (opt.Contains("dropindex")) {
3408  onIndexError = kDrop;
3409  } else {
3410  onIndexError = kBuild;
3411  }
3412  Ssiz_t cacheSizeLoc = opt.Index("cachesize=");
3413  Int_t cacheSize = -1;
3414  if (cacheSizeLoc != TString::kNPOS) {
3415  // If the parse faile, cacheSize stays at -1.
3416  Ssiz_t cacheSizeEnd = opt.Index(" ",cacheSizeLoc+10) - (cacheSizeLoc+10);
3417  TSubString cacheSizeStr( opt(cacheSizeLoc+10,cacheSizeEnd) );
3418  auto parseResult = ROOT::FromHumanReadableSize(cacheSizeStr,cacheSize);
3419  if (parseResult == ROOT::EFromHumanReadableSize::kParseFail) {
3420  Warning("CopyEntries","The cachesize option can not be parsed: %s. The default size will be used.",cacheSizeStr.String().Data());
3421  } else if (parseResult == ROOT::EFromHumanReadableSize::kOverflow) {
3422  double m;
3423  const char *munit = nullptr;
3424  ROOT::ToHumanReadableSize(std::numeric_limits<decltype(cacheSize)>::max(),false,&m,&munit);
3425 
3426  Warning("CopyEntries","The cachesize option is too large: %s (%g%s max). The default size will be used.",cacheSizeStr.String().Data(),m,munit);
3427  }
3428  }
3429  if (gDebug > 0 && cacheSize != -1) Info("CopyEntries","Using Cache size: %d\n",cacheSize);
3430 
3431  Long64_t nbytes = 0;
3432  Long64_t treeEntries = tree->GetEntriesFast();
3433  if (nentries < 0) {
3434  nentries = treeEntries;
3435  } else if (nentries > treeEntries) {
3436  nentries = treeEntries;
3437  }
3438 
3439  if (fastClone && (nentries < 0 || nentries == tree->GetEntriesFast())) {
3440  // Quickly copy the basket without decompression and streaming.
3441  Long64_t totbytes = GetTotBytes();
3442  for (Long64_t i = 0; i < nentries; i += tree->GetTree()->GetEntries()) {
3443  if (tree->LoadTree(i) < 0) {
3444  break;
3445  }
3446  if ( withIndex ) {
3447  withIndex = R__HandleIndex( onIndexError, this, tree );
3448  }
3449  if (this->GetDirectory()) {
3450  TFile* file2 = this->GetDirectory()->GetFile();
3451  if (file2 && (file2->GetEND() > TTree::GetMaxTreeSize())) {
3452  if (this->GetDirectory() == (TDirectory*) file2) {
3453  this->ChangeFile(file2);
3454  }
3455  }
3456  }
3457  TTreeCloner cloner(tree->GetTree(), this, option, TTreeCloner::kNoWarnings);
3458  if (cloner.IsValid()) {
3459  this->SetEntries(this->GetEntries() + tree->GetTree()->GetEntries());
3460  if (cacheSize != -1) cloner.SetCacheSize(cacheSize);
3461  cloner.Exec();
3462  } else {
3463  if (i == 0) {
3464  Warning("CopyEntries","%s",cloner.GetWarning());
3465  // If the first cloning does not work, something is really wrong
3466  // (since apriori the source and target are exactly the same structure!)
3467  return -1;
3468  } else {
3469  if (cloner.NeedConversion()) {
3470  TTree *localtree = tree->GetTree();
3471  Long64_t tentries = localtree->GetEntries();
3472  for (Long64_t ii = 0; ii < tentries; ii++) {
3473  if (localtree->GetEntry(ii) <= 0) {
3474  break;
3475  }
3476  this->Fill();
3477  }
3478  if (this->GetTreeIndex()) {
3479  this->GetTreeIndex()->Append(tree->GetTree()->GetTreeIndex(), kTRUE);
3480  }
3481  } else {
3482  Warning("CopyEntries","%s",cloner.GetWarning());
3483  if (tree->GetDirectory() && tree->GetDirectory()->GetFile()) {
3484  Warning("CopyEntries", "Skipped file %s\n", tree->GetDirectory()->GetFile()->GetName());
3485  } else {
3486  Warning("CopyEntries", "Skipped file number %d\n", tree->GetTreeNumber());
3487  }
3488  }
3489  }
3490  }
3491 
3492  }
3493  if (this->GetTreeIndex()) {
3494  this->GetTreeIndex()->Append(0,kFALSE); // Force the sorting
3495  }
3496  nbytes = GetTotBytes() - totbytes;
3497  } else {
3498  if (nentries < 0) {
3499  nentries = treeEntries;
3500  } else if (nentries > treeEntries) {
3501  nentries = treeEntries;
3502  }
3503  Int_t treenumber = -1;
3504  for (Long64_t i = 0; i < nentries; i++) {
3505  if (tree->LoadTree(i) < 0) {
3506  break;
3507  }
3508  if (treenumber != tree->GetTreeNumber()) {
3509  if ( withIndex ) {
3510  withIndex = R__HandleIndex( onIndexError, this, tree );
3511  }
3512  treenumber = tree->GetTreeNumber();
3513  }
3514  if (tree->GetEntry(i) <= 0) {
3515  break;
3516  }
3517  nbytes += this->Fill();
3518  }
3519  if (this->GetTreeIndex()) {
3520  this->GetTreeIndex()->Append(0,kFALSE); // Force the sorting
3521  }
3522  }
3523  return nbytes;
3524 }
3525 
3526 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3527 /// Copy a tree with selection.
3528 ///
3529 /// ### Important:
3530 ///
3531 /// The returned copied tree stays connected with the original tree
3532 /// until the original tree is deleted. In particular, any changes
3533 /// to the branch addresses in the original tree are also made to
3534 /// the copied tree. Any changes made to the branch addresses of the
3535 /// copied tree are overridden anytime the original tree changes its
3536 /// branch addresses. When the original tree is deleted, all the
3537 /// branch addresses of the copied tree are set to zero.
3538 ///
3539 /// For examples of CopyTree, see the tutorials:
3540 ///
3541 /// - copytree.C:
3542 /// Example macro to copy a subset of a tree to a new tree.
3543 /// The input file was generated by running the program in
3544 /// $ROOTSYS/test/Event in this way:
3545 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
3546 /// ./Event 1000 1 1 1
3547 /// ~~~
3548 /// - copytree2.C
3549 /// Example macro to copy a subset of a tree to a new tree.
3550 /// One branch of the new tree is written to a separate file.
3551 /// The input file was generated by running the program in
3552 /// $ROOTSYS/test/Event in this way:
3553 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
3554 /// ./Event 1000 1 1 1
3555 /// ~~~
3556 /// - copytree3.C
3557 /// Example macro to copy a subset of a tree to a new tree.
3558 /// Only selected entries are copied to the new tree.
3559 /// NOTE that only the active branches are copied.
3560 
3561 TTree* TTree::CopyTree(const char* selection, Option_t* option /* = 0 */, Long64_t nentries /* = TTree::kMaxEntries */, Long64_t firstentry /* = 0 */)
3562 {
3563  GetPlayer();
3564  if (fPlayer) {
3565  return fPlayer->CopyTree(selection, option, nentries, firstentry);
3566  }
3567  return 0;
3568 }
3569 
3570 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3571 /// Create a basket for this tree and given branch.
3572 
3573 TBasket* TTree::CreateBasket(TBranch* branch)
3574 {
3575  if (!branch) {
3576  return 0;
3577  }
3578  return new TBasket(branch->GetName(), GetName(), branch);
3579 }
3580 
3581 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3582 /// Delete this tree from memory or/and disk.
3583 ///
3584 /// - if option == "all" delete Tree object from memory AND from disk
3585 /// all baskets on disk are deleted. All keys with same name
3586 /// are deleted.
3587 /// - if option =="" only Tree object in memory is deleted.
3588 
3589 void TTree::Delete(Option_t* option /* = "" */)
3590 {
3591  TFile *file = GetCurrentFile();
3592 
3593  // delete all baskets and header from file
3594  if (file && !strcmp(option,"all")) {
3595  if (!file->IsWritable()) {
3596  Error("Delete","File : %s is not writable, cannot delete Tree:%s", file->GetName(),GetName());
3597  return;
3598  }
3599 
3600  //find key and import Tree header in memory
3601  TKey *key = fDirectory->GetKey(GetName());
3602  if (!key) return;
3603 
3604  TDirectory *dirsav = gDirectory;
3605  file->cd();
3606 
3607  //get list of leaves and loop on all the branches baskets
3608  TIter next(GetListOfLeaves());
3609  TLeaf *leaf;
3610  char header[16];
3611  Int_t ntot = 0;
3612  Int_t nbask = 0;
3613  Int_t nbytes,objlen,keylen;
3614  while ((leaf = (TLeaf*)next())) {
3615  TBranch *branch = leaf->GetBranch();
3616  Int_t nbaskets = branch->GetMaxBaskets();
3617  for (Int_t i=0;i<nbaskets;i++) {
3618  Long64_t pos = branch->GetBasketSeek(i);
3619  if (!pos) continue;
3620  TFile *branchFile = branch->GetFile();
3621  if (!branchFile) continue;
3622  branchFile->GetRecordHeader(header,pos,16,nbytes,objlen,keylen);
3623  if (nbytes <= 0) continue;
3624  branchFile->MakeFree(pos,pos+nbytes-1);
3625  ntot += nbytes;
3626  nbask++;
3627  }
3628  }
3629 
3630  // delete Tree header key and all keys with the same name
3631  // A Tree may have been saved many times. Previous cycles are invalid.
3632  while (key) {
3633  ntot += key->GetNbytes();
3634  key->Delete();
3635  delete key;
3636  key = fDirectory->GetKey(GetName());
3637  }
3638  if (dirsav) dirsav->cd();
3639  if (gDebug) Info("TTree::Delete", "Deleting Tree: %s: %d baskets deleted. Total space freed = %d bytes\n",GetName(),nbask,ntot);
3640  }
3641 
3642  if (fDirectory) {
3643  fDirectory->Remove(this);
3644  //delete the file cache if it points to this Tree
3645  MoveReadCache(file,0);
3646  fDirectory = 0;
3647  ResetBit(kMustCleanup);
3648  }
3649 
3650  // Delete object from CINT symbol table so it can not be used anymore.
3651  gCling->DeleteGlobal(this);
3652 
3653  // Warning: We have intentional invalidated this object while inside a member function!
3654  delete this;
3655 }
3656 
3657  ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3658  /// Called by TKey and TObject::Clone to automatically add us to a directory
3659  /// when we are read from a file.
3660 
3661 void TTree::DirectoryAutoAdd(TDirectory* dir)
3662 {
3663  if (fDirectory == dir) return;
3664  if (fDirectory) {
3665  fDirectory->Remove(this);
3666  // Delete or move the file cache if it points to this Tree
3667  TFile *file = fDirectory->GetFile();
3668  MoveReadCache(file,dir);
3669  }
3670  fDirectory = dir;
3671  TBranch* b = 0;
3672  TIter next(GetListOfBranches());
3673  while((b = (TBranch*) next())) {
3674  b->UpdateFile();
3675  }
3676  if (fBranchRef) {
3677  fBranchRef->UpdateFile();
3678  }
3679  if (fDirectory) fDirectory->Append(this);
3680 }
