5653 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5654 /// Return entry number corresponding to major and minor number.
5655 /// Note that this function returns only the entry number, not the data
5656 /// To read the data corresponding to an entry number, use TTree::GetEntryWithIndex
5657 /// the BuildIndex function has created a table of Long64_t* of sorted values
5658 /// corresponding to val = major<<31 + minor;
5659 /// The function performs binary search in this sorted table.
5660 /// If it finds a pair that matches val, it returns directly the
5661 /// index in the table.
5662 /// If an entry corresponding to major and minor is not found, the function
5663 /// returns the index of the major,minor pair immediately lower than the
5664 /// requested value, ie it will return -1 if the pair is lower than
5665 /// the first entry in the index.
5666 ///
5667 /// See also GetEntryNumberWithIndex
5668 
5669 Long64_t TTree::GetEntryNumberWithBestIndex(Long64_t major, Long64_t minor) const
5670 {
5671  if (!fTreeIndex) {
5672  return -1;
5673  }
5674  return fTreeIndex->GetEntryNumberWithBestIndex(major, minor);
5675 }
5676 
5677 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5678 /// Return entry number corresponding to major and minor number.
5679 /// Note that this function returns only the entry number, not the data
5680 /// To read the data corresponding to an entry number, use TTree::GetEntryWithIndex
5681 /// the BuildIndex function has created a table of Long64_t* of sorted values
5682 /// corresponding to val = major<<31 + minor;
5683 /// The function performs binary search in this sorted table.
5684 /// If it finds a pair that matches val, it returns directly the
5685 /// index in the table, otherwise it returns -1.
5686 ///
5687 /// See also GetEntryNumberWithBestIndex
5688 
5689 Long64_t TTree::GetEntryNumberWithIndex(Long64_t major, Long64_t minor) const
5690 {
5691  if (!fTreeIndex) {
5692  return -1;
5693  }
5694  return fTreeIndex->GetEntryNumberWithIndex(major, minor);
5695 }
5696 
5697 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5698 /// Read entry corresponding to major and minor number.
5699 ///
5700 /// The function returns the total number of bytes read.
5701 /// If the Tree has friend trees, the corresponding entry with
5702 /// the index values (major,minor) is read. Note that the master Tree
5703 /// and its friend may have different entry serial numbers corresponding
5704 /// to (major,minor).
5705 
5706 Int_t TTree::GetEntryWithIndex(Int_t major, Int_t minor)
5707 {
5708  // We already have been visited while recursively looking
5709  // through the friends tree, let's return.
5710  if (kGetEntryWithIndex & fFriendLockStatus) {
5711  return 0;
5712  }
5713  Long64_t serial = GetEntryNumberWithIndex(major, minor);
5714  if (serial < 0) {
5715  return -1;
5716  }
5717  // create cache if wanted
5718  if (fCacheDoAutoInit)
5719  SetCacheSizeAux();
5720 
5721  Int_t i;
5722  Int_t nbytes = 0;
5723  fReadEntry = serial;
5724  TBranch *branch;
5725  Int_t nbranches = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
5726  Int_t nb;
5727  for (i = 0; i < nbranches; ++i) {
5728  branch = (TBranch*)fBranches.UncheckedAt(i);
5729  nb = branch->GetEntry(serial);
5730  if (nb < 0) return nb;
5731  nbytes += nb;
5732  }
5733  // GetEntry in list of friends
5734  if (!fFriends) return nbytes;
5735  TFriendLock lock(this,kGetEntryWithIndex);
5736  TIter nextf(fFriends);
5737  TFriendElement* fe = 0;
5738  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*) nextf())) {
5739  TTree *t = fe->GetTree();
5740  if (t) {
5741  serial = t->GetEntryNumberWithIndex(major,minor);
5742  if (serial <0) return -nbytes;
5743  nb = t->GetEntry(serial);
5744  if (nb < 0) return nb;
5745  nbytes += nb;
5746  }
5747  }
5748  return nbytes;
5749 }
5750 
5751 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5752 /// Return a pointer to the TTree friend whose name or alias is 'friendname.
5753 
5754 TTree* TTree::GetFriend(const char *friendname) const
5755 {
5756 
5757  // We already have been visited while recursively
5758  // looking through the friends tree, let's return.
5759  if (kGetFriend & fFriendLockStatus) {
5760  return 0;
5761  }
5762  if (!fFriends) {
5763  return 0;
5764  }
5765  TFriendLock lock(const_cast<TTree*>(this), kGetFriend);
5766  TIter nextf(fFriends);
5767  TFriendElement* fe = 0;
5768  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*) nextf())) {
5769  if (strcmp(friendname,fe->GetName())==0
5770  || strcmp(friendname,fe->GetTreeName())==0) {
5771  return fe->GetTree();
5772  }
5773  }
5774  // After looking at the first level,
5775  // let's see if it is a friend of friends.
5776  nextf.Reset();
5777  fe = 0;
5778  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*) nextf())) {
5779  TTree *res = fe->GetTree()->GetFriend(friendname);
5780  if (res) {
5781  return res;
5782  }
5783  }
5784  return 0;
5785 }
5786 
5787 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5788 /// If the 'tree' is a friend, this method returns its alias name.
5789 ///
5790 /// This alias is an alternate name for the tree.
5791 ///
5792 /// It can be used in conjunction with a branch or leaf name in a TTreeFormula,
5793 /// to specify in which particular tree the branch or leaf can be found if
5794 /// the friend trees have branches or leaves with the same name as the master
5795 /// tree.
5796 ///
5797 /// It can also be used in conjunction with an alias created using
5798 /// TTree::SetAlias in a TTreeFormula, e.g.:
5799 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
5800 /// maintree->Draw("treealias.fPx - treealias.myAlias");
5801 /// ~~~
5802 /// where fPx is a branch of the friend tree aliased as 'treealias' and 'myAlias'
5803 /// was created using TTree::SetAlias on the friend tree.
5804 ///
5805 /// However, note that 'treealias.myAlias' will be expanded literally,
5806 /// without remembering that it comes from the aliased friend and thus
5807 /// the branch name might not be disambiguated properly, which means
5808 /// that you may not be able to take advantage of this feature.
5809 ///
5810 
5811 const char* TTree::GetFriendAlias(TTree* tree) const
5812 {
5813  if ((tree == this) || (tree == GetTree())) {
5814  return 0;
5815  }
5816 
5817  // We already have been visited while recursively
5818  // looking through the friends tree, let's return.
5819  if (kGetFriendAlias & fFriendLockStatus) {
5820  return 0;
5821  }
5822  if (!fFriends) {
5823  return 0;
5824  }
5825  TFriendLock lock(const_cast<TTree*>(this), kGetFriendAlias);
5826  TIter nextf(fFriends);
5827  TFriendElement* fe = 0;
5828  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*) nextf())) {
5829  TTree* t = fe->GetTree();
5830  if (t == tree) {
5831  return fe->GetName();
5832  }
5833  // Case of a chain:
5834  if (t && t->GetTree() == tree) {
5835  return fe->GetName();
5836  }
5837  }
5838  // After looking at the first level,
5839  // let's see if it is a friend of friends.
5840  nextf.Reset();
5841  fe = 0;
5842  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*) nextf())) {
5843  const char* res = fe->GetTree()->GetFriendAlias(tree);
5844  if (res) {
5845  return res;
5846  }
5847  }
5848  return 0;
5849 }

5852 /// Returns the current set of IO settings
5853 ROOT::TIOFeatures TTree::GetIOFeatures() const
5854 {
5855  return fIOFeatures;
5856 }

5858 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5859 /// Creates a new iterator that will go through all the leaves on the tree itself and its friend.
5860 
5861 TIterator* TTree::GetIteratorOnAllLeaves(Bool_t dir)
5862 {
5863  return new TTreeFriendLeafIter(this, dir);

5865 
5866 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5867 /// Return pointer to the 1st Leaf named name in any Branch of this
5868 /// Tree or any branch in the list of friend trees.
5869 ///
5870 /// The leaf name can contain the name of a friend tree with the
5871 /// syntax: friend_dir_and_tree.full_leaf_name
5872 /// the friend_dir_and_tree can be of the form:
5873 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
5874 /// TDirectoryName/TreeName
5875 /// ~~~
5876 
5877 TLeaf* TTree::GetLeafImpl(const char* branchname, const char *leafname)
5878 {
5879  TLeaf *leaf = 0;
5880  if (branchname) {
5881  TBranch *branch = FindBranch(branchname);
5882  if (branch) {
5883  leaf = branch->GetLeaf(leafname);
5884  if (leaf) {
5885  return leaf;
5886  }
5887  }
5888  }
5889  TIter nextl(GetListOfLeaves());
5890  while ((leaf = (TLeaf*)nextl())) {
5891  if (strcmp(leaf->GetName(),leafname)) continue;
5892  if (branchname) {
5893  UInt_t nbch = strlen(branchname);
5894  TBranch *br = leaf->GetBranch();
5895  const char* brname = br->GetName();
5896  TBranch *mother = br->GetMother();
5897  if (strncmp(brname,branchname,nbch)) {
5898  if (mother != br) {
5899  const char *mothername = mother->GetName();
5900  UInt_t motherlen = strlen(mothername);
5901  if (nbch > motherlen && strncmp(mothername,branchname,motherlen)==0 && (mothername[motherlen-1]=='.' || branchname[motherlen]=='.')) {
5902  // The left part of the requested name match the name of the mother, let's see if the right part match the name of the branch.
5903  if (strncmp(brname,branchname+motherlen+1,nbch-motherlen-1)) {
5904  // No it does not
5905  continue;
5906  } // else we have match so we can proceed.
5907  } else {
5908  // no match
5909  continue;
5910  }
5911  } else {
5912  continue;
5913  }
5914  }
5915  // The start of the branch name is identical to the content
5916  // of 'aname' before the first '/'.
5917  // Let's make sure that it is not longer (we are trying
5918  // to avoid having jet2/value match the branch jet23
5919  if ((strlen(brname) > nbch) && (brname[nbch] != '.') && (brname[nbch] != '[')) {
5920  continue;
5921  }
5922  }
5923  return leaf;
5924  }
5925  if (!fFriends) return 0;
5926  TFriendLock lock(this,kGetLeaf);
5927  TIter next(fFriends);
5928  TFriendElement *fe;
5929  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*)next())) {
5930  TTree *t = fe->GetTree();
5931  if (t) {
5932  leaf = t->GetLeaf(leafname);
5933  if (leaf) return leaf;
5934  }
5935  }
5936 
5937  //second pass in the list of friends when the leaf name
5938  //is prefixed by the tree name
5939  TString strippedArg;
5940  next.Reset();
5941  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*)next())) {
5942  TTree *t = fe->GetTree();
5943  if (t==0) continue;
5944  char *subname = (char*)strstr(leafname,fe->GetName());
5945  if (subname != leafname) continue;
5946  Int_t l = strlen(fe->GetName());
5947  subname += l;
5948  if (*subname != '.') continue;
5949  subname++;
5950  strippedArg += subname;
5951  leaf = t->GetLeaf(branchname,subname);
5952  if (leaf) return leaf;
5953  }
5954  return 0;
5955 }
5956 
5957 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5958 /// Return pointer to the 1st Leaf named name in any Branch of this
5959 /// Tree or any branch in the list of friend trees.
5960 ///
5961 /// The leaf name can contain the name of a friend tree with the
5962 /// syntax: friend_dir_and_tree.full_leaf_name
5963 /// the friend_dir_and_tree can be of the form:
5964 ///
5965 /// TDirectoryName/TreeName
5966 
5967 TLeaf* TTree::GetLeaf(const char* branchname, const char *leafname)
5968 {
5969  if (leafname == 0) return 0;
5970 
5971  // We already have been visited while recursively looking
5972  // through the friends tree, let return
5973  if (kGetLeaf & fFriendLockStatus) {
5974  return 0;
5975  }
5976 
5977  return GetLeafImpl(branchname,leafname);
5978 }
5979 
5980 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
5981 /// Return pointer to first leaf named \param[name] in any branch of this
5982 /// tree or its friend trees.
5983 ///
5984 /// \param[name] may be in the form 'branch/leaf'
5985 ///
5986 
5987 TLeaf* TTree::GetLeaf(const char *name)
5988 {
5989  // Return nullptr if name is invalid or if we have
5990  // already been visited while searching friend trees
5991  if (!name || (kGetLeaf & fFriendLockStatus))
5992  return nullptr;
5993 
5994  std::string path(name);
5995  const auto sep = path.find_last_of("/");
5996  if (sep != std::string::npos)
5997  return GetLeafImpl(path.substr(0, sep).c_str(), name+sep+1);
5998 
5999  return GetLeafImpl(nullptr, name);
6000 }

6002 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6003 /// Return maximum of column with name columname.
6004 /// if the Tree has an associated TEventList or TEntryList, the maximum
6005 /// is computed for the entries in this list.
6006 
6007 Double_t TTree::GetMaximum(const char* columname)
6008 {
6009  TLeaf* leaf = this->GetLeaf(columname);
6010  if (!leaf) {
6011  return 0;
6012  }
6013 
6014  // create cache if wanted
6015  if (fCacheDoAutoInit)
6016  SetCacheSizeAux();
6017 
6018  TBranch* branch = leaf->GetBranch();
6019  Double_t cmax = -DBL_MAX;
6020  for (Long64_t i = 0; i < fEntries; ++i) {
6021  Long64_t entryNumber = this->GetEntryNumber(i);
6022  if (entryNumber < 0) break;
6023  branch->GetEntry(entryNumber);
6024  for (Int_t j = 0; j < leaf->GetLen(); ++j) {
6025  Double_t val = leaf->GetValue(j);
6026  if (val > cmax) {
6027  cmax = val;
6028  }
6029  }
6030  }
6031  return cmax;
6032 }

6042 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6043 /// Return minimum of column with name columname.
6044 /// if the Tree has an associated TEventList or TEntryList, the minimum
6045 /// is computed for the entries in this list.
6046 
6047 Double_t TTree::GetMinimum(const char* columname)
6048 {
6049  TLeaf* leaf = this->GetLeaf(columname);
6050  if (!leaf) {
6051  return 0;
6052  }
6053 
6054  // create cache if wanted
6055  if (fCacheDoAutoInit)
6056  SetCacheSizeAux();
6057 
6058  TBranch* branch = leaf->GetBranch();
6059  Double_t cmin = DBL_MAX;
6060  for (Long64_t i = 0; i < fEntries; ++i) {
6061  Long64_t entryNumber = this->GetEntryNumber(i);
6062  if (entryNumber < 0) break;
6063  branch->GetEntry(entryNumber);
6064  for (Int_t j = 0;j < leaf->GetLen(); ++j) {
6065  Double_t val = leaf->GetValue(j);
6066  if (val < cmin) {
6067  cmin = val;
6068  }
6069  }
6070  }
6071  return cmin;
6072 }

6137 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6138 /// Appends the cluster range information stored in 'fromtree' to this tree,
6139 /// including the value of fAutoFlush.
6140 ///
6141 /// This is used when doing a fast cloning (by TTreeCloner).
6142 /// See also fAutoFlush and fAutoSave if needed.
6143 
6144 void TTree::ImportClusterRanges(TTree *fromtree)
6145 {
6146  Long64_t autoflush = fromtree->GetAutoFlush();
6147  if (fromtree->fNClusterRange == 0 && fromtree->fAutoFlush == fAutoFlush) {
6148  // nothing to do
6149  } else if (fNClusterRange || fromtree->fNClusterRange) {
6150  Int_t newsize = fNClusterRange + 1 + fromtree->fNClusterRange;
6151  if (newsize > fMaxClusterRange) {
6152  if (fMaxClusterRange) {
6153  fClusterRangeEnd = (Long64_t*)TStorage::ReAlloc(fClusterRangeEnd,
6154  newsize*sizeof(Long64_t),fMaxClusterRange*sizeof(Long64_t));
6155  fClusterSize = (Long64_t*)TStorage::ReAlloc(fClusterSize,
6156  newsize*sizeof(Long64_t),fMaxClusterRange*sizeof(Long64_t));
6157  fMaxClusterRange = newsize;
6158  } else {
6159  fMaxClusterRange = newsize;
6160  fClusterRangeEnd = new Long64_t[fMaxClusterRange];
6161  fClusterSize = new Long64_t[fMaxClusterRange];
6162  }
6163  }
6164  if (fEntries) {
6165  fClusterRangeEnd[fNClusterRange] = fEntries - 1;
6166  fClusterSize[fNClusterRange] = fAutoFlush<0 ? 0 : fAutoFlush;
6167  ++fNClusterRange;
6168  }
6169  for (Int_t i = 0 ; i < fromtree->fNClusterRange; ++i) {
6170  fClusterRangeEnd[fNClusterRange] = fEntries + fromtree->fClusterRangeEnd[i];
6171  fClusterSize[fNClusterRange] = fromtree->fClusterSize[i];
6172  ++fNClusterRange;
6173  }
6174  fAutoFlush = autoflush;
6175  } else {
6176  SetAutoFlush( autoflush );
6177  }
6178  Long64_t autosave = GetAutoSave();
6179  if (autoflush > 0 && autosave > 0) {
6180  SetAutoSave( autoflush*(autosave/autoflush) );
6181  }
6182 }
6183 
6184 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6185 /// Keep a maximum of fMaxEntries in memory.
6186 
6187 void TTree::KeepCircular()
6188 {
6189  Int_t nb = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
6190  Long64_t maxEntries = fMaxEntries - (fMaxEntries / 10);
6191  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nb; ++i) {
6192  TBranch* branch = (TBranch*) fBranches.UncheckedAt(i);
6193  branch->KeepCircular(maxEntries);
6194  }
6195  if (fNClusterRange) {
6196  Long64_t entriesOffset = fEntries - maxEntries;
6197  Int_t oldsize = fNClusterRange;
6198  for(Int_t i = 0, j = 0; j < oldsize; ++j) {
6199  if (fClusterRangeEnd[j] > entriesOffset) {
6200  fClusterRangeEnd[i] = fClusterRangeEnd[j] - entriesOffset;
6201  ++i;
6202  } else {
6203  --fNClusterRange;
6204  }
6205  }
6206  }
6207  fEntries = maxEntries;
6208  fReadEntry = -1;
6209 }
6210 
6211 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6212 /// Read in memory all baskets from all branches up to the limit of maxmemory bytes.
6213 ///
6214 /// If maxmemory is non null and positive SetMaxVirtualSize is called
6215 /// with this value. Default for maxmemory is 2000000000 (2 Gigabytes).
6216 /// The function returns the total number of baskets read into memory
6217 /// if negative an error occurred while loading the branches.
6218 /// This method may be called to force branch baskets in memory
6219 /// when random access to branch entries is required.
6220 /// If random access to only a few branches is required, you should
6221 /// call directly TBranch::LoadBaskets.
6222 
6223 Int_t TTree::LoadBaskets(Long64_t maxmemory)
6224 {
6225  if (maxmemory > 0) SetMaxVirtualSize(maxmemory);
6226 
6227  TIter next(GetListOfLeaves());
6228  TLeaf *leaf;
6229  Int_t nimported = 0;
6230  while ((leaf=(TLeaf*)next())) {
6231  nimported += leaf->GetBranch()->LoadBaskets();//break;
6232  }
6233  return nimported;
6234 }
6235 
6236 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6237 /// Set current entry.
6238 ///
6239 /// Returns -2 if entry does not exist (just as TChain::LoadTree()).
6240 /// Returns -6 if an error occours in the notification callback (just as TChain::LoadTree()).
6241 ///
6242 /// Note: This function is overloaded in TChain.
6243 ///
6244 
6245 Long64_t TTree::LoadTree(Long64_t entry)
6246 {
6247  // We already have been visited while recursively looking
6248  // through the friends tree, let return
6249  if (kLoadTree & fFriendLockStatus) {
6250  // We need to return a negative value to avoid a circular list of friend
6251  // to think that there is always an entry somewhere in the list.
6252  return -1;
6253  }
6254 
6255  // create cache if wanted
6256  if (fCacheDoAutoInit && entry >=0)
6257  SetCacheSizeAux();
6258 
6259  if (fNotify) {
6260  if (fReadEntry < 0) {
6261  fNotify->Notify();
6262  }
6263  }
6264  fReadEntry = entry;
6265 
6266  Bool_t friendHasEntry = kFALSE;
6267  if (fFriends) {
6268  // Set current entry in friends as well.
6269  //
6270  // An alternative would move this code to each of the
6271  // functions calling LoadTree (and to overload a few more).
6272  Bool_t needUpdate = kFALSE;
6273  {
6274  // This scope is need to insure the lock is released at the right time
6275  TIter nextf(fFriends);
6276  TFriendLock lock(this, kLoadTree);
6277  TFriendElement* fe = 0;
6278  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*) nextf())) {
6279  if (fe->TestBit(TFriendElement::kFromChain)) {
6280  // This friend element was added by the chain that owns this
6281  // tree, the chain will deal with loading the correct entry.
6282  continue;
6283  }
6284  TTree* friendTree = fe->GetTree();
6285  if (friendTree == 0) {
6286  // Somehow we failed to retrieve the friend TTree.
6287  } else if (friendTree->IsA() == TTree::Class()) {
6288  // Friend is actually a tree.
6289  if (friendTree->LoadTreeFriend(entry, this) >= 0) {
6290  friendHasEntry = kTRUE;
6291  }
6292  } else {
6293  // Friend is actually a chain.
6294  // FIXME: This logic should be in the TChain override.
6295  Int_t oldNumber = friendTree->GetTreeNumber();
6296  if (friendTree->LoadTreeFriend(entry, this) >= 0) {
6297  friendHasEntry = kTRUE;
6298  }
6299  Int_t newNumber = friendTree->GetTreeNumber();
6300  if (oldNumber != newNumber) {
6301  // We can not just compare the tree pointers because they could be reused.
6302  // So we compare the tree number instead.
6303  needUpdate = kTRUE;
6304  }
6305  }
6306  } // for each friend
6307  }
6308  if (needUpdate) {
6309  //update list of leaves in all TTreeFormula of the TTreePlayer (if any)
6310  if (fPlayer) {
6311  fPlayer->UpdateFormulaLeaves();
6312  }
6313  //Notify user if requested
6314  if (fNotify) {
6315  if(!fNotify->Notify()) return -6;
6316  }
6317  }
6318  }
6319 
6320  if ((fReadEntry >= fEntries) && !friendHasEntry) {
6321  fReadEntry = -1;
6322  return -2;
6323  }
6324  return fReadEntry;
6325 }
6326 
6327 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6328 /// Load entry on behalf of our master tree, we may use an index.
6329 ///
6330 /// Called by LoadTree() when the masterTree looks for the entry
6331 /// number in a friend tree (us) corresponding to the passed entry
6332 /// number in the masterTree.
6333 ///
6334 /// If we have no index, our entry number and the masterTree entry
6335 /// number are the same.
6336 ///
6337 /// If we *do* have an index, we must find the (major, minor) value pair
6338 /// in masterTree to locate our corresponding entry.
6339 ///
6340 
6341 Long64_t TTree::LoadTreeFriend(Long64_t entry, TTree* masterTree)
6342 {
6343  if (!fTreeIndex) {
6344  return LoadTree(entry);
6345  }
6346  return LoadTree(fTreeIndex->GetEntryNumberFriend(masterTree));
6347 }
6348 
6349 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6350 /// Generate a skeleton analysis class for this tree.
6351 ///
6352 /// The following files are produced: classname.h and classname.C.
6353 /// If classname is 0, classname will be called "nameoftree".
6354 ///
6355 /// The generated code in classname.h includes the following:
6356 ///
6357 /// - Identification of the original tree and the input file name.
6358 /// - Definition of an analysis class (data members and member functions).
6359 /// - The following member functions:
6360 /// - constructor (by default opening the tree file),
6361 /// - GetEntry(Long64_t entry),
6362 /// - Init(TTree* tree) to initialize a new TTree,
6363 /// - Show(Long64_t entry) to read and dump entry.
6364 ///
6365 /// The generated code in classname.C includes only the main
6366 /// analysis function Loop.
6367 ///
6368 /// To use this function:
6369 ///
6370 /// - Open your tree file (eg: TFile f("myfile.root");)
6371 /// - T->MakeClass("MyClass");
6372 ///
6373 /// where T is the name of the TTree in file myfile.root,
6374 /// and MyClass.h, MyClass.C the name of the files created by this function.
6375 /// In a ROOT session, you can do:
6376 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6377 /// root > .L MyClass.C
6378 /// root > MyClass* t = new MyClass;
6379 /// root > t->GetEntry(12); // Fill data members of t with entry number 12.
6380 /// root > t->Show(); // Show values of entry 12.
6381 /// root > t->Show(16); // Read and show values of entry 16.
6382 /// root > t->Loop(); // Loop on all entries.
6383 /// ~~~
6384 /// NOTE: Do not use the code generated for a single TTree which is part
6385 /// of a TChain to process that entire TChain. The maximum dimensions
6386 /// calculated for arrays on the basis of a single TTree from the TChain
6387 /// might be (will be!) too small when processing all of the TTrees in
6388 /// the TChain. You must use myChain.MakeClass() to generate the code,
6389 /// not myTree.MakeClass(...).
6390 
6391 Int_t TTree::MakeClass(const char* classname, Option_t* option)
6392 {
6393  GetPlayer();
6394  if (!fPlayer) {
6395  return 0;
6396  }
6397  return fPlayer->MakeClass(classname, option);
6398 }
6399 
6400 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6401 /// Generate a skeleton function for this tree.
6402 ///
6403 /// The function code is written on filename.
6404 /// If filename is 0, filename will be called nameoftree.C
6405 ///
6406 /// The generated code includes the following:
6407 /// - Identification of the original Tree and Input file name,
6408 /// - Opening the Tree file,
6409 /// - Declaration of Tree variables,
6410 /// - Setting of branches addresses,
6411 /// - A skeleton for the entry loop.
6412 ///
6413 /// To use this function:
6414 ///
6415 /// - Open your Tree file (eg: TFile f("myfile.root");)
6416 /// - T->MakeCode("MyAnalysis.C");
6417 ///
6418 /// where T is the name of the TTree in file myfile.root
6419 /// and MyAnalysis.C the name of the file created by this function.
6420 ///
6421 /// NOTE: Since the implementation of this function, a new and better
6422 /// function TTree::MakeClass() has been developed.
6423 
6424 Int_t TTree::MakeCode(const char* filename)
6425 {
6426  Warning("MakeCode", "MakeCode is obsolete. Use MakeClass or MakeSelector instead");
6427 
6428  GetPlayer();
6429  if (!fPlayer) return 0;
6430  return fPlayer->MakeCode(filename);
6431 }
6432 
6433 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6434 /// Generate a skeleton analysis class for this Tree using TBranchProxy.
6435 ///
6436 /// TBranchProxy is the base of a class hierarchy implementing an
6437 /// indirect access to the content of the branches of a TTree.
6438 ///
6439 /// "proxyClassname" is expected to be of the form:
6440 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6441 /// [path/]fileprefix
6442 /// ~~~
6443 /// The skeleton will then be generated in the file:
6444 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6445 /// fileprefix.h
6446 /// ~~~
6447 /// located in the current directory or in 'path/' if it is specified.
6448 /// The class generated will be named 'fileprefix'
6449 ///
6450 /// "macrofilename" and optionally "cutfilename" are expected to point
6451 /// to source files which will be included by the generated skeleton.
6452 /// Method of the same name as the file(minus the extension and path)
6453 /// will be called by the generated skeleton's Process method as follow:
6454 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6455 /// [if (cutfilename())] htemp->Fill(macrofilename());
6456 /// ~~~
6457 /// "option" can be used select some of the optional features during
6458 /// the code generation. The possible options are:
6459 ///
6460 /// - nohist : indicates that the generated ProcessFill should not fill the histogram.
6461 ///
6462 /// 'maxUnrolling' controls how deep in the class hierarchy does the
6463 /// system 'unroll' classes that are not split. Unrolling a class
6464 /// allows direct access to its data members (this emulates the behavior
6465 /// of TTreeFormula).
6466 ///
6467 /// The main features of this skeleton are:
6468 ///
6469 /// * on-demand loading of branches
6470 /// * ability to use the 'branchname' as if it was a data member
6471 /// * protection against array out-of-bounds errors
6472 /// * ability to use the branch data as an object (when the user code is available)
6473 ///
6474 /// For example with Event.root, if
6475 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6476 /// Double_t somePx = fTracks.fPx[2];
6477 /// ~~~
6478 /// is executed by one of the method of the skeleton,
6479 /// somePx will updated with the current value of fPx of the 3rd track.
6480 ///
6481 /// Both macrofilename and the optional cutfilename are expected to be
6482 /// the name of source files which contain at least a free standing
6483 /// function with the signature:
6484 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6485 /// x_t macrofilename(); // i.e function with the same name as the file
6486 /// ~~~
6487 /// and
6488 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6489 /// y_t cutfilename(); // i.e function with the same name as the file
6490 /// ~~~
6491 /// x_t and y_t needs to be types that can convert respectively to a double
6492 /// and a bool (because the skeleton uses:
6493 ///
6494 /// if (cutfilename()) htemp->Fill(macrofilename());
6495 ///
6496 /// These two functions are run in a context such that the branch names are
6497 /// available as local variables of the correct (read-only) type.
6498 ///
6499 /// Note that if you use the same 'variable' twice, it is more efficient
6500 /// to 'cache' the value. For example:
6501 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6502 /// Int_t n = fEventNumber; // Read fEventNumber
6503 /// if (n<10 || n>10) { ... }
6504 /// ~~~
6505 /// is more efficient than
6506 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6507 /// if (fEventNumber<10 || fEventNumber>10)
6508 /// ~~~
6509 /// Also, optionally, the generated selector will also call methods named
6510 /// macrofilename_methodname in each of 6 main selector methods if the method
6511 /// macrofilename_methodname exist (Where macrofilename is stripped of its
6512 /// extension).
6513 ///
6514 /// Concretely, with the script named h1analysisProxy.C,
6515 ///
6516 /// - The method calls the method (if it exist)
6517 /// - Begin -> void h1analysisProxy_Begin(TTree*);
6518 /// - SlaveBegin -> void h1analysisProxy_SlaveBegin(TTree*);
6519 /// - Notify -> Bool_t h1analysisProxy_Notify();
6520 /// - Process -> Bool_t h1analysisProxy_Process(Long64_t);
6521 /// - SlaveTerminate -> void h1analysisProxy_SlaveTerminate();
6522 /// - Terminate -> void h1analysisProxy_Terminate();
6523 ///
6524 /// If a file name macrofilename.h (or .hh, .hpp, .hxx, .hPP, .hXX) exist
6525 /// it is included before the declaration of the proxy class. This can
6526 /// be used in particular to insure that the include files needed by
6527 /// the macro file are properly loaded.
6528 ///
6529 /// The default histogram is accessible via the variable named 'htemp'.
6530 ///
6531 /// If the library of the classes describing the data in the branch is
6532 /// loaded, the skeleton will add the needed `include` statements and
6533 /// give the ability to access the object stored in the branches.
6534 ///
6535 /// To draw px using the file hsimple.root (generated by the
6536 /// hsimple.C tutorial), we need a file named hsimple.cxx:
6537 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6538 /// double hsimple() {
6539 /// return px;
6540 /// }
6541 /// ~~~
6542 /// MakeProxy can then be used indirectly via the TTree::Draw interface
6543 /// as follow:
6544 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6545 /// new TFile("hsimple.root")
6546 /// ntuple->Draw("hsimple.cxx");
6547 /// ~~~
6548 /// A more complete example is available in the tutorials directory:
6549 /// h1analysisProxy.cxx , h1analysProxy.h and h1analysisProxyCut.C
6550 /// which reimplement the selector found in h1analysis.C
6551 
6552 Int_t TTree::MakeProxy(const char* proxyClassname, const char* macrofilename, const char* cutfilename, const char* option, Int_t maxUnrolling)
6553 {
6554  GetPlayer();
6555  if (!fPlayer) return 0;
6556  return fPlayer->MakeProxy(proxyClassname,macrofilename,cutfilename,option,maxUnrolling);
6557 }
6558 
6559 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6560 /// Generate skeleton selector class for this tree.
6561 ///
6562 /// The following files are produced: selector.h and selector.C.
6563 /// If selector is 0, the selector will be called "nameoftree".
6564 /// The option can be used to specify the branches that will have a data member.
6565 /// - If option is "=legacy", a pre-ROOT6 selector will be generated (data
6566 /// members and branch pointers instead of TTreeReaders).
6567 /// - If option is empty, readers will be generated for each leaf.
6568 /// - If option is "@", readers will be generated for the topmost branches.
6569 /// - Individual branches can also be picked by their name:
6570 /// - "X" generates readers for leaves of X.
6571 /// - "@X" generates a reader for X as a whole.
6572 /// - "@X;Y" generates a reader for X as a whole and also readers for the
6573 /// leaves of Y.
6574 /// - For further examples see the figure below.
6575 ///
6576 /// \image html ttree_makeselector_option_examples.png
6577 ///
6578 /// The generated code in selector.h includes the following:
6579 /// - Identification of the original Tree and Input file name
6580 /// - Definition of selector class (data and functions)
6581 /// - The following class functions:
6582 /// - constructor and destructor
6583 /// - void Begin(TTree *tree)
6584 /// - void SlaveBegin(TTree *tree)
6585 /// - void Init(TTree *tree)
6586 /// - Bool_t Notify()
6587 /// - Bool_t Process(Long64_t entry)
6588 /// - void Terminate()
6589 /// - void SlaveTerminate()
6590 ///
6591 /// The class selector derives from TSelector.
6592 /// The generated code in selector.C includes empty functions defined above.
6593 ///
6594 /// To use this function:
6595 ///
6596 /// - connect your Tree file (eg: `TFile f("myfile.root");`)
6597 /// - `T->MakeSelector("myselect");`
6598 ///
6599 /// where T is the name of the Tree in file myfile.root
6600 /// and myselect.h, myselect.C the name of the files created by this function.
6601 /// In a ROOT session, you can do:
6602 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6603 /// root > T->Process("myselect.C")
6604 /// ~~~
6605 
6606 Int_t TTree::MakeSelector(const char* selector, Option_t* option)
6607 {
6608  TString opt(option);
6609  if(opt.EqualTo("=legacy", TString::ECaseCompare::kIgnoreCase)) {
6610  return MakeClass(selector, "selector");
6611  } else {
6612  GetPlayer();
6613  if (!fPlayer) return 0;
6614  return fPlayer->MakeReader(selector, option);
6615  }
6616 }

6618 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6619 /// Check if adding nbytes to memory we are still below MaxVirtualsize.
6620 
6621 Bool_t TTree::MemoryFull(Int_t nbytes)
6622 {
6623  if ((fTotalBuffers + nbytes) < fMaxVirtualSize) {
6624  return kFALSE;
6625  }
6626  return kTRUE;
6627 }
6628 
6629 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6630 /// Static function merging the trees in the TList into a new tree.
6631 ///
6632 /// Trees in the list can be memory or disk-resident trees.
6633 /// The new tree is created in the current directory (memory if gROOT).
6634 
6635 TTree* TTree::MergeTrees(TList* li, Option_t* options)
6636 {
6637  if (!li) return 0;
6638  TIter next(li);
6639  TTree *newtree = 0;
6640  TObject *obj;
6641 
6642  while ((obj=next())) {
6643  if (!obj->InheritsFrom(TTree::Class())) continue;
6644  TTree *tree = (TTree*)obj;
6645  Long64_t nentries = tree->GetEntries();
6646  if (nentries == 0) continue;
6647  if (!newtree) {
6648  newtree = (TTree*)tree->CloneTree();
6649  if (!newtree) continue;
6650 
6651  // Once the cloning is done, separate the trees,
6652  // to avoid as many side-effects as possible
6653  // The list of clones is guaranteed to exist since we
6654  // just cloned the tree.
6655  tree->GetListOfClones()->Remove(newtree);
6656  tree->ResetBranchAddresses();
6657  newtree->ResetBranchAddresses();
6658  continue;
6659  }
6660 
6661  newtree->CopyAddresses(tree);
6662 
6663  newtree->CopyEntries(tree,-1,options);
6664 
6665  tree->ResetBranchAddresses(); // Disconnect from new tree.
6666  }
6667  if (newtree && newtree->GetTreeIndex()) {
6668  newtree->GetTreeIndex()->Append(0,kFALSE); // Force the sorting
6669  }
6670  return newtree;
6671 }
6672 
6673 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6674 /// Merge the trees in the TList into this tree.
6675 ///
6676 /// Returns the total number of entries in the merged tree.
6677 
6678 Long64_t TTree::Merge(TCollection* li, Option_t *options)
6679 {
6680  if (!li) return 0;
6681  Long64_t storeAutoSave = fAutoSave;
6682  // Disable the autosave as the TFileMerge keeps a list of key and deleting the underlying
6683  // key would invalidate its iteration (or require costly measure to not use the deleted keys).
6684  // Also since this is part of a merging operation, the output file is not as precious as in
6685  // the general case since the input file should still be around.
6686  fAutoSave = 0;
6687  TIter next(li);
6688  TTree *tree;
6689  while ((tree = (TTree*)next())) {
6690  if (tree==this) continue;
6691  if (!tree->InheritsFrom(TTree::Class())) {
6692  Error("Add","Attempt to add object of class: %s to a %s", tree->ClassName(), ClassName());
6693  fAutoSave = storeAutoSave;
6694  return -1;
6695  }
6696 
6697  Long64_t nentries = tree->GetEntries();
6698  if (nentries == 0) continue;
6699 
6700  CopyAddresses(tree);
6701 
6702  CopyEntries(tree,-1,options);
6703 
6704  tree->ResetBranchAddresses();
6705  }
6706  fAutoSave = storeAutoSave;
6707  return GetEntries();
6708 }
6709 
6710 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6711 /// Merge the trees in the TList into this tree.
6712 /// If info->fIsFirst is true, first we clone this TTree info the directory
6713 /// info->fOutputDirectory and then overlay the new TTree information onto
6714 /// this TTree object (so that this TTree object is now the appropriate to
6715 /// use for further merging).
6716 ///
6717 /// Returns the total number of entries in the merged tree.
6718 
6719 Long64_t TTree::Merge(TCollection* li, TFileMergeInfo *info)
6720 {
6721  const char *options = info ? info->fOptions.Data() : "";
6722  if (info && info->fIsFirst && info->fOutputDirectory && info->fOutputDirectory->GetFile() != GetCurrentFile()) {
6723  TDirectory::TContext ctxt(info->fOutputDirectory);
6724  TIOFeatures saved_features = fIOFeatures;
6725  if (info->fIOFeatures) {
6726  fIOFeatures = *(info->fIOFeatures);
6727  }
6728  TTree *newtree = CloneTree(-1, options);
6729  fIOFeatures = saved_features;
6730  if (newtree) {
6731  newtree->Write();
6732  delete newtree;
6733  }
6734  // Make sure things are really written out to disk before attempting any reading.
6735  info->fOutputDirectory->GetFile()->Flush();
6736  info->fOutputDirectory->ReadTObject(this,this->GetName());
6737  }
6738  if (!li) return 0;
6739  Long64_t storeAutoSave = fAutoSave;
6740  // Disable the autosave as the TFileMerge keeps a list of key and deleting the underlying
6741  // key would invalidate its iteration (or require costly measure to not use the deleted keys).
6742  // Also since this is part of a merging operation, the output file is not as precious as in
6743  // the general case since the input file should still be around.
6744  fAutoSave = 0;
6745  TIter next(li);
6746  TTree *tree;
6747  while ((tree = (TTree*)next())) {
6748  if (tree==this) continue;
6749  if (!tree->InheritsFrom(TTree::Class())) {
6750  Error("Add","Attempt to add object of class: %s to a %s", tree->ClassName(), ClassName());
6751  fAutoSave = storeAutoSave;
6752  return -1;
6753  }
6754  // Copy MakeClass status.
6755  tree->SetMakeClass(fMakeClass);
6756 
6757  // Copy branch addresses.
6758  CopyAddresses(tree);
6759 
6760  CopyEntries(tree,-1,options);
6761 
6762  tree->ResetBranchAddresses();
6763  }
6764  fAutoSave = storeAutoSave;
6765  return GetEntries();
6766 }

6768 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6769 /// Move a cache from a file to the current file in dir.
6770 /// if src is null no operation is done, if dir is null or there is no
6771 /// current file the cache is deleted.
6772 
6773 void TTree::MoveReadCache(TFile *src, TDirectory *dir)
6774 {
6775  if (!src) return;
6776  TFile *dst = (dir && dir != gROOT) ? dir->GetFile() : 0;
6777  if (src == dst) return;
6778 
6779  TTreeCache *pf = GetReadCache(src);
6780  if (dst) {
6781  src->SetCacheRead(0,this);
6782  dst->SetCacheRead(pf, this);
6783  } else {
6784  if (pf) {
6785  pf->WaitFinishPrefetch();
6786  }
6787  src->SetCacheRead(0,this);
6788  delete pf;
6789  }
6790 }

6792 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6793 /// Function called when loading a new class library.
6794 
6795 Bool_t TTree::Notify()
6796 {
6797  TIter next(GetListOfLeaves());
6798  TLeaf* leaf = 0;
6799  while ((leaf = (TLeaf*) next())) {
6800  leaf->Notify();
6801  leaf->GetBranch()->Notify();
6802  }
6803  return kTRUE;
6804 }
6805 
6806 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6807 /// This function may be called after having filled some entries in a Tree.
6808 /// Using the information in the existing branch buffers, it will reassign
6809 /// new branch buffer sizes to optimize time and memory.
6810 ///
6811 /// The function computes the best values for branch buffer sizes such that
6812 /// the total buffer sizes is less than maxMemory and nearby entries written
6813 /// at the same time.
6814 /// In case the branch compression factor for the data written so far is less
6815 /// than compMin, the compression is disabled.
6816 ///
6817 /// if option ="d" an analysis report is printed.
6818 
6819 void TTree::OptimizeBaskets(ULong64_t maxMemory, Float_t minComp, Option_t *option)
6820 {
6821  //Flush existing baskets if the file is writable
6822  if (this->GetDirectory()->IsWritable()) this->FlushBasketsImpl();
6823 
6824  TString opt( option );
6825  opt.ToLower();
6826  Bool_t pDebug = opt.Contains("d");
6827  TObjArray *leaves = this->GetListOfLeaves();
6828  Int_t nleaves = leaves->GetEntries();
6829  Double_t treeSize = (Double_t)this->GetTotBytes();
6830 
6831  if (nleaves == 0 || treeSize == 0) {
6832  // We're being called too early, we really have nothing to do ...
6833  return;
6834  }
6835  Double_t aveSize = treeSize/nleaves;
6836  UInt_t bmin = 512;
6837  UInt_t bmax = 256000;
6838  Double_t memFactor = 1;
6839  Int_t i, oldMemsize,newMemsize,oldBaskets,newBaskets;
6840  i = oldMemsize = newMemsize = oldBaskets = newBaskets = 0;
6841 
6842  //we make two passes
6843  //one pass to compute the relative branch buffer sizes
6844  //a second pass to compute the absolute values
6845  for (Int_t pass =0;pass<2;pass++) {
6846  oldMemsize = 0; //to count size of baskets in memory with old buffer size
6847  newMemsize = 0; //to count size of baskets in memory with new buffer size
6848  oldBaskets = 0; //to count number of baskets with old buffer size
6849  newBaskets = 0; //to count number of baskets with new buffer size
6850  for (i=0;i<nleaves;i++) {
6851  TLeaf *leaf = (TLeaf*)leaves->At(i);
6852  TBranch *branch = leaf->GetBranch();
6853  Double_t totBytes = (Double_t)branch->GetTotBytes();
6854  Double_t idealFactor = totBytes/aveSize;
6855  UInt_t sizeOfOneEntry;
6856  if (branch->GetEntries() == 0) {
6857  // There is no data, so let's make a guess ...
6858  sizeOfOneEntry = aveSize;
6859  } else {
6860  sizeOfOneEntry = 1+(UInt_t)(totBytes / (Double_t)branch->GetEntries());
6861  }
6862  Int_t oldBsize = branch->GetBasketSize();
6863  oldMemsize += oldBsize;
6864  oldBaskets += 1+Int_t(totBytes/oldBsize);
6865  Int_t nb = branch->GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries();
6866  if (nb > 0) {
6867  newBaskets += 1+Int_t(totBytes/oldBsize);
6868  continue;
6869  }
6870  Double_t bsize = oldBsize*idealFactor*memFactor; //bsize can be very large !
6871  if (bsize < 0) bsize = bmax;
6872  if (bsize > bmax) bsize = bmax;
6873  UInt_t newBsize = UInt_t(bsize);
6874  if (pass) { // only on the second pass so that it doesn't interfere with scaling
6875  // If there is an entry offset, it will be stored in the same buffer as the object data; hence,
6876  // we must bump up the size of the branch to account for this extra footprint.
6877  // If fAutoFlush is not set yet, let's assume that it is 'in the process of being set' to
6878  // the value of GetEntries().
6879  Long64_t clusterSize = (fAutoFlush > 0) ? fAutoFlush : branch->GetEntries();
6880  if (branch->GetEntryOffsetLen()) {
6881  newBsize = newBsize + (clusterSize * sizeof(Int_t) * 2);
6882  }
6883  // We used ATLAS fully-split xAOD for testing, which is a rather unbalanced TTree, 10K branches,
6884  // with 8K having baskets smaller than 512 bytes. To achieve good I/O performance ATLAS uses auto-flush 100,
6885  // resulting in the smallest baskets being ~300-400 bytes, so this change increases their memory by about 8k*150B =~ 1MB,
6886  // at the same time it significantly reduces the number of total baskets because it ensures that all 100 entries can be
6887  // stored in a single basket (the old optimization tended to make baskets too small). In a toy example with fixed sized
6888  // structures we found a factor of 2 fewer baskets needed in the new scheme.
6889  // rounds up, increases basket size to ensure all entries fit into single basket as intended
6890  newBsize = newBsize - newBsize%512 + 512;
6891  }
6892  if (newBsize < sizeOfOneEntry) newBsize = sizeOfOneEntry;
6893  if (newBsize < bmin) newBsize = bmin;
6894  if (newBsize > 10000000) newBsize = bmax;
6895  if (pass) {
6896  if (pDebug) Info("OptimizeBaskets", "Changing buffer size from %6d to %6d bytes for %s\n",oldBsize,newBsize,branch->GetName());
6897  branch->SetBasketSize(newBsize);
6898  }
6899  newMemsize += newBsize;
6900  // For this number to be somewhat accurate when newBsize is 'low'
6901  // we do not include any space for meta data in the requested size (newBsize) even-though SetBasketSize will
6902  // not let it be lower than 100+TBranch::fEntryOffsetLen.
6903  newBaskets += 1+Int_t(totBytes/newBsize);
6904  if (pass == 0) continue;
6905  //Reset the compression level in case the compression factor is small
6906  Double_t comp = 1;
6907  if (branch->GetZipBytes() > 0) comp = totBytes/Double_t(branch->GetZipBytes());
6908  if (comp > 1 && comp < minComp) {
6909  if (pDebug) Info("OptimizeBaskets", "Disabling compression for branch : %s\n",branch->GetName());
6910  branch->SetCompressionSettings(ROOT::RCompressionSetting::EAlgorithm::kUseGlobal);
6911  }
6912  }
6913  // coverity[divide_by_zero] newMemsize can not be zero as there is at least one leaf
6914  memFactor = Double_t(maxMemory)/Double_t(newMemsize);
6915  if (memFactor > 100) memFactor = 100;
6916  Double_t bmin_new = bmin*memFactor;
6917  Double_t bmax_new = bmax*memFactor;
6918  static const UInt_t hardmax = 1*1024*1024*1024; // Really, really never give more than 1Gb to a single buffer.
6919 
6920  // Really, really never go lower than 8 bytes (we use this number
6921  // so that the calculation of the number of basket is consistent
6922  // but in fact SetBasketSize will not let the size go below
6923  // TBranch::fEntryOffsetLen + (100 + strlen(branch->GetName())
6924  // (The 2nd part being a slight over estimate of the key length.
6925  static const UInt_t hardmin = 8;
6926  bmin = (bmin_new > hardmax) ? hardmax : ( bmin_new < hardmin ? hardmin : (UInt_t)bmin_new );
6927  bmax = (bmax_new > hardmax) ? bmin : (UInt_t)bmax_new;
6928  }
6929  if (pDebug) {
6930  Info("OptimizeBaskets", "oldMemsize = %d, newMemsize = %d\n",oldMemsize, newMemsize);
6931  Info("OptimizeBaskets", "oldBaskets = %d, newBaskets = %d\n",oldBaskets, newBaskets);
6932  }
6933 }
6934 
6935 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6936 /// Interface to the Principal Components Analysis class.
6937 ///
6938 /// Create an instance of TPrincipal
6939 ///
6940 /// Fill it with the selected variables
6941 ///
6942 /// - if option "n" is specified, the TPrincipal object is filled with
6943 /// normalized variables.
6944 /// - If option "p" is specified, compute the principal components
6945 /// - If option "p" and "d" print results of analysis
6946 /// - If option "p" and "h" generate standard histograms
6947 /// - If option "p" and "c" generate code of conversion functions
6948 /// - return a pointer to the TPrincipal object. It is the user responsibility
6949 /// - to delete this object.
6950 /// - The option default value is "np"
6951 ///
6952 /// see TTree::Draw for explanation of the other parameters.
6953 ///
6954 /// The created object is named "principal" and a reference to it
6955 /// is added to the list of specials Root objects.
6956 /// you can retrieve a pointer to the created object via:
6957 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
6958 /// TPrincipal *principal =
6959 /// (TPrincipal*)gROOT->GetListOfSpecials()->FindObject("principal");
6960 /// ~~~
6961 
6962 TPrincipal* TTree::Principal(const char* varexp, const char* selection, Option_t* option, Long64_t nentries, Long64_t firstentry)
6963 {
6964  GetPlayer();

6966  return fPlayer->Principal(varexp, selection, option, nentries, firstentry);
6967  }
6968  return 0;
6969 }
6970 
6971 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
6972 /// Print a summary of the tree contents.
6973 ///
6974 /// - If option contains "all" friend trees are also printed.
6975 /// - If option contains "toponly" only the top level branches are printed.
6976 /// - If option contains "clusters" information about the cluster of baskets is printed.
6977 ///
6978 /// Wildcarding can be used to print only a subset of the branches, e.g.,
6979 /// `T.Print("Elec*")` will print all branches with name starting with "Elec".
6980 
6981 void TTree::Print(Option_t* option) const
6982 {
6983  // We already have been visited while recursively looking
6984  // through the friends tree, let's return.
6985  if (kPrint & fFriendLockStatus) {
6986  return;
6987  }
6988  Int_t s = 0;
6989  Int_t skey = 0;
6990  if (fDirectory) {
6991  TKey* key = fDirectory->GetKey(GetName());
6992  if (key) {
6993  skey = key->GetKeylen();
6994  s = key->GetNbytes();
6995  }
6996  }
6997  Long64_t total = skey;
6998  Long64_t zipBytes = GetZipBytes();
6999  if (zipBytes > 0) {
7000  total += GetTotBytes();
7001  }
7002  TBufferFile b(TBuffer::kWrite, 10000);
7003  TTree::Class()->WriteBuffer(b, (TTree*) this);
7004  total += b.Length();
7005  Long64_t file = zipBytes + s;
7006  Float_t cx = 1;
7007  if (zipBytes) {
7008  cx = (GetTotBytes() + 0.00001) / zipBytes;
7009  }
7010  Printf("******************************************************************************");
7011  Printf("*Tree :%-10s: %-54s *", GetName(), GetTitle());
7012  Printf("*Entries : %8lld : Total = %15lld bytes File Size = %10lld *", fEntries, total, file);
7013  Printf("* : : Tree compression factor = %6.2f *", cx);
7014  Printf("******************************************************************************");
7015 
7016  // Avoid many check of option validity
7017  if (option == nullptr)
7018  option = "";
7019 
7020  if (strncmp(option,"clusters",strlen("clusters"))==0) {
7021  Printf("%-16s %-16s %-16s %5s",
7022  "Cluster Range #", "Entry Start", "Last Entry", "Size");
7023  Int_t index= 0;
7024  Long64_t clusterRangeStart = 0;
7025  if (fNClusterRange) {
7026  for( ; index < fNClusterRange; ++index) {
7027  Printf("%-16d %-16lld %-16lld %5lld",
7028  index, clusterRangeStart, fClusterRangeEnd[index], fClusterSize[index]);
7029  clusterRangeStart = fClusterRangeEnd[index] + 1;
7030  }
7031  }
7032  Printf("%-16d %-16lld %-16lld %5lld",
7033  index, clusterRangeStart, fEntries - 1, fAutoFlush);
7034  return;
7035  }
7036 
7037  Int_t nl = const_cast<TTree*>(this)->GetListOfLeaves()->GetEntries();
7038  Int_t l;
7039  TBranch* br = 0;
7040  TLeaf* leaf = 0;
7041  if (strstr(option, "toponly")) {
7042  Long64_t *count = new Long64_t[nl];
7043  Int_t keep =0;
7044  for (l=0;l<nl;l++) {
7045  leaf = (TLeaf *)const_cast<TTree*>(this)->GetListOfLeaves()->At(l);
7046  br = leaf->GetBranch();
7047  if (strchr(br->GetName(),'.')) {
7048  count[l] = -1;
7049  count[keep] += br->GetZipBytes();
7050  } else {
7051  keep = l;
7052  count[keep] = br->GetZipBytes();
7053  }
7054  }
7055  for (l=0;l<nl;l++) {
7056  if (count[l] < 0) continue;
7057  leaf = (TLeaf *)const_cast<TTree*>(this)->GetListOfLeaves()->At(l);
7058  br = leaf->GetBranch();
7059  Printf("branch: %-20s %9lld\n",br->GetName(),count[l]);
7060  }
7061  delete [] count;
7062  } else {
7063  TString reg = "*";
7064  if (strlen(option) && strchr(option,'*')) reg = option;
7065  TRegexp re(reg,kTRUE);
7066  TIter next(const_cast<TTree*>(this)->GetListOfBranches());
7067  TBranch::ResetCount();
7068  while ((br= (TBranch*)next())) {
7069  TString st = br->GetName();
7070  st.ReplaceAll("/","_");
7071  if (st.Index(re) == kNPOS) continue;
7072  br->Print(option);
7073  }
7074  }
7075 
7076  //print TRefTable (if one)
7077  if (fBranchRef) fBranchRef->Print(option);
7078 
7079  //print friends if option "all"
7080  if (!fFriends || !strstr(option,"all")) return;
7081  TIter nextf(fFriends);
7082  TFriendLock lock(const_cast<TTree*>(this),kPrint);
7083  TFriendElement *fr;
7084  while ((fr = (TFriendElement*)nextf())) {
7085  TTree * t = fr->GetTree();
7086  if (t) t->Print(option);
7087  }
7088 }

7090 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7091 /// Print statistics about the TreeCache for this tree.
7092 /// Like:
7093 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
7094 /// ******TreeCache statistics for file: cms2.root ******
7095 /// Reading 73921562 bytes in 716 transactions
7096 /// Average transaction = 103.242405 Kbytes
7097 /// Number of blocks in current cache: 202, total size : 6001193
7098 /// ~~~
7099 /// if option = "a" the list of blocks in the cache is printed
7100 
7101 void TTree::PrintCacheStats(Option_t* option) const
7102 {
7103  TFile *f = GetCurrentFile();
7104  if (!f) return;
7105  TTreeCache *tc = GetReadCache(f);
7106  if (tc) tc->Print(option);
7107 }
7108 
7109 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7110 /// Process this tree executing the TSelector code in the specified filename.
7111 /// The return value is -1 in case of error and TSelector::GetStatus() in
7112 /// in case of success.
7113 ///
7114 /// The code in filename is loaded (interpreted or compiled, see below),
7115 /// filename must contain a valid class implementation derived from TSelector,
7116 /// where TSelector has the following member functions:
7117 ///
7118 /// - `Begin()`: called every time a loop on the tree starts,
7119 /// a convenient place to create your histograms.
7120 /// - `SlaveBegin()`: called after Begin(), when on PROOF called only on the
7121 /// slave servers.
7122 /// - `Process()`: called for each event, in this function you decide what
7123 /// to read and fill your histograms.
7124 /// - `SlaveTerminate`: called at the end of the loop on the tree, when on PROOF
7125 /// called only on the slave servers.
7126 /// - `Terminate()`: called at the end of the loop on the tree,
7127 /// a convenient place to draw/fit your histograms.
7128 ///
7129 /// If filename is of the form file.C, the file will be interpreted.
7130 ///
7131 /// If filename is of the form file.C++, the file file.C will be compiled
7132 /// and dynamically loaded.
7133 ///
7134 /// If filename is of the form file.C+, the file file.C will be compiled
7135 /// and dynamically loaded. At next call, if file.C is older than file.o
7136 /// and file.so, the file.C is not compiled, only file.so is loaded.
7137 ///
7138 /// ## NOTE1
7139 ///
7140 /// It may be more interesting to invoke directly the other Process function
7141 /// accepting a TSelector* as argument.eg
7142 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
7143 /// MySelector *selector = (MySelector*)TSelector::GetSelector(filename);
7144 /// selector->CallSomeFunction(..);
7145 /// mytree.Process(selector,..);
7146 /// ~~~
7147 /// ## NOTE2
7148 //
7149 /// One should not call this function twice with the same selector file
7150 /// in the same script. If this is required, proceed as indicated in NOTE1,
7151 /// by getting a pointer to the corresponding TSelector,eg
7152 ///
7153 /// ### Workaround 1
7154 ///
7155 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
7156 /// void stubs1() {
7157 /// TSelector *selector = TSelector::GetSelector("h1test.C");
7158 /// TFile *f1 = new TFile("stubs_nood_le1.root");
7159 /// TTree *h1 = (TTree*)f1->Get("h1");
7160 /// h1->Process(selector);
7161 /// TFile *f2 = new TFile("stubs_nood_le1_coarse.root");
7162 /// TTree *h2 = (TTree*)f2->Get("h1");
7163 /// h2->Process(selector);
7164 /// }
7165 /// ~~~
7166 /// or use ACLIC to compile the selector
7167 ///
7168 /// ### Workaround 2
7169 ///
7170 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
7171 /// void stubs2() {
7172 /// TFile *f1 = new TFile("stubs_nood_le1.root");
7173 /// TTree *h1 = (TTree*)f1->Get("h1");
7174 /// h1->Process("h1test.C+");
7175 /// TFile *f2 = new TFile("stubs_nood_le1_coarse.root");
7176 /// TTree *h2 = (TTree*)f2->Get("h1");
7177 /// h2->Process("h1test.C+");
7178 /// }
7179 /// ~~~
7180 
7181 Long64_t TTree::Process(const char* filename, Option_t* option, Long64_t nentries, Long64_t firstentry)
7182 {
7183  GetPlayer();
7184  if (fPlayer) {
7185  return fPlayer->Process(filename, option, nentries, firstentry);
7186  }
7187  return -1;
7188 }
7189 
7190 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7191 /// Process this tree executing the code in the specified selector.
7192 /// The return value is -1 in case of error and TSelector::GetStatus() in
7193 /// in case of success.
7194 ///
7195 /// The TSelector class has the following member functions:
7196 ///
7197 /// - `Begin()`: called every time a loop on the tree starts,
7198 /// a convenient place to create your histograms.
7199 /// - `SlaveBegin()`: called after Begin(), when on PROOF called only on the
7200 /// slave servers.
7201 /// - `Process()`: called for each event, in this function you decide what
7202 /// to read and fill your histograms.
7203 /// - `SlaveTerminate`: called at the end of the loop on the tree, when on PROOF
7204 /// called only on the slave servers.
7205 /// - `Terminate()`: called at the end of the loop on the tree,
7206 /// a convenient place to draw/fit your histograms.
7207 ///
7208 /// If the Tree (Chain) has an associated EventList, the loop is on the nentries
7209 /// of the EventList, starting at firstentry, otherwise the loop is on the
7210 /// specified Tree entries.
7211 
7212 Long64_t TTree::Process(TSelector* selector, Option_t* option, Long64_t nentries, Long64_t firstentry)
7213 {
7214  GetPlayer();
7215  if (fPlayer) {
7216  return fPlayer->Process(selector, option, nentries, firstentry);
7217  }
7218  return -1;
7219 }

7221 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7222 /// Make a projection of a tree using selections.
7223 ///
7224 /// Depending on the value of varexp (described in Draw) a 1-D, 2-D, etc.,
7225 /// projection of the tree will be filled in histogram hname.
7226 /// Note that the dimension of hname must match with the dimension of varexp.
7227 ///
7228 
7229 Long64_t TTree::Project(const char* hname, const char* varexp, const char* selection, Option_t* option, Long64_t nentries, Long64_t firstentry)
7230 {
7231  TString var;
7232  var.Form("%s>>%s", varexp, hname);
7233  TString opt("goff");
7234  if (option) {
7235  opt.Form("%sgoff", option);
7236  }
7237  Long64_t nsel = Draw(var, selection, opt, nentries, firstentry);
7238  return nsel;
7239 }

7241 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7242 /// Loop over entries and return a TSQLResult object containing entries following selection.
7243 
7244 TSQLResult* TTree::Query(const char* varexp, const char* selection, Option_t* option, Long64_t nentries, Long64_t firstentry)
7245 {

7248  return fPlayer->Query(varexp, selection, option, nentries, firstentry);
7249  }
7250  return 0;

7252 
7253 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7254 /// Create or simply read branches from filename.
7255 ///
7256 /// if branchDescriptor = "" (default), it is assumed that the Tree descriptor
7257 /// is given in the first line of the file with a syntax like
7258 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
7259 /// A/D:Table[2]/F:Ntracks/I:astring/C
7260 /// ~~~
7261 /// otherwise branchDescriptor must be specified with the above syntax.
7262 ///
7263 /// - If the type of the first variable is not specified, it is assumed to be "/F"
7264 /// - If the type of any other variable is not specified, the type of the previous
7265 /// variable is assumed. eg
7266 /// - `x:y:z` (all variables are assumed of type "F"
7267 /// - `x/D:y:z` (all variables are of type "D"
7268 /// - `x:y/D:z` (x is type "F", y and z of type "D"
7269 ///
7270 /// delimiter allows for the use of another delimiter besides whitespace.
7271 /// This provides support for direct import of common data file formats
7272 /// like csv. If delimiter != ' ' and branchDescriptor == "", then the
7273 /// branch description is taken from the first line in the file, but
7274 /// delimiter is used for the branch names tokenization rather than ':'.
7275 /// Note however that if the values in the first line do not use the
7276 /// /[type] syntax, all variables are assumed to be of type "F".
7277 /// If the filename ends with extensions .csv or .CSV and a delimiter is
7278 /// not specified (besides ' '), the delimiter is automatically set to ','.
7279 ///
7280 /// Lines in the input file starting with "#" are ignored. Leading whitespace
7281 /// for each column data is skipped. Empty lines are skipped.
7282 ///
7283 /// A TBranch object is created for each variable in the expression.
7284 /// The total number of rows read from the file is returned.
7285 ///
7286 /// ## FILLING a TTree WITH MULTIPLE INPUT TEXT FILES
7287 ///
7288 /// To fill a TTree with multiple input text files, proceed as indicated above
7289 /// for the first input file and omit the second argument for subsequent calls
7290 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
7291 /// T.ReadFile("file1.dat","branch descriptor");
7292 /// T.ReadFile("file2.dat");
7293 /// ~~~
7294 
7295 Long64_t TTree::ReadFile(const char* filename, const char* branchDescriptor, char delimiter)
7296 {
7297  std::ifstream in;
7298  in.open(filename);
7299  if (!in.good()) {
7300  Error("ReadFile","Cannot open file: %s",filename);
7301  return 0;
7302  }
7303  const char* ext = strrchr(filename, '.');
7304  if(ext != NULL && ((strcmp(ext, ".csv") == 0) || (strcmp(ext, ".CSV") == 0)) && delimiter == ' ') {
7305  delimiter = ',';
7306  }
7307  return ReadStream(in, branchDescriptor, delimiter);
7308 }
7309 
7310 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7311 /// Determine which newline this file is using.
7312 /// Return '\\r' for Windows '\\r\\n' as that already terminates.
7313 
7314 char TTree::GetNewlineValue(std::istream &inputStream)
7315 {
7316  Long_t inPos = inputStream.tellg();
7317  char newline = '\n';
7318  while(1) {
7319  char c = 0;
7320  inputStream.get(c);
7321  if(!inputStream.good()) {
7322  Error("ReadStream","Error reading stream: no newline found.");
7323  return 0;
7324  }
7325  if(c == newline) break;
7326  if(c == '\r') {
7327  newline = '\r';
7328  break;
7329  }
7330  }
7331  inputStream.clear();
7332  inputStream.seekg(inPos);
7333  return newline;
7334 }
7335 
7336 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7337 /// Create or simply read branches from an input stream.
7338 ///
7339 /// See reference information for TTree::ReadFile
7340 
7341 Long64_t TTree::ReadStream(std::istream& inputStream, const char *branchDescriptor, char delimiter)
7342 {
7343  char newline = 0;
7344  std::stringstream ss;
7345  std::istream *inTemp;
7346  Long_t inPos = inputStream.tellg();
7347  if (!inputStream.good()) {
7348  Error("ReadStream","Error reading stream");
7349  return 0;
7350  }
7351  if (inPos == -1) {
7352  ss << std::cin.rdbuf();
7353  newline = GetNewlineValue(ss);
7354  inTemp = &ss;
7355  } else {
7356  newline = GetNewlineValue(inputStream);
7357  inTemp = &inputStream;
7358  }
7359  std::istream& in = *inTemp;
7360  Long64_t nlines = 0;
7361 
7362  TBranch *branch = 0;
7363  Int_t nbranches = fBranches.GetEntries();
7364  if (nbranches == 0) {
7365  char *bdname = new char[4000];
7366  char *bd = new char[100000];
7367  Int_t nch = 0;
7368  if (branchDescriptor) nch = strlen(branchDescriptor);
7369  // branch Descriptor is null, read its definition from the first line in the file
7370  if (!nch) {
7371  do {
7372  in.getline(bd, 100000, newline);
7373  if (!in.good()) {
7374  delete [] bdname;
7375  delete [] bd;
7376  Error("ReadStream","Error reading stream");
7377  return 0;
7378  }
7379  char *cursor = bd;
7380  while( isspace(*cursor) && *cursor != '\n' && *cursor != '\0') {
7381  ++cursor;
7382  }
7383  if (*cursor != '#' && *cursor != '\n' && *cursor != '\0') {
7384  break;
7385  }
7386  } while (true);
7387  ++nlines;
7388  nch = strlen(bd);
7389  } else {
7390  strlcpy(bd,branchDescriptor,100000);
7391  }
7392 
7393  //parse the branch descriptor and create a branch for each element
7394  //separated by ":"
7395  void *address = &bd[90000];
7396  char *bdcur = bd;
7397  TString desc="", olddesc="F";
7398  char bdelim = ':';
7399  if(delimiter != ' ') {
7400  bdelim = delimiter;
7401  if (strchr(bdcur,bdelim)==0 && strchr(bdcur,':') != 0) {
7402  // revert to the default
7403  bdelim = ':';
7404  }
7405  }
7406  while (bdcur) {
7407  char *colon = strchr(bdcur,bdelim);
7408  if (colon) *colon = 0;
7409  strlcpy(bdname,bdcur,4000);
7410  char *slash = strchr(bdname,'/');
7411  if (slash) {
7412  *slash = 0;
7413  desc = bdcur;
7414  olddesc = slash+1;
7415  } else {
7416  desc.Form("%s/%s",bdname,olddesc.Data());
7417  }
7418  char *bracket = strchr(bdname,'[');
7419  if (bracket) {
7420  *bracket = 0;
7421  }
7422  branch = new TBranch(this,bdname,address,desc.Data(),32000);
7423  if (branch->IsZombie()) {
7424  delete branch;
7425  Warning("ReadStream","Illegal branch definition: %s",bdcur);
7426  } else {
7427  fBranches.Add(branch);
7428  branch->SetAddress(0);
7429  }
7430  if (!colon)break;
7431  bdcur = colon+1;
7432  }
7433  delete [] bdname;
7434  delete [] bd;
7435  }
7436 
7437  nbranches = fBranches.GetEntries();
7438 
7439  if (gDebug > 1) {
7440  Info("ReadStream", "Will use branches:");
7441  for (int i = 0 ; i < nbranches; ++i) {
7442  TBranch* br = (TBranch*) fBranches.At(i);
7443  Info("ReadStream", " %s: %s [%s]", br->GetName(),
7444  br->GetTitle(), br->GetListOfLeaves()->At(0)->IsA()->GetName());
7445  }
7446  if (gDebug > 3) {
7447  Info("ReadStream", "Dumping read tokens, format:");
7448  Info("ReadStream", "LLLLL:BBB:gfbe:GFBE:T");
7449  Info("ReadStream", " L: line number");
7450  Info("ReadStream", " B: branch number");
7451  Info("ReadStream", " gfbe: good / fail / bad / eof of token");
7452  Info("ReadStream", " GFBE: good / fail / bad / eof of file");
7453  Info("ReadStream", " T: Token being read");
7454  }
7455  }
7456 
7457  //loop on all lines in the file
7458  Long64_t nGoodLines = 0;
7459  std::string line;
7460  const char sDelimBuf[2] = { delimiter, 0 };
7461  const char* sDelim = sDelimBuf;
7462  if (delimiter == ' ') {
7463  // ' ' really means whitespace
7464  sDelim = "[ \t]";
7465  }
7466  while(in.good()) {
7467  if (newline == '\r' && in.peek() == '\n') {
7468  // Windows, skip '\n':
7469  in.get();
7470  }
7471  std::getline(in, line, newline);
7472  ++nlines;
7473 
7474  TString sLine(line);
7475  sLine = sLine.Strip(TString::kLeading); // skip leading whitespace
7476  if (sLine.IsNull()) {
7477  if (gDebug > 2) {
7478  Info("ReadStream", "Skipping empty line number %lld", nlines);
7479  }
7480  continue; // silently skip empty lines
7481  }
7482  if (sLine[0] == '#') {
7483  if (gDebug > 2) {
7484  Info("ReadStream", "Skipping comment line number %lld: '%s'",
7485  nlines, line.c_str());
7486  }
7487  continue;
7488  }
7489  if (gDebug > 2) {
7490  Info("ReadStream", "Parsing line number %lld: '%s'",
7491  nlines, line.c_str());
7492  }
7493 
7494  // Loop on branches and read the branch values into their buffer
7495  branch = 0;
7496  TString tok; // one column's data
7497  TString leafData; // leaf data, possibly multiple tokens for e.g. /I[2]
7498  std::stringstream sToken; // string stream feeding leafData into leaves
7499  Ssiz_t pos = 0;
7500  Int_t iBranch = 0;
7501  Bool_t goodLine = kTRUE; // whether the row can be filled into the tree
7502  Int_t remainingLeafLen = 0; // remaining columns for the current leaf
7503  while (goodLine && iBranch < nbranches
7504  && sLine.Tokenize(tok, pos, sDelim)) {
7505  tok = tok.Strip(TString::kLeading); // skip leading whitespace
7506  if (tok.IsNull() && delimiter == ' ') {
7507  // 1 2 should not be interpreted as 1,,,2 but 1, 2.
7508  // Thus continue until we have a non-empty token.
7509  continue;
7510  }
7511 
7512  if (!remainingLeafLen) {
7513  // next branch!
7514  branch = (TBranch*)fBranches.At(iBranch);
7515  }
7516  TLeaf *leaf = (TLeaf*)branch->GetListOfLeaves()->At(0);
7517  if (!remainingLeafLen) {
7518  remainingLeafLen = leaf->GetLen();
7519  if (leaf->GetMaximum() > 0) {
7520  // This is a dynamic leaf length, i.e. most likely a TLeafC's
7521  // string size. This still translates into one token:
7522  remainingLeafLen = 1;
7523  }
7524 
7525  leafData = tok;
7526  } else {
7527  // append token to laf data:
7528  leafData += " ";
7529  leafData += tok;
7530  }
7531  --remainingLeafLen;
7532  if (remainingLeafLen) {
7533  // need more columns for this branch:
7534  continue;
7535  }
7536  ++iBranch;
7537 
7538  // initialize stringstream with token
7539  sToken.clear();
7540  sToken.seekp(0, std::ios_base::beg);
7541  sToken.str(leafData.Data());
7542  sToken.seekg(0, std::ios_base::beg);
7543  leaf->ReadValue(sToken, 0 /* 0 = "all" */);
7544  if (gDebug > 3) {
7545  Info("ReadStream", "%5lld:%3d:%d%d%d%d:%d%d%d%d:%s",
7546  nlines, iBranch,
7547  (int)sToken.good(), (int)sToken.fail(),
7548  (int)sToken.bad(), (int)sToken.eof(),
7549  (int)in.good(), (int)in.fail(),
7550  (int)in.bad(), (int)in.eof(),
7551  sToken.str().c_str());
7552  }
7553 
7554  // Error handling
7555  if (sToken.bad()) {
7556  // How could that happen for a stringstream?
7557  Warning("ReadStream",
7558  "Buffer error while reading data for branch %s on line %lld",
7559  branch->GetName(), nlines);
7560  } else if (!sToken.eof()) {
7561  if (sToken.fail()) {
7562  Warning("ReadStream",
7563  "Couldn't read formatted data in \"%s\" for branch %s on line %lld; ignoring line",
7564  tok.Data(), branch->GetName(), nlines);
7565  goodLine = kFALSE;
7566  } else {
7567  std::string remainder;
7568  std::getline(sToken, remainder, newline);
7569  if (!remainder.empty()) {
7570  Warning("ReadStream",
7571  "Ignoring trailing \"%s\" while reading data for branch %s on line %lld",
7572  remainder.c_str(), branch->GetName(), nlines);
7573  }
7574  }
7575  }
7576  } // tokenizer loop
7577 
7578  if (iBranch < nbranches) {
7579  Warning("ReadStream",
7580  "Read too few columns (%d < %d) in line %lld; ignoring line",
7581  iBranch, nbranches, nlines);
7582  goodLine = kFALSE;
7583  } else if (pos != kNPOS) {
7584  sLine = sLine.Strip(TString::kTrailing);
7585  if (pos < sLine.Length()) {
7586  Warning("ReadStream",
7587  "Ignoring trailing \"%s\" while reading line %lld",
7588  sLine.Data() + pos - 1 /* also print delimiter */,
7589  nlines);
7590  }
7591  }
7592 
7593  //we are now ready to fill the tree
7594  if (goodLine) {
7595  Fill();
7596  ++nGoodLines;
7597  }
7598  }
7599 
7600  return nGoodLines;
7601 }
7602 
7603 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7604 /// Make sure that obj (which is being deleted or will soon be) is no
7605 /// longer referenced by this TTree.
7606 
7607 void TTree::RecursiveRemove(TObject *obj)
7608 {
7609  if (obj == fEventList) {
7610  fEventList = 0;
7611  }
7612  if (obj == fEntryList) {
7613  fEntryList = 0;
7614  }
7615  if (fUserInfo) {
7616  fUserInfo->RecursiveRemove(obj);
7617  }
7618  if (fPlayer == obj) {
7619  fPlayer = 0;
7620  }
7621  if (fTreeIndex == obj) {
7622  fTreeIndex = 0;
7623  }
7624  if (fAliases) {
7625  fAliases->RecursiveRemove(obj);
7626  }
7627  if (fFriends) {
7628  fFriends->RecursiveRemove(obj);
7629  }
7630 }
7631 
7632 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7633 /// Refresh contents of this tree and its branches from the current status on disk.
7634 ///
7635 /// One can call this function in case the tree file is being
7636 /// updated by another process.
7637 
7638 void TTree::Refresh()
7639 {
7640  if (!fDirectory->GetFile()) {
7641  return;
7642  }
7643  fDirectory->ReadKeys();
7644  fDirectory->Remove(this);
7645  TTree* tree; fDirectory->GetObject(GetName(),tree);
7646  if (!tree) {
7647  return;
7648  }
7649  //copy info from tree header into this Tree
7650  fEntries = 0;
7651  fNClusterRange = 0;
7652  ImportClusterRanges(tree);
7653 
7654  fAutoSave = tree->fAutoSave;
7655  fEntries = tree->fEntries;
7656  fTotBytes = tree->GetTotBytes();
7657  fZipBytes = tree->GetZipBytes();
7658  fSavedBytes = tree->fSavedBytes;
7659  fTotalBuffers = tree->fTotalBuffers.load();
7660 
7661  //loop on all branches and update them
7662  Int_t nleaves = fLeaves.GetEntriesFast();
7663  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nleaves; i++) {
7664  TLeaf* leaf = (TLeaf*) fLeaves.UncheckedAt(i);
7665  TBranch* branch = (TBranch*) leaf->GetBranch();
7666  branch->Refresh(tree->GetBranch(branch->GetName()));
7667  }
7668  fDirectory->Remove(tree);
7669  fDirectory->Append(this);
7670  delete tree;
7671  tree = 0;
7672 }
7673 
7674 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7675 /// Remove a friend from the list of friends.
7676 
7677 void TTree::RemoveFriend(TTree* oldFriend)
7678 {
7679  // We already have been visited while recursively looking
7680  // through the friends tree, let return
7681  if (kRemoveFriend & fFriendLockStatus) {
7682  return;
7683  }
7684  if (!fFriends) {
7685  return;
7686  }
7687  TFriendLock lock(this, kRemoveFriend);
7688  TIter nextf(fFriends);
7689  TFriendElement* fe = 0;
7690  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*) nextf())) {
7691  TTree* friend_t = fe->GetTree();
7692  if (friend_t == oldFriend) {
7693  fFriends->Remove(fe);
7694  delete fe;
7695  fe = 0;
7696  }
7697  }
7698 }

7700 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7701 /// Reset baskets, buffers and entries count in all branches and leaves.
7702 
7703 void TTree::Reset(Option_t* option)
7704 {
7705  fNotify = 0;
7706  fEntries = 0;
7707  fNClusterRange = 0;
7708  fTotBytes = 0;
7709  fZipBytes = 0;
7710  fFlushedBytes = 0;
7711  fSavedBytes = 0;
7712  fTotalBuffers = 0;
7713  fChainOffset = 0;
7714  fReadEntry = -1;
7715 
7716  delete fTreeIndex;
7717  fTreeIndex = 0;
7718 
7719  Int_t nb = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
7720  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nb; ++i) {
7721  TBranch* branch = (TBranch*) fBranches.UncheckedAt(i);
7722  branch->Reset(option);
7723  }
7724 
7725  if (fBranchRef) {
7726  fBranchRef->Reset();
7727  }
7728 }
