7802 
7803 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7804 /// Set a tree variable alias.
7805 ///
7806 /// Set an alias for an expression/formula based on the tree 'variables'.
7807 ///
7808 /// The content of 'aliasName' can be used in TTreeFormula (i.e. TTree::Draw,
7809 /// TTree::Scan, TTreeViewer) and will be evaluated as the content of
7810 /// 'aliasFormula'.
7811 ///
7812 /// If the content of 'aliasFormula' only contains symbol names, periods and
7813 /// array index specification (for example event.fTracks[3]), then
7814 /// the content of 'aliasName' can be used as the start of symbol.
7815 ///
7816 /// If the alias 'aliasName' already existed, it is replaced by the new
7817 /// value.
7818 ///
7819 /// When being used, the alias can be preceded by an eventual 'Friend Alias'
7820 /// (see TTree::GetFriendAlias)
7821 ///
7822 /// Return true if it was added properly.
7823 ///
7824 /// For example:
7825 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
7826 /// tree->SetAlias("x1","(tdc1[1]-tdc1[0])/49");
7827 /// tree->SetAlias("y1","(tdc1[3]-tdc1[2])/47");
7828 /// tree->SetAlias("x2","(tdc2[1]-tdc2[0])/49");
7829 /// tree->SetAlias("y2","(tdc2[3]-tdc2[2])/47");
7830 /// tree->Draw("y2-y1:x2-x1");
7831 ///
7832 /// tree->SetAlias("theGoodTrack","event.fTracks[3]");
7833 /// tree->Draw("theGoodTrack.fPx"); // same as "event.fTracks[3].fPx"
7834 /// ~~~
7835 
7836 Bool_t TTree::SetAlias(const char* aliasName, const char* aliasFormula)
7837 {
7838  if (!aliasName || !aliasFormula) {
7839  return kFALSE;
7840  }
7841  if (!aliasName[0] || !aliasFormula[0]) {
7842  return kFALSE;
7843  }
7844  if (!fAliases) {
7845  fAliases = new TList;
7846  } else {
7847  TNamed* oldHolder = (TNamed*) fAliases->FindObject(aliasName);
7848  if (oldHolder) {
7849  oldHolder->SetTitle(aliasFormula);
7850  return kTRUE;
7851  }
7852  }
7853  TNamed* holder = new TNamed(aliasName, aliasFormula);
7854  fAliases->Add(holder);
7855  return kTRUE;
7856 }
7857 
7858 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7859 /// This function may be called at the start of a program to change
7860 /// the default value for fAutoFlush.
7861 ///
7862 /// ### CASE 1 : autof > 0
7863 ///
7864 /// autof is the number of consecutive entries after which TTree::Fill will
7865 /// flush all branch buffers to disk.
7866 ///
7867 /// ### CASE 2 : autof < 0
7868 ///
7869 /// When filling the Tree the branch buffers will be flushed to disk when
7870 /// more than autof bytes have been written to the file. At the first FlushBaskets
7871 /// TTree::Fill will replace fAutoFlush by the current value of fEntries.
7872 ///
7873 /// Calling this function with autof<0 is interesting when it is hard to estimate
7874 /// the size of one entry. This value is also independent of the Tree.
7875 ///
7876 /// The Tree is initialized with fAutoFlush=-30000000, ie that, by default,
7877 /// the first AutoFlush will be done when 30 MBytes of data are written to the file.
7878 ///
7879 /// ### CASE 3 : autof = 0
7880 ///
7881 /// The AutoFlush mechanism is disabled.
7882 ///
7883 /// Flushing the buffers at regular intervals optimize the location of
7884 /// consecutive entries on the disk by creating clusters of baskets.
7885 ///
7886 /// A cluster of baskets is a set of baskets that contains all
7887 /// the data for a (consecutive) set of entries and that is stored
7888 /// consecutively on the disk. When reading all the branches, this
7889 /// is the minimum set of baskets that the TTreeCache will read.
7890 
7891 void TTree::SetAutoFlush(Long64_t autof /* = -30000000 */ )
7892 {
7893  // Implementation note:
7894  //
7895  // A positive value of autoflush determines the size (in number of entries) of
7896  // a cluster of baskets.
7897  //
7898  // If the value of autoflush is changed over time (this happens in
7899  // particular when the TTree results from fast merging many trees),
7900  // we record the values of fAutoFlush in the data members:
7901  // fClusterRangeEnd and fClusterSize.
7902  // In the code we refer to a range of entries where the size of the
7903  // cluster of baskets is the same (i.e the value of AutoFlush was
7904  // constant) is called a ClusterRange.
7905  //
7906  // The 2 arrays (fClusterRangeEnd and fClusterSize) have fNClusterRange
7907  // active (used) values and have fMaxClusterRange allocated entries.
7908  //
7909  // fClusterRangeEnd contains the last entries number of a cluster range.
7910  // In particular this means that the 'next' cluster starts at fClusterRangeEnd[]+1
7911  // fClusterSize contains the size in number of entries of all the cluster
7912  // within the given range.
7913  // The last range (and the only one if fNClusterRange is zero) start at
7914  // fNClusterRange[fNClusterRange-1]+1 and ends at the end of the TTree. The
7915  // size of the cluster in this range is given by the value of fAutoFlush.
7916  //
7917  // For example printing the beginning and end of each the ranges can be done by:
7918  //
7919  // Printf("%-16s %-16s %-16s %5s",
7920  // "Cluster Range #", "Entry Start", "Last Entry", "Size");
7921  // Int_t index= 0;
7922  // Long64_t clusterRangeStart = 0;
7923  // if (fNClusterRange) {
7924  // for( ; index < fNClusterRange; ++index) {
7925  // Printf("%-16d %-16lld %-16lld %5lld",
7926  // index, clusterRangeStart, fClusterRangeEnd[index], fClusterSize[index]);
7927  // clusterRangeStart = fClusterRangeEnd[index] + 1;
7928  // }
7929  // }
7930  // Printf("%-16d %-16lld %-16lld %5lld",
7931  // index, prevEntry, fEntries - 1, fAutoFlush);
7932  //
7933 
7934  // Note: We store the entry number corresponding to the end of the cluster
7935  // rather than its start in order to avoid using the array if the cluster
7936  // size never varies (If there is only one value of AutoFlush for the whole TTree).
7937 
7938  if( fAutoFlush != autof) {
7939  if ((fAutoFlush > 0 || autof > 0) && fFlushedBytes) {
7940  // The mechanism was already enabled, let's record the previous
7941  // cluster if needed.
7942  MarkEventCluster();
7943  }
7944  fAutoFlush = autof;
7945  }
7946 }
7947 
7948 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7949 /// Mark the previous event as being at the end of the event cluster.
7950 ///
7951 /// So, if fEntries is set to 10 (and this is the first cluster) when MarkEventCluster
7952 /// is called, then the first cluster has 9 events.
7953 void TTree::MarkEventCluster()
7954 {
7955  if (!fEntries) return;
7956 
7957  if ( (fNClusterRange+1) > fMaxClusterRange ) {
7958  if (fMaxClusterRange) {
7959  // Resize arrays to hold a larger event cluster.
7960  Int_t newsize = TMath::Max(10,Int_t(2*fMaxClusterRange));
7961  fClusterRangeEnd = (Long64_t*)TStorage::ReAlloc(fClusterRangeEnd,
7962  newsize*sizeof(Long64_t),fMaxClusterRange*sizeof(Long64_t));
7963  fClusterSize = (Long64_t*)TStorage::ReAlloc(fClusterSize,
7964  newsize*sizeof(Long64_t),fMaxClusterRange*sizeof(Long64_t));
7965  fMaxClusterRange = newsize;
7966  } else {
7967  // Cluster ranges have never been initialized; create them now.
7968  fMaxClusterRange = 2;
7969  fClusterRangeEnd = new Long64_t[fMaxClusterRange];
7970  fClusterSize = new Long64_t[fMaxClusterRange];
7971  }
7972  }
7973  fClusterRangeEnd[fNClusterRange] = fEntries - 1;
7974  // If we are auto-flushing, then the cluster size is the same as the current auto-flush setting.
7975  if (fAutoFlush > 0) {
7976  // Even if the user triggers MarkEventRange prior to fAutoFlush being present, the TClusterIterator
7977  // will appropriately go to the next event range.
7978  fClusterSize[fNClusterRange] = fAutoFlush;
7979  // Otherwise, assume there is one cluster per event range (e.g., user is manually controlling the flush).
7980  } else if (fNClusterRange == 0) {
7981  fClusterSize[fNClusterRange] = fEntries;
7982  } else {
7983  fClusterSize[fNClusterRange] = fClusterRangeEnd[fNClusterRange] - fClusterRangeEnd[fNClusterRange-1];
7984  }
7985  ++fNClusterRange;
7986 }
7987 
7988 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
7989 /// This function may be called at the start of a program to change
7990 /// the default value for fAutoSave (and for SetAutoSave) is -300000000, ie 300 MBytes.
7991 /// When filling the Tree the branch buffers as well as the Tree header
7992 /// will be flushed to disk when the watermark is reached.
7993 /// If fAutoSave is positive the watermark is reached when a multiple of fAutoSave
7994 /// entries have been written.
7995 /// If fAutoSave is negative the watermark is reached when -fAutoSave bytes
7996 /// have been written to the file.
7997 /// In case of a program crash, it will be possible to recover the data in the Tree
7998 /// up to the last AutoSave point.
7999 
8000 void TTree::SetAutoSave(Long64_t autos)
8001 {
8002  fAutoSave = autos;
8003 }
8004 
8005 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8006 /// Set a branch's basket size.
8007 ///
8008 /// bname is the name of a branch.
8009 ///
8010 /// - if bname="*", apply to all branches.
8011 /// - if bname="xxx*", apply to all branches with name starting with xxx
8012 ///
8013 /// see TRegexp for wildcarding options
8014 /// buffsize = branc basket size
8015 
8016 void TTree::SetBasketSize(const char* bname, Int_t buffsize)
8017 {
8018  Int_t nleaves = fLeaves.GetEntriesFast();
8019  TRegexp re(bname, kTRUE);
8020  Int_t nb = 0;
8021  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nleaves; i++) {
8022  TLeaf* leaf = (TLeaf*) fLeaves.UncheckedAt(i);
8023  TBranch* branch = (TBranch*) leaf->GetBranch();
8024  TString s = branch->GetName();
8025  if (strcmp(bname, branch->GetName()) && (s.Index(re) == kNPOS)) {
8026  continue;
8027  }
8028  nb++;
8029  branch->SetBasketSize(buffsize);
8030  }
8031  if (!nb) {
8032  Error("SetBasketSize", "unknown branch -> '%s'", bname);
8033  }
8034 }
8035 
8036 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8037 /// Change branch address, dealing with clone trees properly.
8038 /// See TTree::CheckBranchAddressType for the semantic of the return value.
8039 ///
8040 /// Note: See the comments in TBranchElement::SetAddress() for the
8041 /// meaning of the addr parameter and the object ownership policy.
8042 
8043 Int_t TTree::SetBranchAddress(const char* bname, void* addr, TBranch** ptr)
8044 {
8045  TBranch* branch = GetBranch(bname);
8046  if (!branch) {
8047  if (ptr) *ptr = 0;
8048  Error("SetBranchAddress", "unknown branch -> %s", bname);
8049  return kMissingBranch;
8050  }
8051  return SetBranchAddressImp(branch,addr,ptr);
8052 }
8053 
8054 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8055 /// Verify the validity of the type of addr before calling SetBranchAddress.
8056 /// See TTree::CheckBranchAddressType for the semantic of the return value.
8057 ///
8058 /// Note: See the comments in TBranchElement::SetAddress() for the
8059 /// meaning of the addr parameter and the object ownership policy.
8060 
8061 Int_t TTree::SetBranchAddress(const char* bname, void* addr, TClass* ptrClass, EDataType datatype, Bool_t isptr)
8062 {
8063  return SetBranchAddress(bname, addr, 0, ptrClass, datatype, isptr);
8064 }
8065 
8066 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8067 /// Verify the validity of the type of addr before calling SetBranchAddress.
8068 /// See TTree::CheckBranchAddressType for the semantic of the return value.
8069 ///
8070 /// Note: See the comments in TBranchElement::SetAddress() for the
8071 /// meaning of the addr parameter and the object ownership policy.
8072 
8073 Int_t TTree::SetBranchAddress(const char* bname, void* addr, TBranch** ptr, TClass* ptrClass, EDataType datatype, Bool_t isptr)
8074 {
8075  TBranch* branch = GetBranch(bname);
8076  if (!branch) {
8077  if (ptr) *ptr = 0;
8078  Error("SetBranchAddress", "unknown branch -> %s", bname);
8079  return kMissingBranch;
8080  }
8081 
8082  Int_t res = CheckBranchAddressType(branch, ptrClass, datatype, isptr);
8083  // This will set the value of *ptr to branch.
8084  if (res >= 0) {
8085  // The check succeeded.
8086  SetBranchAddressImp(branch,addr,ptr);
8087  } else {
8088  if (ptr) *ptr = 0;
8089  }
8090  return res;
8091 }
8092 
8093 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8094 /// Change branch address, dealing with clone trees properly.
8095 /// See TTree::CheckBranchAddressType for the semantic of the return value.
8096 ///
8097 /// Note: See the comments in TBranchElement::SetAddress() for the
8098 /// meaning of the addr parameter and the object ownership policy.
8099 
8100 Int_t TTree::SetBranchAddressImp(TBranch *branch, void* addr, TBranch** ptr)
8101 {
8102  if (ptr) {
8103  *ptr = branch;
8104  }
8105  if (fClones) {
8106  void* oldAddr = branch->GetAddress();
8107  TIter next(fClones);
8108  TTree* clone = 0;
8109  const char *bname = branch->GetName();
8110  while ((clone = (TTree*) next())) {
8111  TBranch* cloneBr = clone->GetBranch(bname);
8112  if (cloneBr && (cloneBr->GetAddress() == oldAddr)) {
8113  cloneBr->SetAddress(addr);
8114  }
8115  }
8116  }
8117  branch->SetAddress(addr);
8118  return kVoidPtr;
8119 }
8120 
8121 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8122 /// Set branch status to Process or DoNotProcess.
8123 ///
8124 /// When reading a Tree, by default, all branches are read.
8125 /// One can speed up considerably the analysis phase by activating
8126 /// only the branches that hold variables involved in a query.
8127 ///
8128 /// bname is the name of a branch.
8129 ///
8130 /// - if bname="*", apply to all branches.
8131 /// - if bname="xxx*", apply to all branches with name starting with xxx
8132 ///
8133 /// see TRegexp for wildcarding options
8134 ///
8135 /// - status = 1 branch will be processed
8136 /// - = 0 branch will not be processed
8137 ///
8138 /// Example:
8139 ///
8140 /// Assume a tree T with sub-branches a,b,c,d,e,f,g,etc..
8141 /// when doing T.GetEntry(i) all branches are read for entry i.
8142 /// to read only the branches c and e, one can do
8143 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
8144 /// T.SetBranchStatus("*",0); //disable all branches
8145 /// T.SetBranchStatus("c",1);
8146 /// T.setBranchStatus("e",1);
8147 /// T.GetEntry(i);
8148 /// ~~~
8149 /// bname is interpreted as a wildcarded TRegexp (see TRegexp::MakeWildcard).
8150 /// Thus, "a*b" or "a.*b" matches branches starting with "a" and ending with
8151 /// "b", but not any other branch with an "a" followed at some point by a
8152 /// "b". For this second behavior, use "*a*b*". Note that TRegExp does not
8153 /// support '|', and so you cannot select, e.g. track and shower branches
8154 /// with "track|shower".
8155 ///
8156 /// __WARNING! WARNING! WARNING!__
8157 ///
8158 /// SetBranchStatus is matching the branch based on match of the branch
8159 /// 'name' and not on the branch hierarchy! In order to be able to
8160 /// selectively enable a top level object that is 'split' you need to make
8161 /// sure the name of the top level branch is prefixed to the sub-branches'
8162 /// name (by adding a dot ('.') at the end of the Branch creation and use the
8163 /// corresponding bname.
8164 ///
8165 /// I.e If your Tree has been created in split mode with a parent branch "parent."
8166 /// (note the trailing dot).
8167 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
8168 /// T.SetBranchStatus("parent",1);
8169 /// ~~~
8170 /// will not activate the sub-branches of "parent". You should do:
8171 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
8172 /// T.SetBranchStatus("parent*",1);
8173 /// ~~~
8174 /// Without the trailing dot in the branch creation you have no choice but to
8175 /// call SetBranchStatus explicitly for each of the sub branches.
8176 ///
8177 /// An alternative to this function is to read directly and only
8178 /// the interesting branches. Example:
8179 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
8180 /// TBranch *brc = T.GetBranch("c");
8181 /// TBranch *bre = T.GetBranch("e");
8182 /// brc->GetEntry(i);
8183 /// bre->GetEntry(i);
8184 /// ~~~
8185 /// If found is not 0, the number of branch(es) found matching the regular
8186 /// expression is returned in *found AND the error message 'unknown branch'
8187 /// is suppressed.
8188 
8189 void TTree::SetBranchStatus(const char* bname, Bool_t status, UInt_t* found)
8190 {
8191  // We already have been visited while recursively looking
8192  // through the friends tree, let return
8193  if (kSetBranchStatus & fFriendLockStatus) {
8194  return;
8195  }
8196 
8197  if (0 == strcmp(bname, "")) {
8198  Error("SetBranchStatus", "Input regexp is an empty string: no match against branch names will be attempted.");
8199  return;
8200  }
8201 
8202  TBranch *branch, *bcount, *bson;
8203  TLeaf *leaf, *leafcount;
8204 
8205  Int_t i,j;
8206  Int_t nleaves = fLeaves.GetEntriesFast();
8207  TRegexp re(bname,kTRUE);
8208  Int_t nb = 0;
8209 
8210  // first pass, loop on all branches
8211  // for leafcount branches activate/deactivate in function of status
8212  for (i=0;i<nleaves;i++) {
8213  leaf = (TLeaf*)fLeaves.UncheckedAt(i);
8214  branch = (TBranch*)leaf->GetBranch();
8215  TString s = branch->GetName();
8216  if (strcmp(bname,"*")) { //Regexp gives wrong result for [] in name
8217  TString longname;
8218  longname.Form("%s.%s",GetName(),branch->GetName());
8219  if (strcmp(bname,branch->GetName())
8220  && longname != bname
8221  && s.Index(re) == kNPOS) continue;
8222  }
8223  nb++;
8224  if (status) branch->ResetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8225  else branch->SetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8226  leafcount = leaf->GetLeafCount();
8227  if (leafcount) {
8228  bcount = leafcount->GetBranch();
8229  if (status) bcount->ResetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8230  else bcount->SetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8231  }
8232  }
8233  if (nb==0 && strchr(bname,'*')==0) {
8234  branch = GetBranch(bname);
8235  if (branch) {
8236  if (status) branch->ResetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8237  else branch->SetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8238  ++nb;
8239  }
8240  }
8241 
8242  //search in list of friends
8243  UInt_t foundInFriend = 0;
8244  if (fFriends) {
8245  TFriendLock lock(this,kSetBranchStatus);
8246  TIter nextf(fFriends);
8247  TFriendElement *fe;
8248  TString name;
8249  while ((fe = (TFriendElement*)nextf())) {
8250  TTree *t = fe->GetTree();
8251  if (t==0) continue;
8252 
8253  // If the alias is present replace it with the real name.
8254  char *subbranch = (char*)strstr(bname,fe->GetName());
8255  if (subbranch!=bname) subbranch = 0;
8256  if (subbranch) {
8257  subbranch += strlen(fe->GetName());
8258  if ( *subbranch != '.' ) subbranch = 0;
8259  else subbranch ++;
8260  }
8261  if (subbranch) {
8262  name.Form("%s.%s",t->GetName(),subbranch);
8263  } else {
8264  name = bname;
8265  }
8266  t->SetBranchStatus(name,status, &foundInFriend);
8267  }
8268  }
8269  if (!nb && !foundInFriend) {
8270  if (found==0) {
8271  if (status) {
8272  if (strchr(bname,'*') != 0)
8273  Error("SetBranchStatus", "No branch name is matching wildcard -> %s", bname);
8274  else
8275  Error("SetBranchStatus", "unknown branch -> %s", bname);
8276  } else {
8277  if (strchr(bname,'*') != 0)
8278  Warning("SetBranchStatus", "No branch name is matching wildcard -> %s", bname);
8279  else
8280  Warning("SetBranchStatus", "unknown branch -> %s", bname);
8281  }
8282  }
8283  return;
8284  }
8285  if (found) *found = nb + foundInFriend;
8286 
8287  // second pass, loop again on all branches
8288  // activate leafcount branches for active branches only
8289  for (i = 0; i < nleaves; i++) {
8290  leaf = (TLeaf*)fLeaves.UncheckedAt(i);
8291  branch = (TBranch*)leaf->GetBranch();
8292  if (!branch->TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
8293  leafcount = leaf->GetLeafCount();
8294  if (leafcount) {
8295  bcount = leafcount->GetBranch();
8296  bcount->ResetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8297  }
8298  } else {
8299  //Int_t nbranches = branch->GetListOfBranches()->GetEntriesFast();
8300  Int_t nbranches = branch->GetListOfBranches()->GetEntries();
8301  for (j=0;j<nbranches;j++) {
8302  bson = (TBranch*)branch->GetListOfBranches()->UncheckedAt(j);
8303  if (!bson) continue;
8304  if (!bson->TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
8305  if (bson->GetNleaves() <= 0) continue;
8306  branch->ResetBit(kDoNotProcess);
8307  break;
8308  }
8309  }
8310  }
8311  }
8312 }
8313 
8314 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8315 /// Set the current branch style. (static function)
8316 ///
8317 /// - style = 0 old Branch
8318 /// - style = 1 new Bronch
8319 
8320 void TTree::SetBranchStyle(Int_t style)
8321 {
8322  fgBranchStyle = style;
8323 }

8325 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8326 /// Set maximum size of the file cache .
8327 //
8328 /// - if cachesize = 0 the existing cache (if any) is deleted.
8329 /// - if cachesize = -1 (default) it is set to the AutoFlush value when writing
8330 /// the Tree (default is 30 MBytes).
8331 ///
8332 /// Returns:
8333 /// - 0 size set, cache was created if possible
8334 /// - -1 on error
8335 
8336 Int_t TTree::SetCacheSize(Long64_t cacheSize)
8337 {
8338  // remember that the user has requested an explicit cache setup
8339  fCacheUserSet = kTRUE;
8340 
8341  return SetCacheSizeAux(kFALSE, cacheSize);
8342 }
8343 
8344 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8345 /// Set the size of the file cache and create it if possible.
8346 ///
8347 /// If autocache is true:
8348 /// this may be an autocreated cache, possibly enlarging an existing
8349 /// autocreated cache. The size is calculated. The value passed in cacheSize:
8350 /// - cacheSize = 0 make cache if default cache creation is enabled
8351 /// - cacheSize = -1 make a default sized cache in any case
8352 ///
8353 /// If autocache is false:
8354 /// this is a user requested cache. cacheSize is used to size the cache.
8355 /// This cache should never be automatically adjusted.
8356 ///
8357 /// Returns:
8358 /// - 0 size set, or existing autosized cache almost large enough.
8359 /// (cache was created if possible)
8360 /// - -1 on error
8361 
8362 Int_t TTree::SetCacheSizeAux(Bool_t autocache /* = kTRUE */, Long64_t cacheSize /* = 0 */ )
8363 {
8364  if (autocache) {
8365  // used as a once only control for automatic cache setup
8366  fCacheDoAutoInit = kFALSE;
8367  }
8368 
8369  if (!autocache) {
8370  // negative size means the user requests the default
8371  if (cacheSize < 0) {
8372  cacheSize = GetCacheAutoSize(kTRUE);
8373  }
8374  } else {
8375  if (cacheSize == 0) {
8376  cacheSize = GetCacheAutoSize();
8377  } else if (cacheSize < 0) {
8378  cacheSize = GetCacheAutoSize(kTRUE);
8379  }
8380  }
8381 
8382  TFile* file = GetCurrentFile();
8383  if (!file || GetTree() != this) {
8384  // if there's no file or we are not a plain tree (e.g. if we're a TChain)
8385  // do not create a cache, only record the size if one was given
8386  if (!autocache) {
8387  fCacheSize = cacheSize;
8388  }
8389  if (GetTree() != this) {
8390  return 0;
8391  }
8392  if (!autocache && cacheSize>0) {
8393  Warning("SetCacheSizeAux", "A TTreeCache could not be created because the TTree has no file");
8394  }
8395  return 0;
8396  }
8397 
8398  // Check for an existing cache
8399  TTreeCache* pf = GetReadCache(file);
8400  if (pf) {
8401  if (autocache) {
8402  // reset our cache status tracking in case existing cache was added
8403  // by the user without using one of the TTree methods
8404  fCacheSize = pf->GetBufferSize();
8405  fCacheUserSet = !pf->IsAutoCreated();
8406 
8407  if (fCacheUserSet) {
8408  // existing cache was created by the user, don't change it
8409  return 0;
8410  }
8411  } else {
8412  // update the cache to ensure it records the user has explicitly
8413  // requested it
8414  pf->SetAutoCreated(kFALSE);
8415  }
8416 
8417  // if we're using an automatically calculated size and the existing
8418  // cache is already almost large enough don't resize
8419  if (autocache && Long64_t(0.80*cacheSize) < fCacheSize) {
8420  // already large enough
8421  return 0;
8422  }
8423 
8424  if (cacheSize == fCacheSize) {
8425  return 0;
8426  }
8427 
8428  if (cacheSize == 0) {
8429  // delete existing cache
8430  pf->WaitFinishPrefetch();
8431  file->SetCacheRead(0,this);
8432  delete pf;
8433  pf = 0;
8434  } else {
8435  // resize
8436  Int_t res = pf->SetBufferSize(cacheSize);
8437  if (res < 0) {
8438  return -1;
8439  }
8440  }
8441  } else {
8442  // no existing cache
8443  if (autocache) {
8444  if (fCacheUserSet) {
8445  // value was already set manually.
8446  if (fCacheSize == 0) return 0;
8447  // Expected a cache should exist; perhaps the user moved it
8448  // Do nothing more here.
8449  if (cacheSize) {
8450  Error("SetCacheSizeAux", "Not setting up an automatically sized TTreeCache because of missing cache previously set");
8451  }
8452  return -1;
8453  }
8454  }
8455  }
8456 
8457  fCacheSize = cacheSize;
8458  if (cacheSize == 0 || pf) {
8459  return 0;
8460  }
8461 
8462 #ifdef R__USE_IMT
8463  if(TTreeCacheUnzip::IsParallelUnzip() && file->GetCompressionLevel() > 0)
8464  pf = new TTreeCacheUnzip(this, cacheSize);
8465  else
8466 #endif
8467  pf = new TTreeCache(this, cacheSize);
8468 
8469  pf->SetAutoCreated(autocache);
8470 
8471  return 0;
8472 }
8473 
8474 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8475 ///interface to TTreeCache to set the cache entry range
8476 ///
8477 /// Returns:
8478 /// - 0 entry range set
8479 /// - -1 on error
8480 
8481 Int_t TTree::SetCacheEntryRange(Long64_t first, Long64_t last)
8482 {
8483  if (!GetTree()) {
8484  if (LoadTree(0)<0) {
8485  Error("SetCacheEntryRange","Could not load a tree");
8486  return -1;
8487  }
8488  }
8489  if (GetTree()) {
8490  if (GetTree() != this) {
8491  return GetTree()->SetCacheEntryRange(first, last);
8492  }
8493  } else {
8494  Error("SetCacheEntryRange", "No tree is available. Could not set cache entry range");
8495  return -1;
8496  }
8497 
8498  TFile *f = GetCurrentFile();
8499  if (!f) {
8500  Error("SetCacheEntryRange", "No file is available. Could not set cache entry range");
8501  return -1;
8502  }
8503  TTreeCache *tc = GetReadCache(f,kTRUE);
8504  if (!tc) {
8505  Error("SetCacheEntryRange", "No cache is available. Could not set entry range");
8506  return -1;
8507  }
8508  tc->SetEntryRange(first,last);
8509  return 0;
8510 }

8512 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8513 /// Interface to TTreeCache to set the number of entries for the learning phase
8514 
8515 void TTree::SetCacheLearnEntries(Int_t n)
8516 {
8517  TTreeCache::SetLearnEntries(n);
8518 }
8519 
8520 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8521 /// Enable/Disable circularity for this tree.
8522 ///
8523 /// if maxEntries > 0 a maximum of maxEntries is kept in one buffer/basket
8524 /// per branch in memory.
8525 /// Note that when this function is called (maxEntries>0) the Tree
8526 /// must be empty or having only one basket per branch.
8527 /// if maxEntries <= 0 the tree circularity is disabled.
8528 ///
8529 /// #### NOTE 1:
8530 /// Circular Trees are interesting in online real time environments
8531 /// to store the results of the last maxEntries events.
8532 /// #### NOTE 2:
8533 /// Calling SetCircular with maxEntries <= 0 is necessary before
8534 /// merging circular Trees that have been saved on files.
8535 /// #### NOTE 3:
8536 /// SetCircular with maxEntries <= 0 is automatically called
8537 /// by TChain::Merge
8538 /// #### NOTE 4:
8539 /// A circular Tree can still be saved in a file. When read back,
8540 /// it is still a circular Tree and can be filled again.
8541 
8542 void TTree::SetCircular(Long64_t maxEntries)
8543 {
8544  if (maxEntries <= 0) {
8545  // Disable circularity.
8546  fMaxEntries = 1000000000;
8547  fMaxEntries *= 1000;
8548  ResetBit(kCircular);
8549  //in case the Tree was originally created in gROOT, the branch
8550  //compression level was set to -1. If the Tree is now associated to
8551  //a file, reset the compression level to the file compression level
8552  if (fDirectory) {
8553  TFile* bfile = fDirectory->GetFile();
8554  Int_t compress = ROOT::RCompressionSetting::EDefaults::kUseGeneralPurpose;
8555  if (bfile) {
8556  compress = bfile->GetCompressionSettings();
8557  }
8558  Int_t nb = fBranches.GetEntriesFast();
8559  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nb; i++) {
8560  TBranch* branch = (TBranch*) fBranches.UncheckedAt(i);
8561  branch->SetCompressionSettings(compress);
8562  }
8563  }
8564  } else {
8565  // Enable circularity.
8566  fMaxEntries = maxEntries;
8567  SetBit(kCircular);
8568  }
8569 }

8572 /// Set the debug level and the debug range.
8573 ///
8574 /// For entries in the debug range, the functions TBranchElement::Fill
8575 /// and TBranchElement::GetEntry will print the number of bytes filled
8576 /// or read for each branch.
8577 
8578 void TTree::SetDebug(Int_t level, Long64_t min, Long64_t max)

8585 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8586 /// Update the default value for the branch's fEntryOffsetLen.
8587 /// If updateExisting is true, also update all the existing branches.
8588 /// If newdefault is less than 10, the new default value will be 10.
8589 
8590 void TTree::SetDefaultEntryOffsetLen(Int_t newdefault, Bool_t updateExisting)
8591 {
8592  if (newdefault < 10) {
8593  newdefault = 10;
8594  }
8595  fDefaultEntryOffsetLen = newdefault;
8596  if (updateExisting) {
8597  TIter next( GetListOfBranches() );
8598  TBranch *b;
8599  while ( ( b = (TBranch*)next() ) ) {
8600  b->SetEntryOffsetLen( newdefault, kTRUE );
8601  }
8602  if (fBranchRef) {
8603  fBranchRef->SetEntryOffsetLen( newdefault, kTRUE );
8604  }
8605  }
8606 }

8608 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8609 /// Change the tree's directory.
8610 ///
8611 /// Remove reference to this tree from current directory and
8612 /// add reference to new directory dir. The dir parameter can
8613 /// be 0 in which case the tree does not belong to any directory.
8614 ///
8615 
8616 void TTree::SetDirectory(TDirectory* dir)
8617 {
8618  if (fDirectory == dir) {
8619  return;
8620  }
8621  if (fDirectory) {
8622  fDirectory->Remove(this);
8623 
8624  // Delete or move the file cache if it points to this Tree
8625  TFile *file = fDirectory->GetFile();
8626  MoveReadCache(file,dir);
8627  }
8628  fDirectory = dir;
8629  if (fDirectory) {
8630  fDirectory->Append(this);
8631  }
8632  TFile* file = 0;
8633  if (fDirectory) {
8634  file = fDirectory->GetFile();
8635  }
8636  if (fBranchRef) {
8637  fBranchRef->SetFile(file);
8638  }
8639  TBranch* b = 0;
8640  TIter next(GetListOfBranches());
8641  while((b = (TBranch*) next())) {
8642  b->SetFile(file);
8643  }
8644 }
8645 
8646 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8647 /// Change number of entries in the tree.
8648 ///
8649 /// If n >= 0, set number of entries in the tree = n.
8650 ///
8651 /// If n < 0, set number of entries in the tree to match the
8652 /// number of entries in each branch. (default for n is -1)
8653 ///
8654 /// This function should be called only when one fills each branch
8655 /// independently via TBranch::Fill without calling TTree::Fill.
8656 /// Calling TTree::SetEntries() make sense only if the number of entries
8657 /// in each branch is identical, a warning is issued otherwise.
8658 /// The function returns the number of entries.
8659 ///
8660 
8661 Long64_t TTree::SetEntries(Long64_t n)
8662 {
8663  // case 1 : force number of entries to n
8664  if (n >= 0) {
8665  fEntries = n;
8666  return n;
8667  }
8668 
8669  // case 2; compute the number of entries from the number of entries in the branches
8670  TBranch* b(nullptr), *bMin(nullptr), *bMax(nullptr);
8671  Long64_t nMin = kMaxEntries;
8672  Long64_t nMax = 0;
8673  TIter next(GetListOfBranches());
8674  while((b = (TBranch*) next())){
8675  Long64_t n2 = b->GetEntries();
8676  if (!bMin || n2 < nMin) {
8677  nMin = n2;
8678  bMin = b;
8679  }
8680  if (!bMax || n2 > nMax) {
8681  nMax = n2;
8682  bMax = b;
8683  }
8684  }
8685  if (bMin && nMin != nMax) {
8686  Warning("SetEntries", "Tree branches have different numbers of entries, eg %s has %lld entries while %s has %lld entries.",
8687  bMin->GetName(), nMin, bMax->GetName(), nMax);
8688  }
8689  fEntries = nMax;
8690  return fEntries;
8691 }
8692 
8693 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8694 /// Set an EntryList
8695 
8696 void TTree::SetEntryList(TEntryList *enlist, Option_t * /*opt*/)
8697 {
8698  if (fEntryList) {
8699  //check if the previous entry list is owned by the tree
8700  if (fEntryList->TestBit(kCanDelete)){
8701  delete fEntryList;
8702  }
8703  }
8704  fEventList = 0;
8705  if (!enlist) {
8706  fEntryList = 0;
8707  return;
8708  }
8709  fEntryList = enlist;
8710  fEntryList->SetTree(this);
8711 
8712 }
8713 
8714 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8715 /// This function transfroms the given TEventList into a TEntryList
8716 /// The new TEntryList is owned by the TTree and gets deleted when the tree
8717 /// is deleted. This TEntryList can be returned by GetEntryList() function.
8718 
8719 void TTree::SetEventList(TEventList *evlist)
8720 {
8721  fEventList = evlist;
8722  if (fEntryList){
8723  if (fEntryList->TestBit(kCanDelete)) {
8724  TEntryList *tmp = fEntryList;
8725  fEntryList = 0; // Avoid problem with RecursiveRemove.
8726  delete tmp;
8727  } else {
8728  fEntryList = 0;
8729  }
8730  }
8731 
8732  if (!evlist) {
8733  fEntryList = 0;
8734  fEventList = 0;
8735  return;
8736  }
8737 
8738  fEventList = evlist;
8739  char enlistname[100];
8740  snprintf(enlistname,100, "%s_%s", evlist->GetName(), "entrylist");
8741  fEntryList = new TEntryList(enlistname, evlist->GetTitle());
8742  fEntryList->SetDirectory(0); // We own this.
8743  Int_t nsel = evlist->GetN();
8744  fEntryList->SetTree(this);
8745  Long64_t entry;
8746  for (Int_t i=0; i<nsel; i++){
8747  entry = evlist->GetEntry(i);
8748  fEntryList->Enter(entry);
8749  }
8750  fEntryList->SetReapplyCut(evlist->GetReapplyCut());
8751  fEntryList->SetBit(kCanDelete, kTRUE);
8752 }

8754 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8755 /// Set number of entries to estimate variable limits.
8756 /// If n is -1, the estimate is set to be the current maximum
8757 /// for the tree (i.e. GetEntries() + 1)
8758 /// If n is less than -1, the behavior is undefined.
8759 
8760 void TTree::SetEstimate(Long64_t n /* = 1000000 */)
8761 {
8762  if (n == 0) {
8763  n = 10000;
8764  } else if (n < 0) {
8765  n = fEntries - n;
8766  }
8767  fEstimate = n;
8768  GetPlayer();
8769  if (fPlayer) {
8770  fPlayer->SetEstimate(n);
8771  }
8772 }

8774 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8775 /// Provide the end-user with the ability to enable/disable various experimental
8776 /// IO features for this TTree.
8777 ///
8778 /// Returns all the newly-set IO settings.
8779 
8780 ROOT::TIOFeatures TTree::SetIOFeatures(const ROOT::TIOFeatures &features)
8781 {
8782  // Purposely ignore all unsupported bits; TIOFeatures implementation already warned the user about the
8783  // error of their ways; this is just a safety check.
8784  UChar_t featuresRequested = features.GetFeatures() & static_cast<UChar_t>(TBasket::EIOBits::kSupported);
8785 
8786  UChar_t curFeatures = fIOFeatures.GetFeatures();
8787  UChar_t newFeatures = ~curFeatures & featuresRequested;
8788  curFeatures |= newFeatures;
8789  fIOFeatures.Set(curFeatures);
8790 
8791  ROOT::TIOFeatures newSettings(newFeatures);
8792  return newSettings;
8793 }
8794 
8795 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8796 /// Set fFileNumber to number.
8797 /// fFileNumber is used by TTree::Fill to set the file name
8798 /// for a new file to be created when the current file exceeds fgTreeMaxSize.
8799 /// (see TTree::ChangeFile)
8800 /// if fFileNumber=10, the new file name will have a suffix "_11",
8801 /// ie, fFileNumber is incremented before setting the file name
8802 
8803 void TTree::SetFileNumber(Int_t number)
8804 {
8805  if (fFileNumber < 0) {
8806  Warning("SetFileNumber", "file number must be positive. Set to 0");
8807  fFileNumber = 0;
8808  return;
8809  }
8810  fFileNumber = number;
8811 }

8842 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8843 /// Change the name of this tree.
8844 
8845 void TTree::SetName(const char* name)
8846 {
8847  if (gPad) {
8848  gPad->Modified();
8849  }
8850  // Trees are named objects in a THashList.
8851  // We must update hashlists if we change the name.
8852  TFile *file = 0;
8853  TTreeCache *pf = 0;
8854  if (fDirectory) {
8855  fDirectory->Remove(this);
8856  if ((file = GetCurrentFile())) {
8857  pf = GetReadCache(file);
8858  file->SetCacheRead(0,this,TFile::kDoNotDisconnect);
8859  }
8860  }
8861  // This changes our hash value.
8862  fName = name;
8863  if (fDirectory) {
8864  fDirectory->Append(this);
8865  if (pf) {
8866  file->SetCacheRead(pf,this,TFile::kDoNotDisconnect);
8867  }
8868  }
8869 }

8960 /// TChain, an option "global" may be specified to set the same weight

8969 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
8970 /// Print values of all active leaves for entry.
8971 ///
8972 /// - if entry==-1, print current entry (default)
8973 /// - if a leaf is an array, a maximum of lenmax elements is printed.
8974 
8975 void TTree::Show(Long64_t entry, Int_t lenmax)
8976 {
8977  if (entry != -1) {
8978  Int_t ret = LoadTree(entry);
8979  if (ret == -2) {
8980  Error("Show()", "Cannot read entry %lld (entry does not exist)", entry);
8981  return;
8982  } else if (ret == -1) {
8983  Error("Show()", "Cannot read entry %lld (I/O error)", entry);
8984  return;
8985  }
8986  ret = GetEntry(entry);
8987  if (ret == -1) {
8988  Error("Show()", "Cannot read entry %lld (I/O error)", entry);
8989  return;
8990  } else if (ret == 0) {
8991  Error("Show()", "Cannot read entry %lld (no data read)", entry);
8992  return;
8993  }
8994  }
8995  printf("======> EVENT:%lld\n", fReadEntry);
8996  TObjArray* leaves = GetListOfLeaves();
8997  Int_t nleaves = leaves->GetEntriesFast();
8998  Int_t ltype;
8999  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nleaves; i++) {
9000  TLeaf* leaf = (TLeaf*) leaves->UncheckedAt(i);
9001  TBranch* branch = leaf->GetBranch();
9002  if (branch->TestBit(kDoNotProcess)) {
9003  continue;
9004  }
9005  Int_t len = leaf->GetLen();
9006  if (len <= 0) {
9007  continue;
9008  }
9009  len = TMath::Min(len, lenmax);
9010  if (leaf->IsA() == TLeafElement::Class()) {
9011  leaf->PrintValue(lenmax);
9012  continue;
9013  }
9014  if (branch->GetListOfBranches()->GetEntriesFast() > 0) {
9015  continue;
9016  }
9017  ltype = 10;
9018  if (leaf->IsA() == TLeafF::Class()) {
9019  ltype = 5;
9020  }
9021  if (leaf->IsA() == TLeafD::Class()) {
9022  ltype = 5;
9023  }
9024  if (leaf->IsA() == TLeafC::Class()) {
9025  len = 1;
9026  ltype = 5;
9027  };
9028  printf(" %-15s = ", leaf->GetName());
9029  for (Int_t l = 0; l < len; l++) {
9030  leaf->PrintValue(l);
9031  if (l == (len - 1)) {
9032  printf("\n");
9033  continue;
9034  }
9035  printf(", ");
9036  if ((l % ltype) == 0) {
9037  printf("\n ");
9038  }
9039  }
9040  }
9041 }

9057 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9058 /// Stop the cache learning phase
9059 ///
9060 /// Returns:
9061 /// - 0 learning phase stopped or not active
9062 /// - -1 on error
9063 
9064 Int_t TTree::StopCacheLearningPhase()
9065 {
9066  if (!GetTree()) {
9067  if (LoadTree(0)<0) {
9068  Error("StopCacheLearningPhase","Could not load a tree");
9069  return -1;
9070  }
9071  }
9072  if (GetTree()) {
9073  if (GetTree() != this) {
9074  return GetTree()->StopCacheLearningPhase();
9075  }
9076  } else {
9077  Error("StopCacheLearningPhase", "No tree is available. Could not stop cache learning phase");
9078  return -1;
9079  }
9080 
9081  TFile *f = GetCurrentFile();
9082  if (!f) {
9083  Error("StopCacheLearningPhase", "No file is available. Could not stop cache learning phase");
9084  return -1;
9085  }
9086  TTreeCache *tc = GetReadCache(f,kTRUE);
9087  if (!tc) {
9088  Error("StopCacheLearningPhase", "No cache is available. Could not stop learning phase");
9089  return -1;
9090  }
9091  tc->StopLearningPhase();
9092  return 0;
9093 }

9095 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9096 /// Set the fTree member for all branches and sub branches.
9097 
9098 static void TBranch__SetTree(TTree *tree, TObjArray &branches)
9099 {
9100  Int_t nb = branches.GetEntriesFast();
9101  for (Int_t i = 0; i < nb; ++i) {
9102  TBranch* br = (TBranch*) branches.UncheckedAt(i);
9103  br->SetTree(tree);
9104 
9105  Int_t nBaskets = br->GetListOfBaskets()->GetEntries();
9106  Int_t writeBasket = br->GetWriteBasket();
9107  for (Int_t j=writeBasket,n=0;j>=0 && n<nBaskets;--j) {
9108  TBasket *bk = (TBasket*)br->GetListOfBaskets()->UncheckedAt(j);
9109  if (bk) {
9110  tree->IncrementTotalBuffers(bk->GetBufferSize());
9111  ++n;
9112  }
9113  }
9114 
9115  TBranch__SetTree(tree,*br->GetListOfBranches());
9116  }
9117 }
9118 
9119 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9120 /// Set the fTree member for all friend elements.
9121 
9122 void TFriendElement__SetTree(TTree *tree, TList *frlist)
9123 {
9124  if (frlist) {
9125  TObjLink *lnk = frlist->FirstLink();
9126  while (lnk) {
9127  TFriendElement *elem = (TFriendElement*)lnk->GetObject();
9128  elem->fParentTree = tree;
9129  lnk = lnk->Next();
9130  }
9131  }
9132 }
9133 
9134 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9135 /// Stream a class object.
9136 
9137 void TTree::Streamer(TBuffer& b)
9138 {
9139  if (b.IsReading()) {
9140  UInt_t R__s, R__c;
9141  if (fDirectory) {
9142  fDirectory->Remove(this);
9143  //delete the file cache if it points to this Tree
9144  TFile *file = fDirectory->GetFile();
9145  MoveReadCache(file,0);
9146  }
9147  fDirectory = 0;
9148  fCacheDoAutoInit = kTRUE;
9149  fCacheUserSet = kFALSE;
9150  Version_t R__v = b.ReadVersion(&R__s, &R__c);
9151  if (R__v > 4) {
9152  b.ReadClassBuffer(TTree::Class(), this, R__v, R__s, R__c);
9153 
9154  fBranches.SetOwner(kTRUE); // True needed only for R__v < 19 and most R__v == 19
9155 
9156  if (fBranchRef) fBranchRef->SetTree(this);
9157  TBranch__SetTree(this,fBranches);
9158  TFriendElement__SetTree(this,fFriends);
9159 
9160  if (fTreeIndex) {
9161  fTreeIndex->SetTree(this);
9162  }
9163  if (fIndex.fN) {
9164  Warning("Streamer", "Old style index in this tree is deleted. Rebuild the index via TTree::BuildIndex");
9165  fIndex.Set(0);
9166  fIndexValues.Set(0);
9167  }
9168  if (fEstimate <= 10000) {
9169  fEstimate = 1000000;
9170  }
9171 
9172  if (fNClusterRange) {
9173  // The I/O allocated just enough memory to hold the
9174  // current set of ranges.
9175  fMaxClusterRange = fNClusterRange;
9176  }
9177  if (GetCacheAutoSize() != 0) {
9178  // a cache will be automatically created.
9179  // No need for TTreePlayer::Process to enable the cache
9180  fCacheSize = 0;
9181  } else if (fAutoFlush < 0) {
9182  // If there is no autoflush set, let's keep the cache completely
9183  // disable by default for now.
9184  fCacheSize = fAutoFlush;
9185  } else if (fAutoFlush != 0) {
9186  // Estimate the cluster size.
9187  // This will allow TTree::Process to enable the cache.
9188  Long64_t zipBytes = GetZipBytes();
9189  Long64_t totBytes = GetTotBytes();
9190  if (zipBytes != 0) {
9191  fCacheSize = fAutoFlush*(zipBytes/fEntries);
9192  } else if (totBytes != 0) {
9193  fCacheSize = fAutoFlush*(totBytes/fEntries);
9194  } else {
9195  fCacheSize = 30000000;
9196  }
9197  if (fCacheSize >= (INT_MAX / 4)) {
9198  fCacheSize = INT_MAX / 4;
9199  } else if (fCacheSize == 0) {
9200  fCacheSize = 30000000;
9201  }
9202  } else {
9203  fCacheSize = 0;
9204  }
9205  ResetBit(kMustCleanup);
9206  return;
9207  }
9208  //====process old versions before automatic schema evolution
9209  Stat_t djunk;
9210  Int_t ijunk;
9211  TNamed::Streamer(b);
9212  TAttLine::Streamer(b);
9213  TAttFill::Streamer(b);
9214  TAttMarker::Streamer(b);
9215  b >> fScanField;
9216  b >> ijunk; fMaxEntryLoop = (Long64_t)ijunk;
9217  b >> ijunk; fMaxVirtualSize = (Long64_t)ijunk;
9218  b >> djunk; fEntries = (Long64_t)djunk;
9219  b >> djunk; fTotBytes = (Long64_t)djunk;
9220  b >> djunk; fZipBytes = (Long64_t)djunk;
9221  b >> ijunk; fAutoSave = (Long64_t)ijunk;
9222  b >> ijunk; fEstimate = (Long64_t)ijunk;
9223  if (fEstimate <= 10000) fEstimate = 1000000;
9224  fBranches.Streamer(b);
9225  if (fBranchRef) fBranchRef->SetTree(this);
9226  TBranch__SetTree(this,fBranches);
9227  fLeaves.Streamer(b);
9228  fSavedBytes = fTotBytes;
9229  if (R__v > 1) fIndexValues.Streamer(b);
9230  if (R__v > 2) fIndex.Streamer(b);
9231  if (R__v > 3) {
9232  TList OldInfoList;
9233  OldInfoList.Streamer(b);
9234  OldInfoList.Delete();
9235  }
9236  fNClusterRange = 0;
9237  fDefaultEntryOffsetLen = 1000;
9238  ResetBit(kMustCleanup);
9239  b.CheckByteCount(R__s, R__c, TTree::IsA());
9240  //====end of old versions
9241  } else {
9242  if (fBranchRef) {
9243  fBranchRef->Clear();
9244  }
9245  TRefTable *table = TRefTable::GetRefTable();
9246  if (table) TRefTable::SetRefTable(0);
9247 
9248  b.WriteClassBuffer(TTree::Class(), this);
9249 
9250  if (table) TRefTable::SetRefTable(table);
9251  }
9252 }
9253 
9254 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9255 /// Unbinned fit of one or more variable(s) from a tree.
9256 ///
9257 /// funcname is a TF1 function.
9258 ///
9259 /// See TTree::Draw for explanations of the other parameters.
9260 ///
9261 /// Fit the variable varexp using the function funcname using the
9262 /// selection cuts given by selection.
9263 ///
9264 /// The list of fit options is given in parameter option.
9265 ///
9266 /// - option = "Q" Quiet mode (minimum printing)
9267 /// - option = "V" Verbose mode (default is between Q and V)
9268 /// - option = "E" Perform better Errors estimation using Minos technique
9269 /// - option = "M" More. Improve fit results
9270 ///
9271 /// You can specify boundary limits for some or all parameters via
9272 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
9273 /// func->SetParLimits(p_number, parmin, parmax);
9274 /// ~~~
9275 /// if parmin>=parmax, the parameter is fixed
9276 ///
9277 /// Note that you are not forced to fix the limits for all parameters.
9278 /// For example, if you fit a function with 6 parameters, you can do:
9279 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
9280 /// func->SetParameters(0,3.1,1.e-6,0.1,-8,100);
9281 /// func->SetParLimits(4,-10,-4);
9282 /// func->SetParLimits(5, 1,1);
9283 /// ~~~
9284 /// With this setup:
9285 ///
9286 /// - Parameters 0->3 can vary freely
9287 /// - Parameter 4 has boundaries [-10,-4] with initial value -8
9288 /// - Parameter 5 is fixed to 100.
9289 ///
9290 /// For the fit to be meaningful, the function must be self-normalized.
9291 ///
9292 /// i.e. It must have the same integral regardless of the parameter
9293 /// settings. Otherwise the fit will effectively just maximize the
9294 /// area.
9295 ///
9296 /// It is mandatory to have a normalization variable
9297 /// which is fixed for the fit. e.g.
9298 /// ~~~ {.cpp}
9299 /// TF1* f1 = new TF1("f1", "gaus(0)/sqrt(2*3.14159)/[2]", 0, 5);
9300 /// f1->SetParameters(1, 3.1, 0.01);
9301 /// f1->SetParLimits(0, 1, 1); // fix the normalization parameter to 1
9302 /// data->UnbinnedFit("f1", "jpsimass", "jpsipt>3.0");
9303 /// ~~~
9304 /// 1, 2 and 3 Dimensional fits are supported. See also TTree::Fit
9305 ///
9306 /// Return status:
9307 ///
9308 /// - The function return the status of the fit in the following form
9309 /// fitResult = migradResult + 10*minosResult + 100*hesseResult + 1000*improveResult
9310 /// - The fitResult is 0 is the fit is OK.
9311 /// - The fitResult is negative in case of an error not connected with the fit.
9312 /// - The number of entries used in the fit can be obtained via mytree.GetSelectedRows();
9313 /// - If the number of selected entries is null the function returns -1
9314 
9315 Int_t TTree::UnbinnedFit(const char* funcname, const char* varexp, const char* selection, Option_t* option, Long64_t nentries, Long64_t firstentry)
9316 {
9317  GetPlayer();
9318  if (fPlayer) {
9319  return fPlayer->UnbinnedFit(funcname, varexp, selection, option, nentries, firstentry);
9320  }
9321  return -1;
9322 }

9331  SetFillStyle(gStyle->GetHistFillStyle());

9338  } else {
9339  gStyle->SetHistFillColor(GetFillColor());
9340  gStyle->SetHistFillStyle(GetFillStyle());
9341  gStyle->SetHistLineColor(GetLineColor());
9342  gStyle->SetHistLineStyle(GetLineStyle());

9376 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

9379 
9380 TTreeFriendLeafIter::TTreeFriendLeafIter(const TTree* tree, Bool_t dir)
9381 : fTree(const_cast<TTree*>(tree))

9401 /// Overridden assignment operator. Does NOT copy the 'cursor' location!
9402

9404 {

9407  fDirection = rhs1.fDirection;

9412 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9413 /// Overridden assignment operator. Does NOT copy the 'cursor' location!
9414 
9415 TTreeFriendLeafIter& TTreeFriendLeafIter::operator=(const TTreeFriendLeafIter& rhs)
9416 {
9417  if (this != &rhs) {
9418  fDirection = rhs.fDirection;
9419  }
9420  return *this;
9421 }
9422 
9423 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9424 /// Go the next friend element
9425 
9426 TObject* TTreeFriendLeafIter::Next()
9427 {
9428  if (!fTree) return 0;
9429 
9430  TObject * next;
9431  TTree * nextTree;
9432 
9433  if (!fLeafIter) {
9434  TObjArray *list = fTree->GetListOfLeaves();
9435  if (!list) return 0; // Can happen with an empty chain.
9436  fLeafIter = list->MakeIterator(fDirection);
9437  if (!fLeafIter) return 0;
9438  }
9439 
9440  next = fLeafIter->Next();
9441  if (!next) {
9442  if (!fTreeIter) {
9443  TCollection * list = fTree->GetListOfFriends();
9444  if (!list) return next;
9445  fTreeIter = list->MakeIterator(fDirection);
9446  if (!fTreeIter) return 0;
9447  }
9448  TFriendElement * nextFriend = (TFriendElement*) fTreeIter->Next();
9449  ///nextTree = (TTree*)fTreeIter->Next();
9450  if (nextFriend) {
9451  nextTree = const_cast<TTree*>(nextFriend->GetTree());
9452  if (!nextTree) return Next();
9453  SafeDelete(fLeafIter);
9454  fLeafIter = nextTree->GetListOfLeaves()->MakeIterator(fDirection);
9455  if (!fLeafIter) return 0;
9456  next = fLeafIter->Next();
9457  }
9458  }
9459  return next;
9460 }
9461 
9462 ////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
9463 /// Returns the object option stored in the list.
9464 
9465 Option_t* TTreeFriendLeafIter::GetOption() const
9466 {
9467  if (fLeafIter) return fLeafIter->GetOption();
9468  return "";
9469 }
